Thousands of years ago, our ancestors, in the Hexagram of Zhun, had already laid out for us the fundamental principles and boundaries for all our actions.

17
00:00:53,086 --> 00:00:56,052
With the existence of Heaven and Earth, all things are born.

18
00:00:56,052 --> 00:00:59,022
And all things are what fill the space between heaven and earth.

19
00:00:59,022 --> 00:01:01,012
And so, the Hexagram of Zhun follows.

20
00:01:01,012 --> 00:01:02,024
The character 'Zhun' signifies fullness.

21
00:01:02,024 --> 00:01:03,044
It is the beginning of all things.

22
00:01:03,044 --> 00:01:05,040
So, with that, we've covered Qian and Kun, the two parent trigrams.

23
00:01:05,040 --> 00:01:06,076
Now, it's time for life to begin its endless cycle of growth.

24
00:01:06,076 --> 00:01:08,042
The second hexagram in the I Ching is the 'Zhun' hexagram.

25
00:01:08,042 --> 00:01:09,074
As the saying goes, 'Zhun means to be full.'

26
00:01:09,074 --> 00:01:10,091
It signifies the beginning of all things.

27
00:01:10,091 --> 00:01:13,005
It's the stage where all things begin to sprout after the creation of heaven and earth.

28
00:01:13,005 --> 00:01:14,041
a scene of order just beginning to form.

29
00:01:14,041 --> 00:01:16,051
The reason the character '屯' (tún) is pronounced this way here,

30
00:01:16,051 --> 00:01:19,052


31
00:01:19,052 --> 00:01:24,066
The Shuowen Jiezi, an ancient Chinese dictionary, explains: "Tun means difficulty. It is an image of how plants struggle to sprout from the earth, full of hardship."

32
00:01:24,066 --> 00:01:26,088
It describes the scene of a seedling breaking through the soil, pushing aside the earth to sprout for the very first time.

33
00:01:26,088 --> 00:01:29,075
to describe 'the beginning of all things.'

34
00:01:29,075 --> 00:01:33,011
It describes the vitality and hardship of all things in their infancy.

35
00:01:33,011 --> 00:01:36,023
So, let's dive into what we have for you today.

36
00:01:40,052 --> 00:01:45,065
The Tun hexagram is Kan above and Zhen below. Now, Kan and Zhen... do you remember what we said about them in the last episode?

37
00:01:45,065 --> 00:01:47,049
They are the second son and the eldest son.

38
00:01:47,049 --> 00:01:49,063
They are the water of wisdom and the thunder of new life.

39
00:01:49,063 --> 00:01:51,028
That's why the Tun Hexagram is also known as "Water over Thunder."

40
00:01:51,028 --> 00:01:51,069
尊 (zūn)

41
00:01:51,069 --> 00:01:53,077
After the spring thunder roars, all things come back to life.

42
00:01:53,077 --> 00:01:55,081
And the spring rain, as precious as oil, nourishes all things.

43
00:01:55,081 --> 00:01:58,049
However, this is just an interpretation based on the combination of the trigrams' names.

44
00:01:58,049 --> 00:02:01,024
In terms of its imagery, it should be called 'Cloud and Thunder Zhun'.

45
00:02:01,024 --> 00:02:04,040
This is because having Water above Thunder signifies that the rain has not yet fallen.

46
00:02:04,040 --> 00:02:06,050
It means the heavy rain is ready to fall.

47
00:02:06,050 --> 00:02:11,048
This state, where the rain is about to fall but has not yet, is also the state just before the spring rain nourishes all things and new life begins.

48
00:02:11,048 --> 00:02:15,074
This is exactly what's stated in the Great Image Commentary: 'Clouds and thunder in Zhun; the superior person, in the same way, plans and manages affairs.'

49
00:02:15,074 --> 00:02:18,054
And this phrase, 'A noble person acts to bring order to the world,' is also a remarkably insightful summary.

50
00:02:18,054 --> 00:02:20,091
The term 'jinglun' originally referred to the art of weaving.

51
00:02:20,091 --> 00:02:23,013
The 'warp' refers to the vertical threads on a loom that are fixed in place.

52
00:02:23,013 --> 00:02:25,041
It forms the skeleton and backbone of the fabric. Once established,

53
00:02:25,041 --> 00:02:28,015
It runs through the entire process and cannot be altered at will. Otherwise, the fabric will fall apart.

54
00:02:28,015 --> 00:02:29,087
Otherwise, you'll just lose your footing.

55
00:02:29,087 --> 00:02:32,088
The 'weft' refers to the horizontal threads that are woven back and forth in the process of textile making.

56
00:02:32,088 --> 00:02:35,062
It's the thread that weaves the warp threads into a cohesive whole.

57
00:02:35,062 --> 00:02:37,036
This allows it to be flexible and adaptable.

58
00:02:37,036 --> 00:02:39,050
adjusting its density and color as needed.

59
00:02:39,050 --> 00:02:44,010
This term, "Jinglun," is used to describe the very beginning, when all things are just sprouting and fraught with peril.

60
00:02:44,010 --> 00:02:46,095
A person of integrity must bring order to chaos and find a clear path forward.

61
00:02:46,095 --> 00:02:48,067
First, establish the warp of strategy: the unchanging, immutable principles of the right path.

62
00:02:48,067 --> 00:02:50,063
an unchanging and righteous strategic vision.

63
00:02:50,063 --> 00:02:53,098
Then, weave in the weft of tactics—adaptable and situation-specific.

64
00:02:53,098 --> 00:02:56,068
Ultimately, in this state of brewing storm, where clouds and thunder clash but the rain has yet to fall,

65
00:02:56,068 --> 00:02:59,016
an era of 'Zhun' where vitality and chaos coexist.

66
00:02:59,016 --> 00:03:01,090
and emerge from this perilous state, from chaos to order.

67
00:03:01,090 --> 00:03:03,062
Don't worry about being completely in the dark.

68
00:03:03,062 --> 00:03:05,068
So, for the past thirty minutes of content,

69
00:03:05,068 --> 00:03:09,076
The answer to what we should do in the perilous early stages of growth will reveal itself.

70
00:03:09,076 --> 00:03:11,002
Now, let's look at the hexagram statement.

71
00:03:11,002 --> 00:03:12,026
Supreme success, perseverance.

72
00:03:12,026 --> 00:03:14,079
Do not act rashly. It is advantageous to establish a firm foundation.

73
00:03:14,079 --> 00:03:16,073
Now, the phrase 'Yuan Heng Li Zhen' that starts this off should be very familiar to us.

74
00:03:16,073 --> 00:03:18,061
The guiding principle of the 'Zhun Hexagram' is the same as that of the 'Qian Hexagram'.

75
00:03:18,061 --> 00:03:20,026
This means it carries on the virtue of Qian.

76
00:03:20,026 --> 00:03:21,092
"Yuan" signifies the beginning of all things.

77
00:03:21,092 --> 00:03:26,072
The presence of 'Yuan' in the hexagram's statement means that Heaven grants every living being a chance to begin.

78
00:03:26,072 --> 00:03:29,081
This is a crucial point. Take, for instance, the Meng hexagram, which comes later and is about the pursuit of knowledge.

79
00:03:29,081 --> 00:03:30,089
or the Xū hexagram, which is about sustenance.

80
00:03:30,089 --> 00:03:32,025
But none of those have the 'Yuan'.

81
00:03:32,025 --> 00:03:35,035
Not everyone is worthy of being taught.

82
00:03:35,035 --> 00:03:36,062
and those who are nurtured,

83
00:03:36,062 --> 00:03:39,044
The 'Heng' or 'persistence' signifies that as long as you follow the natural way of all things at their inception,

84
00:03:39,044 --> 00:03:40,022
Although it is arduous,

85
00:03:40,022 --> 00:03:42,069
it can still break through obstacles and grow smoothly.

86
00:03:42,069 --> 00:03:45,047
The character 'Li' signifies that during this initial, difficult stage of creation,

87
00:03:45,047 --> 00:03:46,099
it is necessary to pursue what is beneficial and reasonable.

88
00:03:46,099 --> 00:03:48,012
No greed, no delusion.

89
00:03:48,012 --> 00:03:50,057
The term 'Zhēn' refers to the stage of initial creation and establishment.

90
00:03:50,057 --> 00:03:51,088
facing a lack of foundation,

91
00:03:51,088 --> 00:03:53,090
and a host of other adverse factors, like a difficult road ahead.

92
00:03:53,090 --> 00:03:56,094
Only by adhering to the right path can you ensure your survival.

93
00:03:56,094 --> 00:03:58,002
This is the principle we mentioned earlier, "The noble person takes action to bring order to the world."

94
00:03:58,002 --> 00:04:01,010
that unchanging and timeless 'Jing'

95
00:04:01,010 --> 00:04:04,026
So, what exactly is the correct way to navigate the "Zhun" phase?

96
00:04:04,026 --> 00:04:05,068
And the Hexagram Statement immediately provides the answer.

97
00:04:05,068 --> 00:04:10,072
“Do not act rashly. It is favorable to establish a lord.” The first part, “Do not act rashly,” means you shouldn't make any large-scale, aggressive moves.

98
00:04:10,072 --> 00:04:12,054
or acting rashly with blind expansion.

99
00:04:12,054 --> 00:04:14,091
And this is how the Commentary on the Decision explains this line.

100
00:04:14,091 --> 00:04:18,013
Zhun. The firm and the yielding are first in interaction. Difficulty is born of movement within danger, yet it brings great success through perseverance.

101
00:04:18,013 --> 00:04:20,022
In the beginning, when all things are born and first created, they are tender and fragile.

102
00:04:20,022 --> 00:04:22,030
At the very beginning of creation and birth, everything is tender.

103
00:04:22,030 --> 00:04:23,076
and cannot withstand any destruction.

104
00:04:23,076 --> 00:04:27,064
The phrase "movement within danger" describes the characteristics of the Zhen and Kan trigrams.

105
00:04:27,064 --> 00:04:29,077
Zhen represents movement, and Kan represents danger.

106
00:04:29,077 --> 00:04:30,045
Now, let's take a closer look at the character 'Kǎn'.

107
00:04:30,045 --> 00:04:31,069
Now, let's take a closer look at this.

108
00:04:31,069 --> 00:04:33,015
From the very moment this character was created, the meaning of 'danger' has been etched into its core.

109
00:04:33,015 --> 00:04:36,013
has already been etched into its very core.

110
00:04:36,013 --> 00:04:38,052
The Shuowen Jiezi, an ancient Chinese dictionary, states that "Kǎn" means "a pit or a trap."

111
00:04:38,052 --> 00:04:41,004
Its original meaning refers to a sunken, uneven pit or hollow.

112
00:04:41,004 --> 00:04:43,026
In the Bagua, the Kan trigram is used to represent water.

113
00:04:43,026 --> 00:04:45,072
This is also because it is the nature of water to flow downwards.

114
00:04:45,072 --> 00:04:48,044
It will inevitably flow and gather in the lowest, sunken places.

115
00:04:48,044 --> 00:04:49,090
Although water nourishes all things,

116
00:04:49,090 --> 00:04:54,057
But the unfathomable depths of rivers, lakes, and seas also signify a peril that can devour life.

117
00:04:54,057 --> 00:04:56,034
So, in the context we're discussing today,

118
00:04:56,034 --> 00:04:59,062


119
00:04:59,062 --> 00:05:01,092
For instance, we talk about a 'rough patch' or 'getting over a hurdle'.

120
00:05:01,092 --> 00:05:04,072
All of these imply running into danger or facing a tough challenge.

121
00:05:04,072 --> 00:05:08,074
The Hexagram of Zhun signifies that the beginning of all things, their initial stage of creation, is fraught with hardship and peril.

122
00:05:08,074 --> 00:05:14,026
Even for the most colossal giants, any minor disaster or hardship at the very beginning of their sprouting can be utterly devastating.

123
00:05:14,026 --> 00:05:15,043
Let's take an example.

124
00:05:15,043 --> 00:05:18,031
The giant sequoia, the largest single-stem tree on Earth by volume,

125
00:05:18,031 --> 00:05:20,075
Take the famous General Sherman tree, for example.

126
00:05:20,075 --> 00:05:22,047
It stands nearly 84 meters tall, with a trunk volume of about 1,500 cubic meters.

127
00:05:24,064 --> 00:05:26,072
with a girth of over 30 meters at the base.

128
00:05:26,072 --> 00:05:28,091
It would take twenty grown adults to encircle its trunk.

129
00:05:28,091 --> 00:05:30,073
It's estimated to be around 2,200 years old.

130
00:05:30,073 --> 00:05:33,062
The average thickness of its bark is over 60 centimeters.

131
00:05:33,062 --> 00:05:36,072
It can withstand any wildfire or gale-force wind nature throws at it.

132
00:05:36,072 --> 00:05:40,081
So, this is a true titan, seemingly transcending the natural world.

133
00:05:40,081 --> 00:05:44,010
When it first breaks through the soil, it's less than a centimeter tall.

134
00:05:44,010 --> 00:05:45,054
Its stem is as thin as a strand of hair and completely lacks any woody structure.

135
00:05:45,054 --> 00:05:47,030
It has no woody structure whatsoever.

136
00:05:47,030 --> 00:05:49,060
It can barely stand upright, relying solely on the turgor pressure of its cells.

137
00:05:49,060 --> 00:05:52,012
The slightest touch will cause it to bend and snap.

138
00:05:52,012 --> 00:05:54,060
If a gust of wind were to blow, or even a raindrop were to fall at this moment,

139
00:05:54,060 --> 00:05:56,044
Even a single raindrop could be enough to kill it.

140
00:05:56,044 --> 00:05:59,048
Even if you just happened to take a leak on it, you'd kill it.

141
00:05:59,048 --> 00:06:02,073
No matter how incredible a person, thing, or idea is, when it's just born...

142
00:06:02,073 --> 00:06:05,020
are extremely vulnerable in their infancy.

143
00:06:05,020 --> 00:06:07,028
Take Ma Huateng, for example, back when QQ had just launched.

144
00:06:07,028 --> 00:06:09,048
And with their funding about to run out and no one using the product, he then gathered the founders...

145
00:06:09,048 --> 00:06:10,086
So, I had to get the founders together,

146
00:06:10,086 --> 00:06:13,094
They'd pretend to be 'Lan Lan,' 'Xiao Yu,' and 'Wei Wei' to chat with users!

147
00:06:13,094 --> 00:06:16,038
The final line of the hexagram statement is 'It is beneficial to establish a feudal lord.'

148
00:06:16,038 --> 00:06:19,081
The term 'establishing feudal lords,' in its original sense, meant enfeoffing vassals and founding states.

149
00:06:19,081 --> 00:06:21,079
This is extended to mean establishing a foundation.

150
00:06:21,079 --> 00:06:24,059
This means building a framework, establishing order, and attracting talent.

151
00:06:24,059 --> 00:06:25,095
The phrase 'li jian hou' refers to the early stages of creation and inception.

152
00:06:25,095 --> 00:06:28,088
You must first solidify your foundation.

153
00:06:28,088 --> 00:06:30,028
First, establish order.

154
00:06:30,028 --> 00:06:32,080
First, build a small, positive feedback loop.

155
00:06:32,080 --> 00:06:35,010
You need to get your model up and running first.

156
00:06:35,010 --> 00:06:37,092
First, get your cash flow positive, just to survive.

157
00:06:37,092 --> 00:06:40,040
and only then can you start thinking about grand plans for future expansion.

158
00:06:40,040 --> 00:06:41,086
Take the giant sequoia we just talked about, for example.

159
00:06:41,086 --> 00:06:43,008
Now, you're probably wondering,

160
00:06:43,008 --> 00:06:45,032
So, this thing, so fragile in its infancy...

161
00:06:45,032 --> 00:06:47,060
So, how did it manage to survive that dangerous period?

162
00:06:47,060 --> 00:06:50,028
This giant sequoia is the perfect embodiment of the Tun Hexagram!

163
00:06:50,028 --> 00:06:53,085
First off, it makes the absolute most of the right time and place.

164
00:06:53,085 --> 00:06:57,000
It absolutely will not just sprout in any ordinary environment.

165
00:06:57,000 --> 00:06:59,056
Its cones are tightly sealed by resin,

166
00:06:59,056 --> 00:07:02,030
This allows the seeds to be preserved intact on the tree for up to 20 years.

167
00:07:02,030 --> 00:07:07,072
Only the intense heat of a wildfire, over 80 degrees Celsius, can melt the resin and cause the cone to split open.

168
00:07:07,072 --> 00:07:09,024
awakening its seeds.

169
00:07:09,024 --> 00:07:11,032
The reason for this specific condition

170
00:07:11,032 --> 00:07:15,044
is that wildfires can burn away the old layer of dead branches and fallen leaves.

171
00:07:15,044 --> 00:07:17,088
This allows the seeds to make direct contact with the soil.

172
00:07:17,088 --> 00:07:20,019
This prevents the problem of seeds failing to take root.

173
00:07:20,019 --> 00:07:24,009
The wildfire burns away the low shrubs, weeds, and other competing tree species.

174
00:07:24,009 --> 00:07:26,003
With no competitors to block the sunlight or steal water,

175
00:07:26,003 --> 00:07:29,032
The intense heat from the wildfire also wiped out the local rodents.

176
00:07:29,032 --> 00:07:31,042
pest eggs, and pathogenic fungi in the soil.

177
00:07:31,042 --> 00:07:34,072
This dramatically lowers the chances of the seedlings being eaten or infected by disease.

178
00:07:34,072 --> 00:07:39,010
The ash left behind by the wildfire acts as a natural fertilizer and a layer that locks in moisture.

179
00:07:39,010 --> 00:07:42,002
providing nutrients for the seedlings while also acting as a layer of sunscreen.

180
00:07:42,002 --> 00:07:43,018
Have you ever noticed?

181
00:07:43,018 --> 00:07:46,042
Right from the moment a giant sequoia sprouts, it's all about 'do not act rashly'.

182
00:07:46,042 --> 00:07:48,056
It means 'Don't act blindly.'

183
00:07:48,056 --> 00:07:52,094
By the time it does make a move, it has already shielded itself from most fatal risks in advance.

184
00:07:52,094 --> 00:07:55,060
And just how far does this 'favorable to establish a domain' principle go?

185
00:07:55,060 --> 00:07:57,092
A sprout that has just broken through the soil doesn't grow upwards.

186
00:07:57,092 --> 00:07:58,068
It doesn't show off.

187
00:07:58,068 --> 00:08:00,072
It puts all its energy into taking root downward.

188
00:08:00,072 --> 00:08:02,024
In the first three months after it sprouts,

189
00:08:02,024 --> 00:08:05,038
It will dedicate 90% of its energy to growing its root system downwards.

190
00:08:05,038 --> 00:08:07,074
When its above-ground part is only two centimeters tall,

191
00:08:07,074 --> 00:08:11,000
its main taproot has already penetrated 30 centimeters deep into the soil.

192
00:08:11,000 --> 00:08:12,062
By the end of the first year,

193
00:08:12,062 --> 00:08:14,034
the seedling is about 10 centimeters tall.

194
00:08:14,034 --> 00:08:17,040
But its root system has already formed a network one meter in diameter.

195
00:08:17,040 --> 00:08:19,088
Once the roots penetrate into the deeper soil layers,

196
00:08:19,088 --> 00:08:21,068
it's no longer in a state where it would die at the slightest touch.

197
00:08:21,068 --> 00:08:24,088
First off, the sapling on the surface doesn't show its true strength.

198
00:08:24,088 --> 00:08:27,036
So when strong winds blow, there's not much surface area for them to catch.

199
00:08:27,036 --> 00:08:28,062
Even if an accident happens,

200
00:08:28,062 --> 00:08:30,057
as long as the main root is deep enough,

201
00:08:30,057 --> 00:08:32,096
it can still self-recover and stand upright again.

202
00:08:32,096 --> 00:08:34,030
and stand tall once again.

203
00:08:34,030 --> 00:08:37,006
The 'Tuan Zhuan' further elaborates on this state of frenzied root-growth.

204
00:08:37,006 --> 00:08:41,062
The movement of thunder and rain fills the heavens, creating a time of primitive chaos. It is suitable to establish a lord, yet there is no peace.

205
00:08:41,062 --> 00:08:44,064
This means that the thunderstorm is already brewing in the heavens, all set to unleash.

206
00:08:44,064 --> 00:08:47,090
And what follows is a scene of thunderbolts striking, rain pouring down, and the earth thrown into chaos.

207
00:08:47,090 --> 00:08:49,014
In this state, it is "suitable to establish a domain, but there is no tranquility."

208
00:08:49,014 --> 00:08:51,005
It's like having a sword at your throat, leaving you no peace.

209
00:08:51,005 --> 00:08:54,093
The Tuan Zhuan, while emphasizing the need to put down roots and establish a foundation, also stresses the phrase 'and not to be tranquil'.

210
00:08:54,093 --> 00:08:55,079
In other words,

211
00:08:55,079 --> 00:08:58,028
Even if you don't rush ahead or try to expand,

212
00:08:58,028 --> 00:09:00,099
So, while you should 'not act rashly,' you must also be putting down roots.

213
00:09:00,099 --> 00:09:02,091
But you also need to be aware of the risks.

214
00:09:02,091 --> 00:09:07,014
Seize every moment to strengthen your roots and build a solid foundation.

215
00:09:07,014 --> 00:09:08,070
You must not be tempted by a false sense of security.

216
00:09:08,070 --> 00:09:09,048
It's no time to be fooling around.

217
00:09:09,048 --> 00:09:11,012
Working only half a day every day, that's not what being steady means.

218
00:09:11,012 --> 00:09:12,057
That's not what being steady means at all.

219
00:09:12,057 --> 00:09:15,002
