00:19:00,057 --> 00:19:01,086
So, what's our next move?

436
00:19:01,086 --> 00:19:03,098
You might even get framed and trapped in a setup.

437
00:19:03,098 --> 00:19:05,048
What kind of future could you possibly have left?

438
00:19:05,048 --> 00:19:09,090
The Xiang Zhuan provides additional commentary on this line: The difficulty of the second six line comes from it being 'ridden' by a firm line. It says, 'ten years to finally have a child'—this is an anomaly.

439
00:19:09,090 --> 00:19:11,074
And the phrase 'ten years to bear a child' signifies a reversal of the natural order.

440
00:19:11,074 --> 00:19:15,057
The term 'riding the firm' refers to a state where a yin line is positioned above a yang line.

441
00:19:15,057 --> 00:19:17,046
The third six is positioned above the first nine.

442
00:19:17,046 --> 00:19:18,084
Although it is in its correct position and central, it is over a strong line.

443
00:19:18,084 --> 00:19:22,059
The Qian and Kun hexagrams are either entirely yang or entirely yin.

444
00:19:22,059 --> 00:19:24,049
So the issue of 'riding the firm' doesn't come into play here.

445
00:19:24,049 --> 00:19:27,034
Starting from the third hexagram, a new condition comes into play.

446
00:19:27,034 --> 00:19:28,096
When the yin is above the yang,

447
00:19:28,096 --> 00:19:32,078
It will naturally be pressured and impacted by the masculine energy below.

448
00:19:32,078 --> 00:19:35,018
This signifies a state where the movement of thunder and rain fills the heavens, creating a time of chaos and new beginnings.

449
00:19:35,018 --> 00:19:38,070
It's a state of chaotic disorder.

450
00:19:38,070 --> 00:19:40,064
You know, it's like the calm before the storm.

451
00:19:40,064 --> 00:19:42,078
This is an anomaly in the objective state of affairs at this moment.

452
00:19:42,078 --> 00:19:44,026
It has nothing to do with us personally.

453
00:19:44,026 --> 00:19:45,084
And this stage corresponds to...

454
00:19:45,084 --> 00:19:48,018
When we are like a tender sprout that has just broken through the soil,

455
00:19:48,018 --> 00:19:52,002
You'll be looked down on, taken advantage of, fed empty promises, and set up for failure.

456
00:19:52,002 --> 00:19:54,030
And the thing is, we haven't actually done anything wrong.

457
00:19:54,030 --> 00:19:57,072
But all sorts of misfortunes will still come our way.

458
00:19:57,072 --> 00:20:01,057
Now, for those of you who haven't been following our content, you're probably having one of two reactions right now.

459
00:20:01,057 --> 00:20:04,007
First, self-doubt and internal conflict.

460
00:20:04,007 --> 00:20:08,069
They'll blame the predicament on something they did wrong.

461
00:20:08,069 --> 00:20:11,068
Second, you become reckless and impulsive, even to the point of panicking and making desperate moves.

462
00:20:11,068 --> 00:20:15,080
They're desperately hoping for some external force to save them from their misery.

463
00:20:15,080 --> 00:20:17,098
You'll go with anyone who comes along and offers a hand.

464
00:20:17,098 --> 00:20:20,080
Remember, at this point, don't get caught up in internal struggles, and even more importantly, don't act on impulse.

465
00:20:20,080 --> 00:20:22,066
This is because 'the difficulty of the second six is that it rides on the firm.'

466
00:20:22,066 --> 00:20:24,056
It's not that we've done anything wrong.

467
00:20:24,056 --> 00:20:28,020
Instead, it's because our position in the ecosystem, being at the Second Six line of the Zhun hexagram, is inherently destined to be a tough one.

468
00:20:28,020 --> 00:20:30,074
This is also the state where you're most vulnerable to weakness and internal conflict.

469
00:20:30,074 --> 00:20:33,044
And then, someone comes along with a so-called 'proposal' for us.

470
00:20:33,044 --> 00:20:37,002
You think he gets you, that he's being completely open and honest with you.

471
00:20:37,002 --> 00:20:38,097
You think it's a 'a man dies for his bosom friend',

472
00:20:38,097 --> 00:20:41,095
But in reality, they're just using you as a cheap, expendable pawn.

473
00:20:41,095 --> 00:20:44,009
You thought they were going to marry you properly,

474
00:20:44,009 --> 00:20:45,069
But in reality, they're just playing you.

475
00:20:45,069 --> 00:20:49,088
This is where the principle of 'ten years to establish, a return to the norm' is needed to guide your path.

476
00:20:49,088 --> 00:20:53,084
Here, the character '反' is a variant of '返', which means 'to return'. So it signifies 'returning to a normal state'.

477
00:20:53,084 --> 00:20:56,030
The phrase 'ten years to establish' means to stay true to your core mission, keep putting down roots, and let things play out over time.

478
00:20:56,030 --> 00:20:57,046
While you're focusing on putting down roots,

479
00:20:57,046 --> 00:20:59,083
and let the bullet fly for a long time.

480
00:20:59,083 --> 00:21:01,087
And just like that, once the chaotic, formative period is over, everything naturally returns to normal.

481
00:21:01,087 --> 00:21:03,060
And everything will return to normal.

482
00:21:03,060 --> 00:21:05,050
By then, you'll see who the real MVP is.

483
00:21:05,050 --> 00:21:07,064
and who's all talk, you'll be able to see clearly.

484
00:21:07,064 --> 00:21:10,086
And by then, you'll have gained enough strength to earn the right to a proper, legitimate union.

485
00:21:10,086 --> 00:21:13,022
and earn the right to be with them openly and properly.

486
00:21:13,022 --> 00:21:17,006
Since ancient times, a lasting partnership has always been about being well-matched!

487
00:21:17,006 --> 00:21:21,036
So, when you're this little newbie and suddenly faced with overwhelming kindness and special treatment...

488
00:21:21,036 --> 00:21:23,068
Now, let that sink in for a moment.

489
00:21:23,068 --> 00:21:26,064
What resources do we have that command a premium price?

490
00:21:26,064 --> 00:21:31,072
If not, what do you think they're trying to get from us?

491
00:21:32,028 --> 00:21:33,061
The Line Statement for the Third Six.

492
00:21:33,061 --> 00:21:35,063
The hexagram text says: 'To chase a deer without a guide is to enter the forest alone.'

493
00:21:35,063 --> 00:21:37,076
A noble person should know when to stop. It is better to let it go than to press on and face regret.

494
00:21:37,076 --> 00:21:39,076
To chase a deer without a guide is to lose your way in the forest.

495
00:21:39,076 --> 00:21:42,003
The original meaning of the character '即' (jì) is 'to eat'.

496
00:21:42,003 --> 00:21:44,061
Because the process of eating involves approaching food.

497
00:21:44,061 --> 00:21:47,022
And so, the character '即' was extended to also mean 'to approach'.

498
00:21:47,022 --> 00:21:49,054
This phrase means to hunt for prey.

499
00:21:49,054 --> 00:21:52,028
but without a gamekeeper familiar with the mountains and forests as a guide.

500
00:21:52,028 --> 00:21:56,015
Ultimately, they can only charge into a perilous and unknown jungle, finding themselves in a dangerous situation.

501
00:21:56,015 --> 00:21:58,020
For the noble person, it is better to let go of an opportunity than to press forward and face humiliation.

502
00:21:58,020 --> 00:22:01,022
Here, the character 'jī' refers to the subtle signs of how things are developing.

503
00:22:01,022 --> 00:22:02,044
As the saying goes, "Ji refers to the subtle signs of change, the early omens of fortune."

504
00:22:02,044 --> 00:22:02,072
danger.

505
00:22:02,072 --> 00:22:04,032
and a precursor to fortune.

506
00:22:04,032 --> 00:22:05,062
So, what this means is,

507
00:22:05,062 --> 00:22:09,048
If you can recognize that 'chasing a deer without a guide' is a dangerous sign,

508
00:22:09,048 --> 00:22:13,016
and by giving up the prey that's run deep into the forest, we can cut our losses.

509
00:22:13,016 --> 00:22:14,064
But if you insist on going in,

510
00:22:14,064 --> 00:22:17,008
then the result will be nothing but hardship and adversity.

511
00:22:17,008 --> 00:22:18,080
Now, 'difficulty' isn't the same as 'blame' or 'misfortune',

512
00:22:18,080 --> 00:22:20,094
But the overall trend is still very unfavorable.

513
00:22:20,094 --> 00:22:22,064
The Xiang Zhuan, or the Commentary on the Images, explains this very well.

514
00:22:22,064 --> 00:22:25,055
A noble person abandons this path, for to proceed leads to hardship and ruin.

515
00:22:25,055 --> 00:22:27,001
You have to resist the temptation and not follow the deer into the woods.

516
00:22:27,001 --> 00:22:28,087
Don't follow the deer into the woods.

517
00:22:28,087 --> 00:22:31,006
If you do go in, the outcome is 'exhaustion'—you'll be trapped with no way out.

518
00:22:31,006 --> 00:22:34,005
The path narrows and narrows until there's nowhere left to go.

519
00:22:34,005 --> 00:22:36,075
The third six is a yin line in a yang position, which is a misplaced position, and it has also lost its centrality.

520
00:22:36,075 --> 00:22:38,085
We've now reached the top of the lower trigram.

521
00:22:38,085 --> 00:22:41,012
This position alone calls for extreme caution.

522
00:22:41,012 --> 00:22:42,072
And the upper trigram is Kan, which represents danger.

523
00:22:42,072 --> 00:22:45,040
Just like a dense forest, it's fraught with danger.

524
00:22:45,040 --> 00:22:47,082
The third six line uses the metaphor of chasing a deer into the forest.

525
00:22:47,082 --> 00:22:51,014
This describes how our young sapling has now reached another layer of temptation.

526
00:22:51,014 --> 00:22:54,068
So, this so-called 'deer' represents all those things that you feel like you could get if you just stretch a little harder.

527
00:22:54,068 --> 00:22:56,062
profits and trends that seem just within your grasp.

528
00:22:56,062 --> 00:22:58,034
Now, there's one thing we need to pay attention to here.

529
00:22:58,034 --> 00:23:02,052
Now, it's not that we're being told not to make a profit or seize opportunities.

530
00:23:02,052 --> 00:23:06,044
Instead, it's asking: do you have a guide? Do you have an insider?

531
00:23:06,044 --> 00:23:07,074
Or to be more precise,

532
00:23:07,074 --> 00:23:10,053
And this 'Yu' isn't just about external help.

533
00:23:10,053 --> 00:23:12,049
授之以鱼不如授之以渔。

534
00:23:12,049 --> 00:23:16,033
It's about whether you yourself have a deep enough understanding of the rules of the industry.

535
00:23:16,033 --> 00:23:20,044
and be fully aware of all the traps lurking deep in the jungle, the ones specifically designed to prey on newcomers.

536
00:23:20,044 --> 00:23:21,070
Let's say, for example,

537
00:23:21,070 --> 00:23:26,000
You know, things like franchise fees and deposits, or promises like, 'Open a store with zero experience, get full support from headquarters, and earn tens of thousands a month!'

538
00:23:26,000 --> 00:23:27,060
and make, like, a gazillion bucks a month!

539
00:23:27,060 --> 00:23:29,056
For instance, let's talk about some pretty funny phenomena that have been popping up recently.

540
00:23:29,056 --> 00:23:33,036
So, 'Business KTV' is a place where you 'discuss K-lines'...

541
00:23:33,036 --> 00:23:36,027
The point being, we must put down roots.

542
00:23:36,027 --> 00:23:38,075
You need to carefully understand the rules of the industry.

543
00:23:38,075 --> 00:23:41,037
and understand the pitfalls set by your peers and colleagues.

544
00:23:41,037 --> 00:23:44,051
Never, ever, when your foundation is still shaky, you're not familiar with the rules, and you lack experience...

545
00:23:44,051 --> 00:23:47,018
and get tempted by the promise of profit.

546
00:23:47,018 --> 00:23:50,074
Now, this isn't to say that the deep woods are always filled with traps set to ensnare you.

547
00:23:50,074 --> 00:23:52,054
There are many,

548
00:23:52,054 --> 00:23:53,070
Oh, absolutely.

549
00:23:53,070 --> 00:23:55,028
The mistakes you could make.

550
00:23:55,028 --> 00:24:00,095
For instance, if from day one of your startup, you don't deeply grasp the life-or-death importance of cash flow...

551
00:24:00,095 --> 00:24:02,051
Then you're bound to fall for some temptation down the line,

552
00:24:02,051 --> 00:24:07,048
and burn through all your reserves, you'll likely face a 'corporate heart attack'.

553
00:24:07,048 --> 00:24:09,064
It's not like all the organs have failed.

554
00:24:09,064 --> 00:24:14,048
It's like you can't even catch your breath before competitors rush in, forcing you out of the market, breaking you, and buying you for pennies on the dollar.

555
00:24:14,048 --> 00:24:16,078
We always encourage the principle of 'actions speak louder than words.'

556
00:24:16,078 --> 00:24:19,006
But that statement isn't entirely correct.

557
00:24:19,006 --> 00:24:19,094
To be more precise,

558
00:24:19,094 --> 00:24:25,037
We always encourage that actions speak louder than words, but only within the bounds of common sense and the rules.

559
00:24:25,037 --> 00:24:28,048
When we're unfamiliar with the rules and have no expert to guide us,

560
00:24:28,048 --> 00:24:29,068
and you have no plan for moving forward or falling back,

561
00:24:29,068 --> 00:24:31,092
and have no surplus resources to fall back on,

562
00:24:31,092 --> 00:24:35,002
No matter how tempting an opportunity may be, you must not take it.

563
00:24:35,002 --> 00:24:38,018
Dark clouds loom, lightning flashes, thunder roars, and a violent wind howls.

564
00:24:38,018 --> 00:24:39,088
In the beginning, when all things are being established,

565
00:24:39,088 --> 00:24:42,000
Beware of reckless ambition that blinds you to the risks.

566
00:24:42,000 --> 00:24:45,030
In fact, even if you've already got one foot caught in the jungle,

567
00:24:45,030 --> 00:24:48,024
In fact, you're still fine at this point. All you have to do is pull back.

568
00:24:48,024 --> 00:24:49,092
A person of virtue simply lets it go.

569
00:24:49,092 --> 00:24:51,016
You must be vigilant.

570
00:24:51,016 --> 00:24:52,008
You have to remind yourself that at this stage, there are no so-called 'great opportunities' to speak of.

571
00:24:52,008 --> 00:24:54,052
That's it.

572
00:24:54,052 --> 00:24:58,098
Don't let the lure of profit lead you blindly into dangerous territory you neither know nor can control.

573
00:24:58,098 --> 00:25:00,051
Have you guys noticed something?

574
00:25:00,051 --> 00:25:03,071
The third and fourth lines of the Zhun Hexagram are all about temptation.

575
00:25:03,071 --> 00:25:06,061
Now, don't you see how profound the wisdom of our ancestors is?

576
00:25:06,061 --> 00:25:11,031
Let's think about ourselves for a second. When we first stepped out into the real world, we thought everything was just so simple, didn't we?

577
00:25:11,031 --> 00:25:14,042
When you first get a little money, you feel like opportunities are everywhere.

578
00:25:14,042 --> 00:25:16,006
Have you ever had that experience where you didn't really know what you were doing, but you just opened an account and jumped right into the stock market?

579
00:25:16,006 --> 00:25:18,012
or the time you just opened an account and jumped right into the stock market?

580
00:25:18,012 --> 00:25:21,015
Have you ever been so fired up by just a few words from someone else?

581
00:25:21,015 --> 00:25:24,063
Our ancestors, through these very hexagrams, were telling us all along: it's all a mirage!

582
00:25:24,063 --> 00:25:26,063
Resist the temptation and put down your roots.

583
00:25:26,063 --> 00:25:27,083
There will be plenty of truly good opportunities in the future.

584
00:25:27,083 --> 00:25:30,094
The prerequisite is that you are worthy of it.

585
00:25:30,094 --> 00:25:32,028
For you, who have just begun to sprout,

586
00:25:32,028 --> 00:25:35,042
It's not yet time to think about those distant things.

587
00:25:35,042 --> 00:25:37,076
Only with tranquility can one achieve far-reaching goals.

588
00:25:37,076 --> 00:25:39,072
Six in the Fourth. Let's look at the line statement.

589
00:25:39,072 --> 00:25:42,092
"Riding a horse, treading warily. It is auspicious to go forward for a marriage proposal. There is nothing unfavorable."

590
00:25:42,092 --> 00:25:45,054
The key here is the character '求' (qiú), which means 'to seek' or 'to pursue'.

591
00:25:45,054 --> 00:25:49,028
In the I Ching, the interaction from a lower line to a higher one is called 'cheng'.

592
00:25:49,028 --> 00:25:54,060
It means 'to hold up with both hands, to carry, to serve.' This state of fulfilling one's proper role is auspicious.

593
00:25:54,060 --> 00:25:57,048
However, if you seek from the bottom up, it's almost always inauspicious.

594
00:25:57,048 --> 00:26:01,042
Because the character 'qiú' doesn't carry the same meaning as the modern word for 'request' or 'seek help', which implies a sense of weakness.

595
00:26:05,018 --> 00:26:07,040
In oracle bone script, the character 'qiú' depicts a whole animal hide with the fur on the outside. Its original meaning is 'qiú', as in the 'qiú' of 'qiú qiān rèn' (a thousand ren of furs).

596
00:26:07,040 --> 00:26:09,056
In ancient times, this was a precious item.

597
00:26:09,056 --> 00:26:12,076
It had to be obtained through hunting, trade, or demanding.

598
00:26:12,076 --> 00:26:14,044
So, its extended meaning, derived from 'acquiring precious things,' is...

599
00:26:14,044 --> 00:26:18,057
It means to take the initiative, to forcibly demand, or to overstep one's bounds in pursuit.

600
00:26:18,057 --> 00:26:21,088
Basically, it's only auspicious to 'seek' from a position of higher authority.

601
00:26:21,088 --> 00:26:24,022
Because only from a higher position can you rightfully seek to acquire.

602
00:26:24,022 --> 00:26:25,068
So, what this line of the hexagram is saying is...

603
00:26:25,068 --> 00:26:27,066
A sprouting seedling halts and hesitates.

604
00:26:27,066 --> 00:26:29,020
After careful consideration,

605
00:26:29,020 --> 00:26:32,078
It should take the initiative to seek out the first nine, the yang line below, to achieve a harmonious union.

606
00:26:32,078 --> 00:26:34,020
Go forth, and it will be auspicious and without disadvantage.

607
00:26:34,020 --> 00:26:37,057
Both the fourth and first lines are positioned at the very bottom of the trigram.

608
00:26:37,057 --> 00:26:41,064
This positional correspondence serves as a reminder for us of the embryonic stage at the very beginning of any venture.

609
00:26:41,064 --> 00:26:43,082
Even when you've already entered the later stages,

610
00:26:43,082 --> 00:26:45,008
We've now reached the fourth line, Six-Four.

611
00:26:45,008 --> 00:26:49,036
The best course of action is still to return to the original intent of the First Nine.

612
00:26:49,036 --> 00:26:51,008
Remember what the first nine was all about?

613
00:26:51,008 --> 00:26:54,010
To hesitate and take root, to be steadfast and establish a foundation.

614
00:26:54,010 --> 00:26:56,072
Keep putting down roots and building your foundation.

615
00:26:56,072 --> 00:26:57,096
and to hone your own skills.

616
00:26:57,096 --> 00:27:01,098
The line from the 'Xiang Zhuan' commentary, 'To seek and then to go is to be enlightened,' is the perfect finishing touch.

617
00:27:01,098 --> 00:27:05,088
This is why the action taken by the fourth six line to seek the first nine line is considered wise.

618
00:27:05,088 --> 00:27:10,042
This is because the hexagram statement for the entire Zhun Hexagram reads: 'Supreme success, perseverance. It is not favorable to go forth. It is favorable to establish feudal lords.'

619
00:27:10,042 --> 00:27:12,046
and it is beneficial to establish a domain.

620
00:27:13,076 --> 00:27:15,074
There are both grand principles and minor principles in all matters.

621
00:27:15,074 --> 00:27:18,036
And all these smaller principles are governed by the greater one.

622
00:27:18,036 --> 00:27:21,016
Always remember that this hexagram, as a whole, is perilous.

623
00:27:21,016 --> 00:27:23,022
This requires caution.

624
00:27:23,022 --> 00:27:24,080
Taking root and establishing a solid foundation is an absolute must.

625
00:27:24,080 --> 00:27:26,026
You must have self-awareness.

626
00:27:26,026 --> 00:27:29,048
The self-awareness in the Zhun hexagram is about recognizing your own weakness.

627
00:27:29,048 --> 00:27:32,090
The outside world is unpredictable; the only safe path is to put down roots.

628
00:27:32,090 --> 00:27:34,018
Striving for the top is perilous.

629
00:27:34,018 --> 00:27:37,054
This holds true even when you reach the next line, the Ninth Five, which represents the position of a ruler.

630
00:27:37,054 --> 00:27:39,030
Even when it's in the right position and well-balanced,

631
00:27:39,030 --> 00:27:42,018
it still can't be considered entirely auspicious.

632
00:27:42,050 --> 00:27:46,070
The fifth nine: 'Amassing its resources. For a small matter, correctness brings good fortune. For a great matter, correctness brings misfortune.'

633
00:27:46,070 --> 00:27:48,099
So, this character '屯' is not pronounced as 'zhūn' here.

634
00:27:48,099 --> 00:27:50,042
It means to hoard or to stockpile.

635
00:27:50,042 --> 00:27:56,006
The line '屯其膏' (tún qí gāo) means that at this point, after putting down deep roots, we have already gathered some resources.

636
00:27:56,006 --> 00:27:57,035
We've built up some resources.

637
00:27:57,035 --> 00:27:59,087
At this point, you can gradually and progressively move forward, but only on the premise of having a solid foundation.

638
00:27:59,087 --> 00:28:03,083
to start taking on some small tasks and experiments.

639
00:28:03,083 --> 00:28:05,026
This is a small but favorable step.

640
00:28:05,026 --> 00:28:07,082
Because you've already gained some experience and have a buffer to fall back on.

641
00:28:07,082 --> 00:28:09,012
Now, you can start experimenting on a small scale.

642
00:28:09,012 --> 00:28:12,026
So, at this stage, any small action you take is auspicious, regardless of whether it succeeds or fails.

643
00:28:12,026 --> 00:28:15,014
Even if these small experiments fail, they are still valuable lessons.

644
00:28:15,014 --> 00:28:17,030
Because the scale is small, we can handle the consequences.

645
00:28:17,030 --> 00:28:19,094
This is also an essential part of moving beyond the initial, budding stage.

646
00:28:19,094 --> 00:28:22,053
But if you go for a massive expansion,

647
00:28:22,053 --> 00:28:24,069
and try to achieve some grand success,

648
00:28:24,069 --> 00:28:26,021
you will inevitably court disaster.

649
00:28:26,021 --> 00:28:28,031
The word 'misfortune' that appears in this line statement,

650
00:28:28,031 --> 00:28:31,015
It represents the worst possible outcome in all of the I Ching's divinations.

651
00:28:31,015 --> 00:28:32,068
You absolutely cannot take this lightly.

652
00:28:32,068 --> 00:28:35,036
The reason why taking major action is doomed to bring disaster is this:

653
00:28:35,036 --> 00:28:37,076
I mean, at this point, you're just a tiny sprout. How much of a foundation could you possibly have?

654
00:28:37,076 --> 00:28:38,084
And...

655
00:28:38,084 --> 00:28:41,094


656
00:28:41,094 --> 00:28:44,027
It's also a reminder of the objective reality of the situation.

657
00:28:44,027 --> 00:28:46,015


658
00:28:46,015 --> 00:28:50,001
but your actions and your strategies still won't lead to a bright future.

659
00:28:50,001 --> 00:28:52,064
Even though the fifth nine is the supreme sovereign line,

660
00:28:52,064 --> 00:28:55,071
you are still bound by the principles of this hexagram.

661
00:28:55,071 --> 00:28:59,055
The Ninth-Five line in the Qian Gua and the Ninth-Five line in the Tun Gua are two completely different concepts.

662
00:28:59,055 --> 00:29:01,090
It's like the difference between a king and a class monitor.

663
00:29:01,090 --> 00:29:04,090
Overall, the Tun hexagram represents the initial stage of sprouting, which is fraught with peril.

664
00:29:04,090 --> 00:29:07,036
So, for these minor situations, you can't really say that a solid line in the ruler's position is always a sign of great fortune.

665
00:29:07,036 --> 00:29:09,023


666
00:29:09,023 --> 00:29:14,048
The fifth nine line of the Zhun hexagram also defines the boundaries of action and the ironclad rules for success or failure in the initial stages of any endeavor.

667
00:29:14,048 --> 00:29:16,072
In the beginning, you must respect the boundaries of that beginning.

668
00:29:16,072 --> 00:29:20,018
We must revere the objective law of the initial hardships all things face at their inception.

669
00:29:20,018 --> 00:29:23,024
Without this reverence, one can never move beyond the Hexagram of Zhun.

670
00:29:23,024 --> 00:29:25,026
Instead, you've reached the dead end of the Zhun hexagram.

671
00:29:25,026 --> 00:29:27,006
We're now at the final line.

672
00:29:27,006 --> 00:29:30,006
Although the top sixth line is a yin line in a yin position, which means it is in its proper place,

673
00:29:30,006 --> 00:29:31,090
However, it is over a firm line, the Nine in the Fifth.

674
00:29:31,090 --> 00:29:34,002
It also loses its centrality, positioned at the very peak of the perilous pit.

675
00:29:34,002 --> 00:29:35,094
And all of this is within the broader framework of the Zhun hexagram.

676
00:29:35,094 --> 00:29:38,006
So, it's doomed to end badly.

677
00:29:38,006 --> 00:29:40,006
It says, "Riding a horse, hesitant and uncertain; weeping tears of blood, in a continuous stream."

678
00:29:40,006 --> 00:29:41,052
This means that

679
00:29:41,052 --> 00:29:43,060
If you insist on acting the moment you get some resources,

680
00:29:43,060 --> 00:29:44,082
and just a little bit of slack,

681
00:29:44,082 --> 00:29:47,026
and go all-in just when you're starting to figure things out,

682
00:29:47,026 --> 00:29:48,078
Then you'll quickly find out

683
00:29:48,078 --> 00:29:53,012
You'll find yourself back at square one, lost and going in circles before you've even taken a few steps.

684
00:29:53,012 --> 00:29:58,032
But the "hesitation on horseback" at this stage is a whole different story compared to the ones in the sixth two and sixth four lines.

685
00:29:58,032 --> 00:30:00,086
When you were hesitating with your horse in the second and fourth lines, you still had some room to maneuver.

686
00:30:00,086 --> 00:30:04,062
But when we get to the top sixth line, it's a real shame.

687
00:30:04,062 --> 00:30:06,094
At this point, going in circles is a sign of extreme grief and regret, so profound it's like weeping tears of blood.

688
00:30:06,094 --> 00:30:11,052
It's not just shedding tears anymore; it's crying blood.

689
00:30:11,052 --> 00:30:13,098
And the word '涟如' (lián rú) describes these tears of blood—they're not just dripping down.

690
00:30:13,098 --> 00:30:16,074
It means they're streaming down, one after another, endlessly.

691
00:30:16,074 --> 00:30:21,008
This line really drives home the sheer depth of your regret after being too greedy and rushing ahead in the Zhun hexagram.

692
00:30:21,008 --> 00:30:23,034
This is actually one of the rarest kinds of hexagrams in the I Ching.

693
00:30:23,034 --> 00:30:25,099
It's an omen of great misfortune with absolutely no room for maneuver!

694
00:30:25,099 --> 00:30:30,057
And this line from the Xiang Zhuan, 'To weep blood, how can this last?' is like twisting the knife.

695
00:30:30,057 --> 00:30:32,026
You're already weeping tears of blood.

696
00:30:32,026 --> 00:30:34,042
Don't be fooled just because you're still on your horse,徘徊着.

697
00:30:34,042 --> 00:30:36,046
But soon enough, you won't even have that horse anymore.

698
00:30:36,046 --> 00:30:38,025
You're about to hit a dead end.

699
00:30:38,025 --> 00:30:43,049
Doesn't that sound like what happens after you've scrimped and saved for ten years, only to pour it all into some... you-know-what?

700
00:30:43,049 --> 00:30:45,083
Doesn't that sound like right after you've finally started to get somewhere,

701
00:30:45,083 --> 00:30:48,053
You take out loans to massively hire people, bring in new equipment to scale up production, and then...

702
00:30:48,053 --> 00:30:50,059
and then the orders suddenly just stop coming in?

703
00:30:50,059 --> 00:30:52,081
Isn't the wisdom of our ancestors just incredible?

704
00:30:52,081 --> 00:30:56,054
So, the question is, can wisdom from thousands of years ago still be applied today?

705
00:30:56,054 --> 00:30:57,030
So, for this hexagram,

706
00:30:57,030 --> 00:30:59,086
Finally, let's revisit the profound meaning of the entire Hexagram of Zhun.

707
00:30:59,086 --> 00:31:02,099
Supreme success. Perseverance furthers. Do not act. It furthers one to build up feudal lords.

708
00:31:02,099 --> 00:31:05,073
Step one: focus on building a solid foundation and learning real skills.

709
00:31:05,073 --> 00:31:08,023
Study past failures to identify the major pitfalls in your industry.

710
00:31:08,023 --> 00:31:10,066
Step two: Don't get caught up in internal struggles, and don't be tempted by distractions.

711
00:31:10,066 --> 00:31:12,074
Ground yourself and repeat the first step.

712
00:31:12,074 --> 00:31:14,048
Step two: don't make any rash moves.

713
00:31:14,048 --> 00:31:18,026
Even if you achieve some small success in the first step, you must still test the waters with small-scale actions.

714
00:31:18,026 --> 00:31:20,006
Any major move is a death sentence.

715
00:31:22,084 --> 00:31:24,024
So, what's the next step?

716
00:31:24,024 --> 00:31:25,032
It is education.

717
00:31:25,032 --> 00:31:29,026
It's about helping all things, in their earliest stages of growth, to understand the fundamental laws of how things develop.

718
00:31:29,026 --> 00:31:31,076
to understand the fundamental laws of heaven and earth.

719
00:31:31,076 --> 00:31:33,048
And this brings us to the Hexagram of Meng.

720
00:31:33,048 --> 00:31:36,044
Let's take a look at the fundamental principles in the process of education and learning.

721
00:31:36,044 --> 00:31:39,032
Aren't you always getting frustrated that you just can't seem to raise this kid right?!

722
00:31:39,032 --> 00:31:40,036
And aren't you always wondering why you can never stick with anything you try to learn?

723
00:31:40,036 --> 00:31:42,002
and why you never seem to get anywhere with your own studies.

724
00:31:42,002 --> 00:31:43,067
And you just can't seem to get the hang of anything, right?

725
00:31:43,067 --> 00:31:46,097
Well, come on! Our ancestors have already summed it all up for us!

726
00:31:47,021 --> 00:31:50,028
Everything that has just sprouted, all newborn things, are completely in the dark.

727
00:31:50,028 --> 00:31:51,049
They know absolutely nothing.

728
00:31:51,049 --> 00:31:54,007
We usually call this state of being 'ignorance' or 'obscurity'.

729
00:31:54,007 --> 00:31:55,083
Regarding this concept of 'Meng' (Ignorance), as recorded in the 'Shuowen Jiezi'...

730
00:31:55,083 --> 00:31:57,015
“Meng, the royal maiden.”

731
00:31:57,015 --> 00:31:59,023
Now, this 'wang nu' doesn't mean 'princess,' by the way.

732
00:31:59,023 --> 00:32:00,043
It refers to dodder.

733
00:32:00,043 --> 00:32:02,083
This thing works by wrapping itself around a host plant,

734
00:32:02,083 --> 00:32:05,011
piercing the host's epidermis to absorb nutrients.

735
00:32:05,011 --> 00:32:07,037
So, in the vast majority of ancient texts,

736
00:32:07,037 --> 00:32:10,064
Originally, the character "Meng" meant to be covered or obscured.

737
00:32:10,064 --> 00:32:13,030
And because it's covered up, we can't see clearly.

738
00:32:13,030 --> 00:32:16,030
And so, the character 'Meng' also came to mean 'to be deceived' or 'to be blinded'.

739
00:32:16,030 --> 00:32:19,006
And because people who are deceived also have their judgment impaired,

740
00:32:19,006 --> 00:32:21,094
And so, the character 'Meng' also came to mean the 'ignorance' or 'naivety' we just talked about.

741
00:32:21,094 --> 00:32:23,024
But when it comes to the character 'Meng'...

742
00:32:23,024 --> 00:32:25,042
But our ancestors didn't mean this in a derogatory way at all.

743
00:32:25,042 --> 00:32:28,044
"Meng" is an inevitable stage at the very beginning of any development.

744
00:32:28,044 --> 00:32:30,038
This is what the 'Sequence of the Hexagrams' says:

745
00:32:30,038 --> 00:32:33,016
“All things that are born must be in a state of obscurity. Therefore, it is followed by Meng.”

746
00:32:33,016 --> 00:32:34,034
Meng means to be in a state of ignorance; it is the infancy of all things.

747
00:32:34,034 --> 00:32:38,028
It means being tender, being young, being a child.

748
00:32:38,028 --> 00:32:40,052
The Meng Hexagram is Gen above, and Kan below.

749
00:32:40,052 --> 00:32:42,016
Gen represents the mountain, which means to stop. Kan represents water, which means danger.

750
00:32:42,016 --> 00:32:43,076
Kan represents water, and water represents danger.

751
00:32:43,076 --> 00:32:45,078
The lower trigram begins with the peril of Kan.

752
00:32:45,078 --> 00:32:46,006
Danger.

753
00:32:46,006 --> 00:32:48,052
This tells us to be careful.

754
00:32:48,052 --> 00:32:51,008
After passing through the lower trigram, we reach the upper trigram, which is another mountain.

755
00:32:51,008 --> 00:32:52,090
telling us to stop.

756
00:32:52,090 --> 00:32:55,086
The Tuan Zhuan states, "Beneath the mountain lies danger, and one halts in the face of danger."

757
00:32:55,086 --> 00:32:58,064
Beneath the mountain, danger is lurking.

758
00:32:58,064 --> 00:33:00,056
This describes a path forward that's blocked by danger.

759
00:33:00,056 --> 00:33:02,056
This state of obscured peril, hidden by the mountain,

760
00:33:02,056 --> 00:33:04,016
It's a state of being like a child, knowing nothing at all.

761
00:33:04,016 --> 00:33:06,006
When the path ahead is unclear and your understanding is limited,

762
00:33:06,006 --> 00:33:10,018
Just how terrifying is this world for us, fresh out of the tutorial?

763
00:33:10,018 --> 00:33:11,032
So, what does this mean?

764
00:33:11,032 --> 00:33:15,011
This calls for education that disciplines children and prunes young trees.

765
00:33:15,011 --> 00:33:17,013
Failing to educate them is doing them a great disservice.

766
00:33:17,013 --> 00:33:18,087
In other words, to initiate their education.

767
00:33:18,087 --> 00:33:21,001
Alright, let's take a look at the judgment for this hexagram.

768
00:33:21,001 --> 00:33:23,001
It is prosperous. It is not I who seek the childlike, but the childlike who seeks me.

769
00:33:23,001 --> 00:33:24,053
Things go wrong.

770
00:33:24,053 --> 00:33:25,043
For the first divination, it gives an answer. But if you ask again and again, it will not answer, for it is treated with disrespect.

771
00:33:25,043 --> 00:33:27,066
Favorable to be steadfast.

772
00:33:27,066 --> 00:33:31,048
First, let's pay attention. The hexagram statement contains the words 'heng' (prosperity), 'li' (benefit), and 'zhen' (steadfastness).

773
00:33:31,048 --> 00:33:32,099
But the 'Yuan' is missing.

774
00:33:32,099 --> 00:33:34,050
This tells us that...

775
00:33:34,050 --> 00:33:36,034
When it comes to education and enlightenment,

776
00:33:36,034 --> 00:33:38,074
It's not something we are inherently and automatically entitled to the moment we are born.

777
00:33:38,074 --> 00:33:42,067
Education and wisdom are luxuries.

778
00:33:42,067 --> 00:33:45,047
Not everyone gets the chance or is even qualified to obtain it.

779
00:33:45,047 --> 00:33:48,088
That's why we must cherish the opportunity to 'seek knowledge'.

780
00:33:48,088 --> 00:33:50,074
亨。匪我求童蒙，童蒙求我。

781
00:33:50,074 --> 00:33:53,056
The essence of enlightenment is 'smooth progress'.

782
00:33:53,056 --> 00:33:56,005
It's about helping the audience see through the fog.

783
00:33:56,005 --> 00:33:59,035
to ensure your heart and your path can flow with clarity and ease.

784
00:33:59,035 --> 00:34:00,095
Now, there's one point we need to emphasize here.

785
00:34:00,095 --> 00:34:05,025
The concept of 'Heng', or smooth progress, is actually something that's highly customized and varies from person to person.

786
00:34:05,025 --> 00:34:07,003
This is the path for those with Jia and Yi Wood elements.

787
00:34:07,003 --> 00:34:09,022
it might not be the right path for those with Bing or Ding.

788
00:34:09,022 --> 00:34:11,074
People with strong 'Shi Shang' and those with heavy 'Guan Sha'

789
00:34:11,074 --> 00:34:14,018
These represent two completely different life strategies.

790
00:34:14,018 --> 00:34:17,027
It would be like asking Liu Bang to be Xiao He; you're just setting him up to fail.

791
00:34:17,027 --> 00:34:19,061
He just loved to piss on the hats of Confucian scholars.

792
00:34:19,061 --> 00:34:20,079
or forcing his son-in-law to do the splits and flash his junk.

793
00:34:20,079 --> 00:34:22,015
or splitting open his opponent's crotch.

794
00:34:22,015 --> 00:34:25,064
You'd have Xiao He hold the line at Xingyang and Chenggao against Xiang Yu's bombardment,

795
00:34:25,064 --> 00:34:28,060
But if you let the theorists like Zhang Liang and Chen Ping

796
00:34:28,060 --> 00:34:29,096
to command those old, tough founding fathers.

797
00:34:29,096 --> 00:34:31,052
And they just don't have that kind of authority to command respect.

798
00:34:31,052 --> 00:34:34,032
This kind of job calls for someone with that special 'He Wanqian' quality.

799
00:34:34,032 --> 00:34:35,067
Only a protagonist with the right temperament can pull it off.

800
00:34:35,067 --> 00:34:37,019
So, when it comes to启蒙 (enlightenment), it all starts from the very beginning.

801
00:34:37,019 --> 00:34:40,081
This is why we have to emphasize tailoring the teaching to the individual.

802
00:34:40,081 --> 00:34:43,089
There's no single formula that can be applied to everyone.

803
00:34:43,089 --> 00:34:45,052
And this goes back to what we said at the very beginning.

804
00:34:45,052 --> 00:34:47,038
The Meng Hexagram does not have the 'Yuan' quality.

805
00:34:47,038 --> 00:34:50,062
Nor does it mean that every single child needs to be educated.

806
00:34:50,062 --> 00:34:52,043
that they are all destined to receive an education.

807
00:34:52,043 --> 00:34:57,031
From the very beginning, the Meng Hexagram serves as a reminder for all those who are teachers, or who are eager to teach others.

808
00:34:57,031 --> 00:34:59,061
You don't have to force the issue of school on your kids.

809
00:34:59,061 --> 00:35:02,099
And it's not a given that you'll be able to get through to them.

810
00:35:02,099 --> 00:35:06,041
The purpose of studying the I Ching is to help us understand the Way of Heaven.

811
00:35:06,041 --> 00:35:08,019
and realize that not everyone can be educated.

812
00:35:08,019 --> 00:35:10,065
is to know that true wisdom is costly.

813
00:35:10,065 --> 00:35:11,049
It is a solemn matter.

814
00:35:11,049 --> 00:35:14,065
and that it must be treated with reverence. This is the very prerequisite for true enlightenment.

815
00:35:14,065 --> 00:35:18,093
“Difficult! Difficult! Difficult!”
The Tao is the most profound mystery.
Do not treat the Golden Elixir as a trivial matter.

816
00:35:18,093 --> 00:35:22,015
Without a true master to impart the secret, all your empty words will just wear out your tongue and leave you dry!

817
00:35:22,015 --> 00:35:23,092
Let's go over that one more time.

818
00:35:23,092 --> 00:35:26,060
Understand that not everyone can be taught.

819
00:35:26,060 --> 00:35:29,052
To understand that true knowledge is a precious and solemn thing...

820
00:35:29,052 --> 00:35:32,065
and that it must be treated with reverence. This is the prerequisite for true enlightenment.

821
00:35:32,065 --> 00:35:36,028
The moment you truly grasp this, your whole world will suddenly expand.

822
00:35:36,028 --> 00:35:40,065
Some kids, or even most of them, actually just don't have what it takes.

823
00:35:40,065 --> 00:35:46,019
And it's even more unnecessary to forcibly interfere with other people's karma. If they have the right stuff, they'll have that blessing.

824
00:35:46,019 --> 00:35:50,057
They would naturally cross two vast oceans to seek the Way.

825
00:35:50,057 --> 00:35:52,022
So naturally, no matter how you try to tempt them,

826
00:35:52,022 --> 00:35:54,057
One moment it's the principle of stillness, the next it's the principle of action.

827
00:35:54,057 --> 00:35:57,033
He remained steadfast in his pursuit of immortality.

828
00:35:57,033 --> 00:35:58,067
It's like, even if you hit him, he'd probably think you're just telling him the time.

829
00:35:58,067 --> 00:36:00,069
He'd even think you're just giving him a massage.

830
00:36:00,069 --> 00:36:05,082
The teachers, the ones who impart wisdom, are the ones who test you from beginning to end.

831
00:36:05,082 --> 00:36:09,034
We shouldn't be the one to rush things. That's not how the natural order works.

832
00:36:09,034 --> 00:36:10,040
“It is not I who seek the naive, but the naive who seek me.”

833
00:36:10,040 --> 00:36:12,052
The unenlightened seek me, this 'un' is not 'together' or 'same'.

834
00:36:12,052 --> 00:36:14,094
This echoes the line from the second six line of the previous hexagram, 'Halted, entangled, riding in a team of horses.'

835
00:36:14,094 --> 00:36:15,096
as if they were bandits.

836
00:36:15,096 --> 00:36:17,024
The word '匪' (fěi) in the line '匪寇婚媾女子貞不字十年乃字' (fěi kòu hūn gòu, nǚ zǐ zhēn bù zì, shí nián nǎi zì)

837
00:36:17,024 --> 00:36:17,084
and after ten years, she finally bears a child.

838
00:36:17,084 --> 00:36:18,098
So, the character 'fei' here has the same meaning.

839
00:36:18,098 --> 00:36:20,034
So, what this means is...

840
00:36:20,034 --> 00:36:24,066
It's not about the teacher rushing after the students, begging them to come and learn from them.

841
00:36:24,066 --> 00:36:27,094
It's the children who must come to the teacher, sincerely seeking knowledge.

842
00:36:27,094 --> 00:36:29,041
This is the prerequisite for education.

843
00:36:29,041 --> 00:36:32,095
The student's initiative is the prerequisite for any education to be effective.

844
00:36:32,095 --> 00:36:35,019
no matter how high our level of启蒙 (qǐméng) is,

845
00:36:35,019 --> 00:36:38,033
But if the person being taught has no desire to learn at all,

846
00:36:38,033 --> 00:36:40,051
That would be treating the Golden Elixir as something trivial.

847
00:36:40,051 --> 00:36:42,063
The Tuan Zhuan, or the Commentary on the Decision, provides the following commentary on this passage.

848
00:36:42,063 --> 00:36:44,063
Meng is prosperous. By acting in accordance with the time, one attains centrality.

849
00:36:44,063 --> 00:36:46,045
It is not I who seek the young and ignorant; it is the young and ignorant who seek me. This is because our wills are in accord.

850
00:36:46,045 --> 00:36:47,061
The student seeks me out, and our wills align.

851
00:36:47,061 --> 00:36:50,089
“To act by offering” means to act in accordance with the momentum.

852
00:36:50,089 --> 00:36:52,085
To be 'timely and centered' means avoiding extremes and not forcing things.

853
00:36:52,085 --> 00:36:54,056
and not to force-feed knowledge.

854
00:36:54,056 --> 00:36:57,075
“Zhi Ying” means having a shared purpose, being on the same wavelength as your teacher.

855
00:36:57,075 --> 00:37:01,081
For those who are just starting out, we must teach them according to their aptitude and go with the flow.

856
00:37:01,081 --> 00:37:03,067
This kid just isn't cut out for it.

857
00:37:03,067 --> 00:37:06,075
Then don't force it. But what if the kid is talented, but right now, all they can think about is having fun?

858
00:37:06,075 --> 00:37:08,033
but all they can think about is having fun,

859
00:37:08,033 --> 00:37:10,094
and they don't even respect you, then just leave them be.

860
00:37:10,094 --> 00:37:14,064
But what if the kid isn't naturally gifted, yet their heart is completely in it?

861
00:37:14,064 --> 00:37:17,080
Then teach them the basic principles for living a stable and grounded life.

862
00:37:17,080 --> 00:37:21,050
The guiding principle of an educator is to teach according to the student's aptitude and to discern the right moment.

863
00:37:21,050 --> 00:37:22,062
Teach when it's time to teach.

864
00:37:22,062 --> 00:37:23,064
and hold back when necessary.

865
00:37:23,064 --> 00:37:25,018
When you come across a devout student,

866
00:37:25,018 --> 00:37:26,048
regardless of their aptitude,

867
00:37:26,048 --> 00:37:29,065
One must sincerely impart the knowledge and skills that are right for them.

868
00:37:29,065 --> 00:37:31,069
But at best, we're just the coaches.

869
00:37:31,069 --> 00:37:34,042
But when it's game time, the athletes have to be the ones on the field.

870
00:37:34,042 --> 00:37:36,082
We neither understep nor overstep our bounds.

871
00:37:36,082 --> 00:37:38,048
The principles have been explained, and the knowledge has been taught.

872
00:37:38,048 --> 00:37:41,028
If you run into any problems, you can come to me for advice.

873
00:37:41,028 --> 00:37:42,039
and I can offer you some guidance.

874
00:37:42,039 --> 00:37:46,011
But, I'm sorry to say, when it comes to your own life, you have to walk that path by yourself.

875
00:37:46,011 --> 00:37:49,007
For those who seek to learn, there's one crucial mindset you must always remember.

876
00:37:49,007 --> 00:37:50,085
Let go of our arrogance.

877
00:37:50,085 --> 00:37:53,013
If you're going to ask for guidance, you should act like it.

878
00:37:53,013 --> 00:37:54,033
Once we've acquired knowledge and wisdom,

879
00:37:54,033 --> 00:37:56,079
is what can change our destiny.

880
00:37:56,079 --> 00:37:59,064
Therefore, you must develop a genuine sense of respect for your mentor from the bottom of your heart.

881
00:37:59,064 --> 00:38:02,062
At the same time, it's not just the mentor who matters; the student is just as important.

882
00:38:02,062 --> 00:38:04,064
must also observe the principle of 'acting with sincerity'.

883
00:38:04,064 --> 00:38:07,088
So, you need to go with the flow and build a connection with your mentor.

884
00:38:07,088 --> 00:38:10,064
The energy and time of highly accomplished people are incredibly precious.

885
00:38:10,064 --> 00:38:12,053
So, what's in it for them to teach you?

886
00:38:12,053 --> 00:38:15,025
Why on earth would they just hand over the secrets they've spent decades of blood, sweat, and tears figuring out?

887
00:38:15,025 --> 00:38:16,062
and reveal all their secrets to you?

888
00:38:16,062 --> 00:38:18,026
We should learn from the Monkey King.

889
00:38:18,026 --> 00:38:20,064
He traveled across two great oceans in search of his own scriptures.

890
00:38:20,064 --> 00:38:27,070
It would take him six or seven years, alongside his fellow disciples, to learn the proper etiquette, discuss scriptures and doctrines, practice calligraphy, and burn incense. This was his daily routine.

891
00:38:27,070 --> 00:38:31,040
In his spare time, he would sweep the floors, tend to the garden, care for the flowers and trees, and gather firewood to light the fires.

892
00:38:31,040 --> 00:38:32,080
Only after carrying water and hauling mortar could he finally await his chance.

893
00:38:32,080 --> 00:38:38,063
the opportunity for the Patriarch to ascend the dais, summon all the immortals, and expound upon the Great Dao.

894
00:38:38,063 --> 00:38:40,037
Only through sufficient hardship and unwavering sincerity,

895
00:38:40,037 --> 00:38:41,061
and enough sincerity,

896
00:38:41,061 --> 00:38:44,004
Only then can you truly understand what it is you want.

897
00:38:44,004 --> 00:38:46,072
Only then can you face the various interferences from the 'Masters,' such as the 'School of Technique,' the 'School of Stillness,' and the 'School of Action.'

898
00:38:46,072 --> 00:38:47,040
the Mirror Gate,

899
00:38:47,040 --> 00:38:48,046
and the distractions from the 'Action' school.

900
00:38:48,046 --> 00:38:49,072
He still refused to learn.

901
00:38:49,072 --> 00:38:51,012
I want to learn the art of immortality.

902
00:38:51,012 --> 00:38:54,026
This was the 'secret signal'—the Patriarch striking him three times.

903
00:38:54,026 --> 00:38:56,026
And then, he finally unraveled the mystery of the plate.

904
00:38:56,026 --> 00:38:57,080
As we've mentioned when discussing 'Journey to the West'...

905
00:38:57,080 --> 00:38:59,096
In the beginning, Monkey King was actually the most polite monkey in the world.

906
00:38:59,096 --> 00:39:01,086
He was practically exuding an aura of Buddhist wisdom.

907
00:39:01,086 --> 00:39:05,044
It was only in this state of mind that he was able to master the Great Pinnacle Heavenly Immortal Art.

908
00:39:05,044 --> 00:39:09,042
So, once he got his skills down and started running his mouth all the time, did he get any better?

909
00:39:09,042 --> 00:39:12,069
Not at all! He was already getting stewed in a pot.

910
00:39:12,069 --> 00:39:14,065
And he still dared to mess with the Buddha!

911
00:39:14,065 --> 00:39:17,085
It wasn't until he was crushed under that mountain for 500 years that he learned there's always someone better out there.

912
00:39:17,085 --> 00:39:21,008
Only when the Golden Fillet was placed on his head, could his very life and death be controlled at another's whim.

913
00:39:21,008 --> 00:39:23,050
It wasn't until he was cast out by Tang Sanzang at White Tiger Ridge and lost his chance to change his fate,

914
00:39:23,050 --> 00:39:25,010
and lost his chance to change his fate,

915
00:39:25,010 --> 00:39:28,020
Only then did he gradually let go of his arrogance and develop a sincere heart.

916
00:39:28,020 --> 00:39:31,046
Only then did his wisdom regain the high ground.

917
00:39:31,046 --> 00:39:32,056
Only by persevering to the end could he truly complete the latter half of his pilgrimage.

918
00:39:32,056 --> 00:39:35,082
and turned it into his own path of spiritual cultivation.

919
00:39:35,082 --> 00:39:40,026
All of Monkey King's upgrades on his path to enlightenment were rooted in his sense of reverence.

920
00:39:40,026 --> 00:39:43,014
and only initiated after securing a strategic high ground once again.

921
00:39:43,014 --> 00:39:46,048
The first divination gives an answer. If you ask again and again, it is disrespectful and will not be answered. It is beneficial to be steadfast.

922
00:39:46,076 --> 00:39:50,079
Here, 'divination' refers to the practice of fortune-telling. When you sincerely consult the oracle for the first time,

923
00:39:50,079 --> 00:39:52,039
the divination should如实 reveal the result.

924
00:39:52,039 --> 00:39:54,021
But if you ask over and over again,

925
00:39:54,021 --> 00:39:56,019
and won't stop until they get the answer they want,

926
00:39:56,019 --> 00:39:58,033
Or, even after you've given them the answer, they refuse to believe it.

927
00:39:58,033 --> 00:39:59,075
That is a sign of disrespect.

928
00:39:59,075 --> 00:40:03,011
This is a blasphemy against the divine. And once blasphemed, no more will be revealed.

929
00:40:03,011 --> 00:40:05,017
Here, the rules of divination are used as a metaphor for the boundaries of education.

930
00:40:05,017 --> 00:40:09,040
This is when a seeker first earnestly asks for guidance,

931
00:40:09,040 --> 00:40:10,054
And pay attention here: it must be sincere.

932
00:40:10,054 --> 00:40:12,082
The mentor should impart true knowledge as it is.

933
00:40:12,082 --> 00:40:16,030
At this point, the learner should take the teaching to heart and reflect on it deeply.

934
00:40:16,030 --> 00:40:19,000
Practice it repeatedly until it becomes second nature, integrated into your own operating system.

935
00:40:19,000 --> 00:40:23,013
If someone asks the same question, or questions about the same kind of matter, over and over again,

936
00:40:23,013 --> 00:40:24,019
he doesn't reflect on it,

937
00:40:24,019 --> 00:40:26,033
This would be a sign of disrespect and contempt.

938
00:40:26,033 --> 00:40:28,021
then the teacher should not tell them.

939
00:40:28,021 --> 00:40:30,056
So, the key here is 'sincerity', alright?

940
00:40:30,056 --> 00:40:32,066
It's not like you just answer every random question that comes along, you know?

941
00:40:32,066 --> 00:40:35,022
It was the Monkey King who proved his sincerity.

942
00:40:35,022 --> 00:40:37,008
He's already come at the third watch of the night.

943
00:40:37,008 --> 00:40:39,098
The Patriarch should now teach him the Great Pinnacle Heavenly Immortal Art.

944
00:40:39,098 --> 00:40:42,018
And it's not like the guy wasn't sincere enough.

945
00:40:42,018 --> 00:40:45,080
He's already solved the riddle of the plate, going to all this trouble to come at the third watch of the night.

946
00:40:45,080 --> 00:40:47,083
And then you just come back with a bunch of empty words.

947
00:40:47,083 --> 00:40:49,015
This principle of 'disrespect brings no answer' is not about the teacher being cold or giving up.

948
00:40:49,015 --> 00:40:52,099
It's not that they're not giving you a chance,

949
00:40:52,099 --> 00:40:56,011
Because the true knowledge was already given to you from the very beginning.

950
00:40:56,011 --> 00:40:58,003
It's not that the teacher isn't dedicated.

951
00:40:58,003 --> 00:41:00,031
The problem is you didn't take it seriously.

952
00:41:00,031 --> 00:41:01,043
So, you might be wondering, what if the student is just plain dumb?

953
00:41:01,043 --> 00:41:03,038
So, what if the student is just hopelessly stupid?

954
00:41:03,038 --> 00:41:06,086
As we mentioned earlier, the Meng Hexagram lacks the 'Yuan' quality.

955
00:41:06,086 --> 00:41:09,064
It was never meant for everyone to attain enlightenment in the first place.

956
00:41:09,064 --> 00:41:12,024
But what if you've explained it clearly, and they still don't get it?

957
00:41:12,024 --> 00:41:16,060
That just means the time isn't right yet. You need to let it simmer for a while longer, wait for the moment to be ripe.

958
00:41:16,060 --> 00:41:18,060
So, if it's not a matter of the student being stupid,

959
00:41:18,060 --> 00:41:20,024
Then it's a matter of mindset.

960
00:41:20,024 --> 00:41:22,024
Or, they don't take the teacher seriously.

961
00:41:22,024 --> 00:41:23,074
or they take the Golden Elixir for granted.

962
00:41:23,074 --> 00:41:25,086
Or, they take themselves way too seriously.

963
00:41:25,086 --> 00:41:28,064
Their minds are so full of their own ideas and obsessions that there's no room for anything else.

964
00:41:28,064 --> 00:41:31,044
This is something the learner must reflect on for themselves.

965
00:41:31,044 --> 00:41:33,016
If he's just not cut out for it, and you keep trying to teach him over and over again,

966
00:41:33,016 --> 00:41:35,070
they'll just get rebellious.

967
00:41:35,070 --> 00:41:38,048
If they don't take you seriously, but you keep trying to teach them,

968
00:41:38,048 --> 00:41:40,033
On one hand, you're letting down the masters who came before you.

969
00:41:40,033 --> 00:41:43,009
Heaven, Earth, and even the spirits will see that you have failed to uphold the dignity of a teacher!

970
00:41:43,009 --> 00:41:46,002
On the other hand, you're actually ruining him and doing him harm.

971
00:41:46,002 --> 00:41:48,073
and encourage his disrespectful and impetuous tendencies.

972
00:41:48,073 --> 00:41:51,035
The Commentary on the Decision, or Tuan Zhuan, explains this line as: 'The first divination gives an answer.'

973
00:41:51,035 --> 00:41:52,093
Because they possess the virtue of firmness and centrality.

974
00:41:52,093 --> 00:41:56,015
If you ask a second time, it shows disrespect. And if you disrespect it, you will not be answered. This is what it means to abuse the spirit of seeking guidance.

975
00:41:56,015 --> 00:41:59,085
The reason you should sincerely answer someone who sincerely seeks your guidance for the first time,

976
00:41:59,085 --> 00:42:02,047
This is because the teacher embodies the virtue of being 'firm and centered'.

977
00:42:02,047 --> 00:42:04,033
The second line of this hexagram is a solid, or yang, line.

978
00:42:04,033 --> 00:42:06,008
The second line, Nine, is a firm line in a central position.

979
00:42:06,008 --> 00:42:09,000
This means that, on one hand, the educator must have a firm, unyielding principle.

980
00:42:09,000 --> 00:42:12,088
and on the other hand, they must have a sincere heart of integrity and peace to educate others with the Way.

981
00:42:12,088 --> 00:42:14,069
This is what it means to be a qualified guide for the unenlightened.

982
00:42:14,069 --> 00:42:17,061
“If you repeatedly show disrespect, I will not answer. This is what it means to disrespect the unenlightened.”

983
00:42:17,061 --> 00:42:21,086
In fact, this means that the ignorant are not just disrespecting their teachers and true knowledge.

984
00:42:21,086 --> 00:42:24,076
but more so, with distracting thoughts of utilitarianism, arrogance, and impetuousness.

985
00:42:24,076 --> 00:42:26,030
but are also desecrating their own innermost being.

986
00:42:26,030 --> 00:42:28,036
and has shut the door to enlightenment.

987
00:42:28,036 --> 00:42:30,057
He has even failed himself.

988
00:42:30,057 --> 00:42:34,030
At this point, the problem lies with the one seeking guidance, not with the one imparting it.

989
00:42:34,030 --> 00:42:37,080
The teacher's refusal to answer is meant to prompt the student to reflect on their own shortcomings.

990
00:42:37,080 --> 00:42:39,024
First, find your true self.

991
00:42:39,024 --> 00:42:42,027
First, know your place, then we can talk about enlightenment.

992
00:42:42,027 --> 00:42:43,043
“If you show disrespect, you will not be told.”

993
00:42:43,043 --> 00:42:45,095
It is the 'teaching without words' of the Great Way.

994
00:42:45,095 --> 00:42:49,004
So, do you understand the principle behind why you shouldn't be so eager to lecture others?

995
00:42:49,004 --> 00:42:52,048
After all these years, I believe we've all learned to keep our mouths shut.

996
00:42:52,048 --> 00:42:54,006
We've learned not to interfere with the law of cause and effect.

997
00:42:54,006 --> 00:42:57,028
But in fact, our ancestors had already summed it all up for us long ago.

998
00:42:57,028 --> 00:42:59,088
Of course, for those who haven't been through the wringer,

999
00:42:59,088 --> 00:43:03,040
Even if they see this, they won't truly grasp its meaning.

1000
00:43:03,040 --> 00:43:04,070
and they won't take it seriously.

1001
00:43:04,070 --> 00:43:06,076
But when you do take a fall,

1002
00:43:06,076 --> 00:43:08,064
Only when reality connects with the theory,

1003
00:43:08,064 --> 00:43:11,087
That's when this principle will be truly etched into your very being.

1004
00:43:11,087 --> 00:43:13,079
This is, in fact, a reflection of the principle: 'It is not I who seek the ignorant child, but the ignorant child who seeks me.'

1005
00:43:13,079 --> 00:43:15,039
This is the manifestation of 'the student seeking the teacher.'

1006
00:43:15,039 --> 00:43:16,096
The Great Way is right there.

1007
00:43:16,096 --> 00:43:19,090
Once you've sailed through a thousand ports and realized that the greatest truths are the simplest,

1008
00:43:19,090 --> 00:43:22,070
The time has come to revere the wisdom of our ancestors.

1009
00:43:22,070 --> 00:43:24,078
Only then can you truly begin to level up.

1010
00:43:24,078 --> 00:43:26,068
The last two characters of the Judgment for the Meng Hexagram are "li zhen".

1011
00:43:26,068 --> 00:43:29,033
This reiterates the foundation of the Meng Hexagram.

1012
00:43:29,033 --> 00:43:32,079
The word 'beneficial' implies that for both the teacher and the learner,

1013
00:43:32,079 --> 00:43:35,013
Both parties should gain their fair and reasonable benefits.

1014
00:43:35,013 --> 00:43:37,084
The true knowledge and skills imparted by the teacher

1015
00:43:37,084 --> 00:43:41,018
must be something that empowers the learner to stand on their own two feet for the rest of their life.

1016
00:43:41,018 --> 00:43:43,048
Otherwise, you're just leading them astray!

1017
00:43:43,048 --> 00:43:48,097
This carries great karmic weight! And the one seeking guidance must also prepare the solemn "Six Rites of Shuxiu" for the teacher.

1018
00:43:48,097 --> 00:43:51,017
to express your sincerity and righteous intentions.

1019
00:43:51,017 --> 00:43:53,065
All that empty talk and flashy stuff won't get you anywhere.

1020
00:43:53,065 --> 00:43:55,069
The world has always been a pragmatic place, since ancient times.

1021
00:43:55,069 --> 00:43:57,049
This was especially true in ancient times.

1022
00:43:57,049 --> 00:44:00,085
You only cherish what you've earned through effort.

1023
00:44:00,085 --> 00:44:04,096
The character 'Zhēn' signifies that the core of all teaching and learning revolves around the right path.

1024
00:44:04,096 --> 00:44:08,028
The fundamental purpose of education is to guide the learner onto the right path.

1025
00:44:08,028 --> 00:44:11,076
This is exactly what the Tuan Zhuan says: "To nourish the young with correctness is the work of the sages."

1026
00:44:11,076 --> 00:44:16,005
Tailoring education to individual aptitude means providing positive guidance for each person.

1027
00:44:16,005 --> 00:44:19,007
and to empower them to have a positive impact on the world.

1028
00:44:19,007 --> 00:44:22,007
The most fundamental purpose of education has never been the mere imparting of knowledge.

1029
00:44:22,007 --> 00:44:23,047
but the cultivation of virtue.

1030
00:44:23,047 --> 00:44:24,095
That's what the Sweeper Monk said.

1031
00:44:24,095 --> 00:44:27,022
The greater one's martial arts prowess, the greater the destructive energy it can unleash.

1032
00:44:27,022 --> 00:44:29,078
the more it needs the compassionate Dharma to neutralize it.

1033
00:44:29,078 --> 00:44:32,028
Regardless of whether this child succeeds in their studies or not,

1034
00:44:32,028 --> 00:44:33,069
regardless of their abilities,

1035
00:44:33,069 --> 00:44:36,013
At the very least, after this child has received their early education,

1036
00:44:36,013 --> 00:44:38,054
he or she should at least be a person who is not a harm to society.

1037
00:44:38,054 --> 00:44:41,018
For those who are immoral and violent, the first step is to cultivate their character.

1038
00:44:44,014 --> 00:44:46,064
Otherwise, you'd just be irresponsible to society!

1039
00:44:46,064 --> 00:44:49,074
This is precisely the summary of the entire hexagram found in the 'Great Image Commentary'.

1040
00:44:49,074 --> 00:44:51,096
Meng: A spring emerging from beneath a mountain.

1041
00:44:51,096 --> 00:44:54,034
A noble person cultivates virtue through resolute action.

1042
00:44:55,030 --> 00:45:00,040
Let's look at the line statement for the first six, "To initiate the unenlightened, it is beneficial to use the punished to break the shackles."

1043
00:45:00,040 --> 00:45:05,012
This means that the starting point of enlightenment is to establish rules, clarify boundaries, and rectify discipline.

1044
00:45:05,012 --> 00:45:06,092
In the Meng Hexagram, the first six is a yin line in a yang position, which is considered out of place.

1045
00:45:06,092 --> 00:45:08,026
This means it is in a yang position, but it is not a proper fit.

1046
00:45:08,026 --> 00:45:10,033
The soft and yielding is in the lowest position, representing the utmost ignorance.

1047
00:45:10,033 --> 00:45:13,001
Therefore, at this stage, this state of 'Meng' needs to be 'initiated' or 'enlightened'.

1048
00:45:13,001 --> 00:45:15,021
This requires help from an external force.

1049
00:45:15,021 --> 00:45:18,007
You can't count on some kind of spontaneous, natural awakening.

1050
00:45:18,007 --> 00:45:19,079
It requires external guidance.

1051
00:45:19,079 --> 00:45:20,089
Now, the word 'xing' in the phrase 'utilizing punitive measures'...

1052
00:45:20,089 --> 00:45:25,027
Now, this doesn't mean just meting out punishment or corporal punishment, okay?

1053
00:45:25,027 --> 00:45:28,027
Instead, it refers to establishing rules, like the principle of 'cultivating virtue before martial arts'.

1054
00:45:28,027 --> 00:45:31,075
When those being taught clearly violate the rules, or even the law,

1055
00:45:31,075 --> 00:45:33,030
appropriate punishment must be meted out.

1056
00:45:33,030 --> 00:45:34,092
The explanation in the Xiang Zhuan is quite apt.

1057
00:45:34,092 --> 00:45:38,024
“Employing punishment is for the sake of upholding the law.”

1058
00:45:38,024 --> 00:45:39,062
Punishment is not about inflicting violence.

1059
00:45:39,062 --> 00:45:42,081
It is to uphold justice, to establish clear boundaries.

1060
00:45:42,081 --> 00:45:44,035
to establish a righteous system of values.

1061
00:45:44,035 --> 00:45:46,019
This is the fundamental principle of enlightenment.

1062
00:45:46,019 --> 00:45:47,035
"to cast off the fetters"

1063
00:45:47,035 --> 00:45:51,035
Here, the character '说' (shuō) is interchangeable with '脱' (tuō), which means 'to take off'. '桎梏' (zhì gù) refers to ancient instruments of punishment, like shackles.

1064
00:45:51,035 --> 00:45:52,021
Finally, it is said, 'set the will.'

1065
00:45:52,021 --> 00:45:53,003
The first principle is 'solidity'.

1066
00:45:53,003 --> 00:45:56,039
So, the complete meaning of this line of the hexagram is: to enlighten the ignorant.

1067
00:45:56,039 --> 00:45:59,005
It's about instilling a sense of reverence in those who seek guidance from the very beginning.

1068
00:45:59,005 --> 00:46:00,005
and understand the boundaries.

1069
00:46:00,005 --> 00:46:04,039
This is the only way to help them later on, to break free from the shackles of their minds and their bad habits.

1070
00:46:04,039 --> 00:46:05,037
When a person is first born,

1071
00:46:05,037 --> 00:46:08,085
So, what do you think? Are people inherently good, or are they inherently evil?

1072
00:46:08,085 --> 00:46:11,059
The idea of innate goodness is correct, and the idea of innate evil is also correct.

1073
00:46:11,059 --> 00:46:13,043
The idea that human nature is inherently good means that at the very beginning,

1074
00:46:13,043 --> 00:46:17,006
They don't have the capacity to commit sins like killing, stealing, sexual misconduct, lying, or drinking.

1075
00:46:17,006 --> 00:46:20,066
The idea that human nature is evil, on the other hand, holds that at the very beginning, we are already full of greed, anger, ignorance, arrogance, and doubt.

1076
00:46:20,066 --> 00:46:23,031
This one point is so spot-on, anyone who's raised a child knows exactly what I'm talking about.

1077
00:46:23,031 --> 00:46:24,085
At the very beginning of a child's life,

1078
00:46:24,085 --> 00:46:28,037
They are completely and utterly driven by patterns of extreme selfishness and self-interest.

1079
00:46:28,037 --> 00:46:31,037
And so, the purpose of our education is to teach the ignorant the objective laws of this world.

1080
00:46:31,037 --> 00:46:37,082
We teach them to stay away from fire and water, and to know what they can and can't eat.

1081
00:46:37,082 --> 00:46:39,026
and to greet your elders when you see them.

1082
00:46:39,026 --> 00:46:41,072
Don't take things that aren't yours, and so on and so forth.

1083
00:46:41,072 --> 00:46:44,024
If they fail to grasp these fundamental rules,

1084
00:46:44,024 --> 00:46:45,098
let alone make a place for themselves in society.

1085
00:46:45,098 --> 00:46:47,044
they won't even be able to survive.

1086
00:46:47,044 --> 00:46:51,075
So, the very first lesson in启蒙, or启蒙, is to teach children what the absolute taboos are.

1087
00:46:51,075 --> 00:46:54,077
Many mistakes, once made, mean you'll have to start all over again in the next life.

1088
00:46:54,077 --> 00:46:57,023
So, why do people observe a three-year mourning period for their parents after they die?

1089
00:46:57,023 --> 00:46:58,086
In reality, it's 27 months.

1090
00:46:58,086 --> 00:47:02,026
This is because, as the saying goes, 'A child is not free from the embrace of its parents until three years of age.'

1091
00:47:02,026 --> 00:47:03,060
Before a child reaches the age of three,

1092
00:47:03,060 --> 00:47:05,056
In fact, every single day is a life-or-death struggle.

1093
00:47:05,056 --> 00:47:07,070
The moment you look away, they could fall into a well.

1094
00:47:07,070 --> 00:47:09,060
If you don't feed them for two days, they'll starve to death.

1095
00:47:09,060 --> 00:47:13,000
It's just that their parents have kept them alive for the first three years, that's all.

1096
00:47:13,000 --> 00:47:14,087
So, what's the state of a young child?

1097
00:47:14,087 --> 00:47:16,035
Cute as they may be,

1098
00:47:16,035 --> 00:47:19,090
But their minds are still undeveloped, they can't tell right from wrong, and they act on their every whim.

1099
00:47:19,090 --> 00:47:22,050
This is where the educator comes in, to set rules, define boundaries, and establish consequences.

1100
00:47:22,050 --> 00:47:24,031
Setting clear boundaries is a form of discipline.

1101
00:47:24,031 --> 00:47:26,071
To put it in terms of a lot of trendy educational methods today,

1102
00:47:26,071 --> 00:47:31,015
This is what's called 'gentle firmness.' You make the boundaries clear to them. Rules are rules.

1103
00:47:31,015 --> 00:47:34,028
You just can't cross the line. If you do, you will be punished.

1104
00:47:34,028 --> 00:47:36,056
Either a spanking on the butt, or standing in the corner.

1105
00:47:36,056 --> 00:47:38,027
Without rules, there's no order!

1106
00:47:38,027 --> 00:47:40,070
Without discipline, there can be no enlightenment!

1107
00:47:40,070 --> 00:47:41,078
The final part of this line, "to go will bring hardship"...

1108
00:47:41,078 --> 00:47:46,023
Here, "to go" means to take the initiative, to step beyond the boundaries.

1109
00:47:46,023 --> 00:47:48,087
And 'ke' signifies hardship, regret, and adversity.

1110
00:47:48,087 --> 00:47:51,033
This is talking about the taboos during the initial, formative stage.

1111
00:47:51,033 --> 00:47:54,037
Don't rush for quick results, and don't ignore the rules.

1112
00:47:54,037 --> 00:47:58,049
In the early stages of establishing rules and nurturing the mind, don't try to force growth.

1113
00:47:58,049 --> 00:48:01,050
Let children grow at their own pace. Don't rush them to succeed.

1114
00:48:01,050 --> 00:48:05,056
The key at this stage is not to overlook those seemingly 'minor' misbehaviors in your child.

1115
00:48:05,056 --> 00:48:08,004
Because, as the saying goes, 'Treading on frost, the solid ice will come.'

1116
00:48:08,004 --> 00:48:09,062


1117
00:48:09,062 --> 00:48:13,041
Setting these rules now is all about laying a solid foundation for the future.

1118
00:48:13,041 --> 00:48:16,031
So, to sum it all up, the first thing in启蒙 is...

1119
00:48:16,031 --> 00:48:18,082
is about setting rules, not just imparting knowledge.

1120
00:48:18,082 --> 00:48:22,043
Slow and steady growth is better than forced progress.

1121
00:48:22,075 --> 00:48:27,067
The second nine, "Nourishing the Ignorant, auspicious." This "nourishing the ignorant" refers to dealing with all kinds of ignorance.

1122
00:48:27,067 --> 00:48:30,091
An educator must possess an inclusive and tolerant character, teaching all without discrimination.

1123
00:48:30,091 --> 00:48:32,018
and not see them through a biased lens.

1124
00:48:32,018 --> 00:48:35,020
and tailors the teaching to each sincere student according to their aptitude.

1125
00:48:35,020 --> 00:48:36,098
This is the righteous virtue of the teaching path.

1126
00:48:36,098 --> 00:48:39,022
Those whose virtue matches their position are destined to find good fortune.

1127
00:48:39,022 --> 00:48:42,048
This is just like how a doctor's sacred duty is to heal the sick and save lives.

1128
00:48:42,048 --> 00:48:45,006
Whether this person is a good guy or a bad guy is not for the healer to consider.

1129
00:48:45,006 --> 00:48:48,094
As long as they seek knowledge with a sincere heart, the teacher should impart it.

1130
00:48:48,094 --> 00:48:52,054
But what to teach, and how, requires the teacher to tailor their instruction to the individual student.

1131
00:48:52,054 --> 00:48:54,090
But what if a bad person sincerely comes to learn?

1132
00:48:54,090 --> 00:48:56,016
Then they should be taught as well.

1133
00:48:56,016 --> 00:48:58,010
However, the first priority is to cultivate virtue.

1134
00:48:58,010 --> 00:49:00,074
As long as they are sincere, a teacher must be tolerant and nurturing.

1135
00:49:00,074 --> 00:49:02,028
To guide and transform, and to accept one's duties.

1136
00:49:02,028 --> 00:49:06,084
The line 'Taking a wife brings good fortune' means that by marrying and uniting the masculine and feminine, one is certain to achieve auspiciousness.

1137
00:49:06,084 --> 00:49:11,014
As we've mentioned, the second and fifth lines are in the middle positions, serving as a bridge connecting the top and bottom.

1138
00:49:11,014 --> 00:49:12,057
They are the core pivot.

1139
00:49:12,057 --> 00:49:16,022
So, these two positions are generally considered favorable, regardless of whether they are yin or yang.

1140
00:49:16,022 --> 00:49:20,008
In the Meng Hexagram, the second line is a Yang line in a Yin position. Although it is not in its proper place, it is located in the central position of the lower trigram, which means the Yang line has attained centrality.

1141
00:49:20,008 --> 00:49:21,076
But it is positioned in the middle of the lower trigram.

1142
00:49:21,076 --> 00:49:23,099
When a yang line is centered, it is also called 'firmly centered'.

1143
00:49:23,099 --> 00:49:27,083
Here, taking a wife is used as a metaphor for the 'firm and central' virtue of the Nine in the Second Place.

1144
00:49:27,083 --> 00:49:33,078
The term "taking a wife" refers to the Nine in the Second Place coming to marry the Six in the Fifth Place, its corresponding partner, which we will discuss later.

1145
00:49:33,078 --> 00:49:35,094
The second line, Nine, is a yang line in a yin position.

1146
00:49:35,094 --> 00:49:37,086
The sixth five is a yin line in a yang position.

1147
00:49:37,086 --> 00:49:39,080
Let's talk about the line statement for the sixth five in advance.

1148
00:49:39,080 --> 00:49:45,035
In other words, the 'naive student' seeks out the 'enveloping mentor,' which corresponds to that specific line in the hexagram's commentary.

1149
00:49:45,035 --> 00:49:47,049
It is not I who seek the young and ignorant, but the young and ignorant who seek me.

1150
00:49:47,049 --> 00:49:52,044
Now, the "childlike seeker" here is the sixth five line. And even though it holds the position of a ruler,

1151
00:49:52,044 --> 00:49:54,046
But it still has to humble itself and proactively reach down to the Ninth Two.

1152
00:49:54,046 --> 00:49:56,012
and take the initiative to seek out the Nine in the Second Place.

1153
00:49:56,012 --> 00:49:59,012
It's like, even if you're a prince,

1154
00:49:59,012 --> 00:50:02,038
you still have to show your teacher the proper respect and perform the rites due to a master.

1155
00:50:02,038 --> 00:50:03,072
As the saying goes, "Only when the teacher is respected, can the Way be esteemed."

1156
00:50:03,072 --> 00:50:05,072
Only when the Way is respected will the people know to honor learning.

1157
00:50:05,072 --> 00:50:09,071
“There are two cases in which a ruler does not treat his subjects as subjects.”

1158
00:50:09,071 --> 00:50:13,087
“When he is a teacher, he is not to be treated as a subject.”

1159
00:50:13,087 --> 00:50:14,087
The rites of the great learning state that even when a teacher is summoned by the Son of Heaven, he does not face north.

1160
00:50:14,087 --> 00:50:16,039
Even if the Son of Heaven himself is present, the master does not face north.

1161
00:50:16,039 --> 00:50:21,044
And that's why teachers are held in such high regard. See? Since ancient times, the rule has been that even the Son of Heaven, when facing his teacher...

1162
00:50:21,044 --> 00:50:24,003
the teacher is also exempt from the kneeling rites between a ruler and his subject.

1163
00:50:24,003 --> 00:50:26,093
Instead, the Son of Heaven must perform a formal bow as a student to his teacher.

1164
00:50:26,093 --> 00:50:29,091
The dignity of the master-student relationship transcends the hierarchy between a ruler and his subject!

1165
00:50:29,091 --> 00:50:33,027
Let's make a comparison, shall we? Even when the Empress meets her own father,

1166
00:50:33,027 --> 00:50:37,002
Even the Empress's father must perform the kneeling ceremony to his own daughter, as a subject to his sovereign.

1167
00:50:37,002 --> 00:50:39,064
Because since ancient times, the bond between a ruler and his subject has always preceded that of a father and his son.

1168
00:50:39,064 --> 00:50:44,006
But the Emperor's Tutor is an exception, because the way of the teacher transcends the relationship between a ruler and his subject!

1169
00:50:44,006 --> 00:50:46,024
And this has been the way of things in our Chinese civilization since ancient times.

1170
00:50:46,024 --> 00:50:50,007
Starting from the Qin and Han dynasties, the etiquette for princes towards their tutors was codified into law.

1171
00:50:50,007 --> 00:50:51,056
And this tradition was reinforced with each passing generation.

1172
00:50:51,056 --> 00:50:52,063
By the time of the Qing Dynasty,

1173
00:50:52,063 --> 00:50:55,056
They even incorporated the princes' respect for their teachers into the imperial family's code of conduct.

1174
00:50:55,056 --> 00:50:57,044
And its enforcement was the strictest of any dynasty in history.

1175
00:50:57,044 --> 00:51:01,024
Throughout the entire Qing Dynasty, there was hardly a single prince who dared to slack off or show disrespect to their tutors.

1176
00:51:01,024 --> 00:51:03,057
Anyone who violated these rules would face severe punishment from the emperor.

1177
00:51:03,057 --> 00:51:05,076
Since ancient times, their studies have always centered on the Four Books and Five Classics.

1178
00:51:05,076 --> 00:51:08,062
So, the imperial family clearly understood what the Meng Hexagram was all about.

1179
00:51:08,062 --> 00:51:12,044
No matter how big a shot you are, you have to humble yourself when you seek knowledge.

1180
00:51:12,044 --> 00:51:15,086
Only with this kind of attitude can you truly achieve success in your studies!

1181
00:51:15,086 --> 00:51:22,056
Now, if we take a closer look at the imagery of the Meng Hexagram, which is 'Mountain over Water,' it shows the mountain in the upper trigram seeking out the water in the lower trigram.

1182
00:51:22,056 --> 00:51:25,002
This once again reflects the degree of their devotion.

1183
00:51:25,002 --> 00:51:27,048
The lower trigram of this hexagram represents the one who teaches.

1184
00:51:27,048 --> 00:51:32,077
The upper trigram represents the one seeking knowledge. It should ascend to approach the lower, just as the yin approaches the yang.

1185
00:51:32,077 --> 00:51:33,093
This is precisely what the final line of the Yao text means by 'a son who can manage the household'.

1186
00:51:33,093 --> 00:51:37,045
The character 'Ke' here doesn't mean 'to overcome' or 'to conquer'.

1187
00:51:37,045 --> 00:51:39,085
It means to be capable and to take on responsibilities.

1188
00:51:39,085 --> 00:51:40,065
or 'pay-to-win'.

1189
00:51:40,065 --> 00:51:44,065
It's the same 'ke' as in 'diligent and frugal.' It refers to a child who approaches learning with a devout and humble attitude.

1190
00:51:44,065 --> 00:51:46,025
Only then can they become pillars of the community.

1191
00:51:46,025 --> 00:51:48,032
and only then can they shoulder great responsibilities in the future.

1192
00:51:48,032 --> 00:51:49,076
This line from the 'Xiang Zhuan', 'The son can manage the family, because the strong and the gentle are in contact,'

1193
00:51:49,076 --> 00:51:52,030
The Xiang Commentary further elaborates on this, explaining the interaction between the firm and the yielding.

1194
00:51:52,030 --> 00:51:54,064
First, as we mentioned earlier, the Nine in the Second Place, despite its low position...

1195
00:51:54,064 --> 00:51:56,086
But it still requires the humble and noble you, the Six in the Fifth, to come down.

1196
00:51:56,086 --> 00:51:58,076
And don't be fooled by the lowly position of the Nine in the Second Place.

1197
00:51:58,076 --> 00:52:00,020
But the thing is, it's a Yang line.

1198
00:52:00,020 --> 00:52:04,045
Even when you, the fifth six, arrive, they will still have to 'enlighten the ignorant by applying penalties, using shackles and fetters.'

1199
00:52:04,045 --> 00:52:07,079
He'll use masculine, righteous principles to set the rules for you.

1200
00:52:07,079 --> 00:52:10,011
The high submits to the low, the yin follows the yang.

1201
00:52:10,011 --> 00:52:11,085
No matter how high your status or how wealthy your family is,

1202
00:52:11,085 --> 00:52:13,009
even a son,

1203
00:52:13,009 --> 00:52:14,097
must also cast aside these external things.

1204
00:52:14,097 --> 00:52:17,026
and approach your studies with the utmost humility.

1205
00:52:17,026 --> 00:52:19,006
If even students of high status are like this,

1206
00:52:19,006 --> 00:52:21,004
let alone children from ordinary families.

1207
00:52:21,004 --> 00:52:23,064
So what right do we have to look down on our teachers?

1208
00:52:23,064 --> 00:52:25,099
The lowly do not fear the high, and the strong do not fawn upon the weak.

1209
00:52:25,099 --> 00:52:28,035
This is the dignity and integrity that educators must uphold.

1210
00:52:28,035 --> 00:52:29,081
If you don't respect me,

1211
00:52:29,081 --> 00:52:31,085
or if you don't follow the rules I've set,

1212
00:52:31,085 --> 00:52:34,035
It doesn't matter how high your status is, or how much money you offer me.

1213
00:52:34,035 --> 00:52:35,098
I will not take you as my student.

1214
00:52:35,098 --> 00:52:38,008
Because leniency in teaching is the teacher's dereliction of duty. Indulging you is actually harming you.

1215
00:52:38,008 --> 00:52:42,008
We can't bear the karma of leading our students astray.

1216
00:52:42,008 --> 00:52:45,044
No matter how humble your background, as long as you come to learn with a sincere heart,

1217
00:52:45,044 --> 00:52:47,086
and show the utmost respect your family can afford.

1218
00:52:47,086 --> 00:52:49,034
Then that's what we call fate.

1219
00:52:49,034 --> 00:52:52,013
And in turn, we will impart to you all the knowledge we have, based on the materials you provide.

1220
00:52:52,013 --> 00:52:54,047
To all our dear seekers of knowledge and mentors,

1221
00:52:54,047 --> 00:52:58,023
So, does this offer any inspiration for you and your own 'treasures'?

1222
00:52:58,047 --> 00:53:00,033
Now, let's look at the third six.

1223
00:53:00,033 --> 00:53:01,081
The line statement says, 'It is not advantageous to take a wife who has seen a man of wealth.'

1224
00:53:01,081 --> 00:53:02,095
Disregard for one's own integrity brings no advantage.

1225
00:53:02,095 --> 00:53:06,033
A yin line in a yang position is out of place, and it's also off-center.

1226
00:53:06,033 --> 00:53:10,019
Furthermore, it resides at the zenith of the Kan trigram, which represents danger, pitfalls, and confusion.

1227
00:53:10,019 --> 00:53:12,076
This line of the hexagram also represents the peak of danger.

1228
00:53:12,076 --> 00:53:15,050
This line begins with the stark warning: 'Do not take this woman.'

1229
00:53:15,050 --> 00:53:17,040
Now, the character '取' (qǔ) here is a pun for '娶' (qǔ), which means 'to marry' as in 'marrying a wife'.

1230
00:53:17,040 --> 00:53:21,008
It starts right off by saying, 'Don't marry this woman!'

1231
00:53:21,008 --> 00:53:22,066
So, what kind of woman are we talking about?

1232
00:53:22,066 --> 00:53:24,093
“She sees a man of wealth, loses all self-control.”

1233
00:53:24,093 --> 00:53:29,009
Oh, come on. The moment they see someone rich and powerful, they forget all about the dignity of their profession as a teacher.

1234
00:53:29,009 --> 00:53:31,028
and just rush to suck up to them.

1235
00:53:31,028 --> 00:53:34,036
Their minds are no longer focused on how to impart knowledge, teach their craft, and resolve doubts.

1236
00:53:34,036 --> 00:53:35,036
to establish the heart of Heaven and Earth,

1237
00:53:35,036 --> 00:53:39,017
to secure a livelihood for the people, to carry on the lost teachings of past sages, and to establish peace for all generations to come.

1238
00:53:39,017 --> 00:53:42,041
All they can think about is how to maximize their own gains.

1239
00:53:42,041 --> 00:53:45,032
This kid doesn't want to learn. He's just not cut out for it.

1240
00:53:45,032 --> 00:53:50,044
And you're just teaching for the sake of money and power. Remember, 'A sheer cliff stands a thousand ren high; without desire, one is invincible.'

1241
00:53:50,044 --> 00:53:53,032
You're scared of your own shadow, constantly calculating risks and rewards.

1242
00:53:53,032 --> 00:53:57,014
Then you can't even talk about educating the child with that firm, yet balanced, virtue anymore.

1243
00:53:57,014 --> 00:53:58,074
Even when it's obvious the kid is going down the wrong path,

1244
00:53:58,074 --> 00:54:00,002
you wouldn't dare to correct them.

1245
00:54:00,002 --> 00:54:00,046
Oh, right.

1246
00:54:00,046 --> 00:54:02,023
Oh, right, this is the boss's son.

1247
00:54:02,023 --> 00:54:04,095
Or, what if the kid doesn't like me? I could lose my job over it.

1248
00:54:04,095 --> 00:54:05,091
blah blah blah...

1249
00:54:05,091 --> 00:54:08,063
This kid just has no respect for real knowledge.

1250
00:54:08,063 --> 00:54:10,054
and just keep making the same mistakes over and over again.

1251
00:54:10,054 --> 00:54:13,038
Over time, this will inevitably lead to a habit of being careless and not thinking.

1252
00:54:13,038 --> 00:54:16,034
But you, the educator, are so preoccupied with your own desires and reservations.

1253
00:54:16,034 --> 00:54:19,087
Do you still dare to 'tell the first divination, but not the second or third, for the second and third are profane'?

1254
00:54:19,087 --> 00:54:20,085
I bet you wouldn't dare.

1255
00:54:20,085 --> 00:54:23,077
Because you're worried the parents will complain, 'Why aren't you more patient?'

1256
00:54:23,077 --> 00:54:29,020
The commentary in the 'Xiang Zhuan' on this line, 'Do not take the woman, for her conduct is not in accordance,' really hits the nail on the head.

1257
00:54:29,020 --> 00:54:31,020
Since ancient times, the divine right of kings has been the rule.

1258
00:54:31,020 --> 00:54:34,032
But the way of the teacher can even transcend the way of the ruler.

1259
00:54:34,032 --> 00:54:37,052
As the one who imparts the Way, you should not let the masculine principle yield to the feminine.

1260
00:54:37,052 --> 00:54:41,044
You shouldn't be like the line 'Seeing a wealthy man, she loses her integrity,' eagerly throwing yourself at him.

1261
00:54:41,044 --> 00:54:43,036
You have strayed from the right path!

1262
00:54:43,036 --> 00:54:45,032
And this final line, 'nothing is beneficial'...

1263
00:54:45,032 --> 00:54:47,022
This means that whether you're the one being this kind of teacher,

1264
00:54:47,022 --> 00:54:51,070
or the students who seek guidance from such teachers, it's a lose-lose situation for both sides!

1265
00:54:51,070 --> 00:54:55,008
First of all, if you seek knowledge from such a teacher, you will never learn anything of real value.

1266
00:54:55,008 --> 00:54:58,068
Because to truly learn something, you need a genuine, heartfelt respect.

1267
00:54:58,068 --> 00:55:01,000
Only when you truly take it to heart,

1268
00:55:01,000 --> 00:55:04,052
Only then will you truly contemplate the wisdom and mentally digest it.

1269
00:55:04,052 --> 00:55:07,044
Only then, in the future, when you apply theory to practice,

1270
00:55:07,044 --> 00:55:11,032
Only then will you have that 'aha!' moment, gaining wisdom that will benefit you for a lifetime.

1271
00:55:11,032 --> 00:55:14,062
And when your mentor is afraid to be firm and set clear rules for you,

1272
00:55:14,062 --> 00:55:16,093
he won't be able to correct your mistakes.

1273
00:55:16,093 --> 00:55:20,087
Failing to correct your mistakes is the greatest obstacle and hidden danger to your growth.

1274
00:55:20,087 --> 00:55:23,009
If you stray from the right path, the further you go, the bigger the mistake becomes.

1275
00:55:23,009 --> 00:55:24,033
the bigger the mistake becomes.

1276
00:55:24,033 --> 00:55:27,045
For the mentor who is described by the line 'upon seeing the wealthy man, she loses her integrity'...

1277
00:55:27,045 --> 00:55:31,067
Do you really think that just by being a smooth operator and dealing with people superficially,

1278
00:55:31,067 --> 00:55:33,051
and get what you want?

1279
00:55:33,051 --> 00:55:34,075
For the mentor,

1280
00:55:34,075 --> 00:55:38,009
The most crucial metric is whether the student can truly become successful.

1281
00:55:38,009 --> 00:55:40,033
Your most enduring legacy is your students.

1282
00:55:40,033 --> 00:55:42,056
and will honor you as their mentor for the rest of their lives.

1283
00:55:42,056 --> 00:55:44,090
And you think this groveling attitude of yours...

1284
00:55:44,090 --> 00:55:46,078
You see mistakes but don't dare to point them out.

1285
00:55:46,078 --> 00:55:49,036
acting all timid and cowering in front of your students and employers,

1286
00:55:49,036 --> 00:55:51,018
Do you think you can help them succeed?

1287
00:55:51,018 --> 00:55:53,056
Will that earn you the respect of your own family?

1288
00:55:53,056 --> 00:55:56,092
As an educator, you must first define your own ecological niche.

1289
00:55:56,092 --> 00:55:59,001
and have a clear understanding of your own path.

1290
00:55:59,001 --> 00:56:03,009
There are many paths and methods to seek progress and prosperity.

1291
00:56:03,009 --> 00:56:06,056
Don't take the responsibility of being a role model lightly.

1292
00:56:07,012 --> 00:56:09,090
Six in the fourth place: The line statement reads, 'In the困境 of ignorance, there is regret.'

1293
00:56:09,090 --> 00:56:12,012
Trapped by ignorance and unable to save oneself.

1294
00:56:12,012 --> 00:56:13,034
Seeking enlightenment, but finding no way in.

1295
00:56:13,034 --> 00:56:15,054
This is a very regrettable and difficult situation.

1296
00:56:15,054 --> 00:56:18,004
Now, as we've mentioned before, the upper trigram represents the learner.

1297
00:56:18,004 --> 00:56:19,089
The lower trigram represents the teacher, and this is the fourth six, '困蒙' (Kùn Méng).

1298
00:56:19,089 --> 00:56:23,051
A yin line in a yin position symbolizes passivity and refraining from reckless action.

1299
00:56:23,051 --> 00:56:24,094
It is in the right position, but not in the center.

1300
00:56:24,094 --> 00:56:27,018
It lacks the virtue of centrality and uprightness, and the power to mediate.

1301
00:56:27,018 --> 00:56:29,038
It is supported by the Six-Three below and carries the Six-Five above, with both the upper and lower positions being yin.

1302
00:56:29,038 --> 00:56:31,062
Both above and below, it's a case of like repelling like.

1303
00:56:31,062 --> 00:56:33,073
This leaves it in a state of isolation and helplessness.

1304
00:56:33,073 --> 00:56:37,027
This line from the 'Xiang Zhuan' commentary, "The sting of being trapped in ignorance is from being alone and distant from the solid,"

1305
00:56:37,027 --> 00:56:40,018
This directly reveals the reason why the fourth six is passively trapped in ignorance.

1306
00:56:40,018 --> 00:56:41,056
You have distanced yourself from the 'substantial'.

1307
00:56:41,056 --> 00:56:43,016
In other words, it has distanced itself from the two yang lines of this hexagram, the 'Nine in the Second Place' and the 'Nine at the Top'.

1308
00:56:43,016 --> 00:56:50,048
This once again emphasizes that the pursuit of knowledge requires a firm foundation of positive, masculine principles.

1309
00:56:50,048 --> 00:56:56,038
It requires you, as the yin line, to be proactive. You must seek out the yang lines, to actively search for a worthy teacher.

1310
00:56:56,038 --> 00:56:59,022
You're not going to figure it out just by sitting at home!

1311
00:56:59,022 --> 00:57:02,044
And this once again echoes the point that the hexagram statement lacks the 'Yuan' or 'Origin' principle.

1312
00:57:02,044 --> 00:57:06,052
When it comes to learning, it's not something you can just figure out on your own.

1313
00:57:06,052 --> 00:57:09,012
You need a master to show you the way and give you guidance.

1314
00:57:09,012 --> 00:57:10,030
It requires an external force.

1315
00:57:10,030 --> 00:57:14,092
Even after you've received the true teachings of a theory, you still need to apply it to the real world.

1316
00:57:14,092 --> 00:57:19,070
We need to be proactive, to step out and see the world, to engage with all living things.

1317
00:57:19,070 --> 00:57:23,010
If we don't seek out mentors, respect them, or ask for their guidance,

1318
00:57:23,010 --> 00:57:24,086
just working behind closed doors.

1319
00:57:24,086 --> 00:57:28,030
Ultimately, you'll just become more and more closed off, and more and more backward.

1320
00:57:28,030 --> 00:57:30,038
and more and more stubborn.

1321
00:57:30,077 --> 00:57:33,078
Now, let's look at the fifth six. The line statement says: 'The young and ignorant. Good fortune.'

1322
00:57:33,078 --> 00:57:36,046
Now, this 'childlike ignorance' doesn't refer to a kid who's just confused.

1323
00:57:36,046 --> 00:57:38,044
It refers to the innocence of a newborn child.

1324
00:57:38,044 --> 00:57:41,076
It's a state of being sincere and open to learning, untainted by worldly influences.

1325
00:57:41,076 --> 00:57:44,036
Many great sages and powerful individuals still maintain the heart of a child, always eager to learn.

1326
00:57:44,036 --> 00:57:46,080
They still maintain this humble and sincere heart.

1327
00:57:46,080 --> 00:57:50,017
The 'Xiang Zhuan' commentary explains this as: 'The good fortune of the youthful ignorance is due to its compliance and humility.'

1328
00:57:50,017 --> 00:57:52,062
This is precisely referring to the virtue of humility in the 'naive and ignorant'.

1329
00:57:52,062 --> 00:57:54,030
The character "Xùn" is often associated with the concept of humility.

1330
00:57:54,030 --> 00:57:57,050


1331
00:57:57,050 --> 00:57:59,024
This means to yield the imperial throne.

1332
00:57:59,024 --> 00:58:00,096
The phrase 'Xùn yǔ zhī yán' in the Analects of Confucius also carries the meaning of being respectful and humble.

1333
00:58:00,096 --> 00:58:03,011
In other words, it means to be respectful and humble.

1334
00:58:03,011 --> 00:58:04,043
The fifth line, a yin line, is in the ruler's position. Although it is not in its proper place,

1335
00:58:04,043 --> 00:58:06,027
Although it is in the ruler's position, it is not in a proper position.

1336
00:58:06,027 --> 00:58:07,095
but it is in the central and esteemed position.

1337
00:58:07,095 --> 00:58:09,012
Generally speaking,

1338
00:58:09,012 --> 00:58:13,050
Those in positions of power often tend to develop flaws like complacency, arrogance, and conceit.

1339
00:58:13,050 --> 00:58:15,094
However, the fifth six, despite its position, remains humble, seeking guidance and positioning itself as a student.

1340
00:58:15,094 --> 00:58:17,000
positioning itself as an ally.

1341
00:58:17,000 --> 00:58:19,034
Avoid the pitfalls of a full moon that begins to wane, or water that overflows when the cup is full.

1342
00:58:19,034 --> 00:58:22,052
This is similar to the Ninth Five of the Qian hexagram, 'A flying dragon in the sky. It is beneficial to see the great man.'

1343
00:58:22,052 --> 00:58:25,000
This is just like the 'Yellow Skirt, Supreme Good Fortune' in the sixth five line of the Kun hexagram.

1344
00:58:25,000 --> 00:58:27,040
It's all about humbling yourself to seek progress.

1345
00:58:27,040 --> 00:58:30,050
Whether it's a child or a great figure who has already achieved fame and success,

1346
00:58:30,050 --> 00:58:34,026
When this person consistently maintains a humble attitude to seek out their own shortcomings,

1347
00:58:34,026 --> 00:58:36,046
seeking out new opportunities for growth and progress.

1348
00:58:36,046 --> 00:58:39,078
and to "seek the great man" for the infusion of new blood.

1349
00:58:39,078 --> 00:58:43,056
In its noble position as the sixth five, it humbles itself to seek out the ninth two.

1350
00:58:43,056 --> 00:58:44,041
To be high in position yet humble.

1351
00:58:44,041 --> 00:58:45,056
This is a case of the firm and the yielding corresponding with each other.

1352
00:58:45,056 --> 00:58:47,031
This is just as Mencius once said,

1353
00:58:47,031 --> 00:58:50,031
A great man is one who has not lost his heart of a newborn child.

1354
00:58:50,031 --> 00:58:52,040
And that's why it's destined for good fortune.

1355
00:58:52,076 --> 00:58:54,030
The Ninth at the Top.

1356
00:58:54,030 --> 00:58:56,051
The line text reads: 'To strike the ignorant is not favorable for being a raider, but favorable for defending against raiders.'

1357
00:58:56,051 --> 00:58:57,063
The top ninth line, a yang line in a yin position, is out of place and off-center.

1358
00:58:57,063 --> 00:58:58,087
It is in a yin position, which is an improper placement.

1359
00:58:58,087 --> 00:59:01,072
This represents the peak of the Gen mountain, and Gen signifies stopping.

1360
00:59:01,072 --> 00:59:03,094
This line talks about the bottom line of the Meng Hexagram.

1361
00:59:03,094 --> 00:59:06,056
It is the ultimate means of imparting enlightenment and education.

1362
00:59:06,056 --> 00:59:09,033
“Ji Meng” means to punish, to strike, to intimidate, and to establish authority.

1363
00:59:09,033 --> 00:59:12,027
It's the ultimate method for dealing with unruly kids.

1364
00:59:12,027 --> 00:59:14,082
If patient persuasion doesn't work,

1365
00:59:14,082 --> 00:59:16,082
or you can just ignore them, as the saying goes, 'if they show contempt, tell them nothing.'

1366
00:59:16,082 --> 00:59:17,094
Let him reflect on his own.

1367
00:59:17,094 --> 00:59:19,086
But guidance isn't a cure-all.

1368
00:59:19,086 --> 00:59:21,028
But if the child doesn't reflect on their actions,

1369
00:59:21,028 --> 00:59:22,072
and continues to be mischievous and disruptive,

1370
00:59:22,072 --> 00:59:24,010
and shows a blatant disregard for the dignity of the teaching profession,

1371
00:59:24,010 --> 00:59:26,022
or even worse, lead other children astray.

1372
00:59:26,022 --> 00:59:28,026
Then it's time to discipline them and show them who's in charge.

1373
00:59:28,026 --> 00:59:30,026
And it's not just petty people who respect power but not virtue.

1374
00:59:30,026 --> 00:59:31,070
Actually, it's the same with kids.

1375
00:59:31,070 --> 00:59:34,050
For many problems, it's useless no matter how much you try to reason with them.

1376
00:59:34,050 --> 00:59:36,014
A good smack will put them in their place.

1377
00:59:36,014 --> 00:59:37,016
It is not advantageous to be the attacker, but advantageous to be the defender.

1378
00:59:37,016 --> 00:59:38,057
This tells us the boundary of 'striking the ignorant'.

1379
00:59:38,057 --> 00:59:42,020
The boundary of 'attacking' lies in preventing violence and infringement.

1380
00:59:42,020 --> 00:59:45,042
If the purpose of 'striking the unenlightened' is to inflict violence or to vent your frustrations,

1381
00:59:45,042 --> 00:59:46,044
That is not right.

1382
00:59:46,044 --> 00:59:48,048
Our approach to 'striking the ignorant' should be a reactive one.

1383
00:59:48,048 --> 00:59:49,091
and to act with a just cause.

1384
00:59:49,091 --> 00:59:55,063
The goal is to uphold the fundamental principles of teaching! Punishing ignorance is the last resort and must not be abused.

1385
00:59:55,063 --> 00:59:57,033
Only when guidance proves ineffective,

1386
00:59:57,033 --> 00:59:59,097
It should only be used when the rules are broken and the right path is defiled.

1387
00:59:59,097 --> 01:00:03,036
Punishment is not the goal, nor is it a means of venting.

1388
01:00:03,036 --> 01:00:05,018
but rather, to "cultivate correctness through enlightenment."

1389
01:00:05,018 --> 01:00:09,033
The goal is to uphold the dignity of our teaching principles, and to be accountable to the masters who came before us.

1390
01:00:09,033 --> 01:00:11,047
and below, to be responsible for the children and their families.

1391
01:00:11,047 --> 01:00:14,011
If a proper measure of discipline still doesn't work,

1392
01:00:14,011 --> 01:00:16,097
we should not escalate the severity or methods of punishment either.

1393
01:00:16,097 --> 01:00:19,079
Because why would you waste all that energy getting angry at them?

1394
01:00:19,079 --> 01:00:21,051
Why would you even bother hitting him?

1395
01:00:21,051 --> 01:00:24,087
This proves that the child is simply not suited for education.

1396
01:00:24,087 --> 01:00:27,043
At least for now, it's not a good fit. End the relationship.

1397
01:00:27,043 --> 01:00:31,064
It means I'm too old and incompetent. This child should find a better master.

1398
01:00:31,064 --> 01:00:32,080
Favorable. I, the teacher, seek the student in their ignorance. The student in their ignorance seeks me.

1399
01:00:32,080 --> 01:00:34,026
If the student comes to me, they are ready.

1400
01:00:34,026 --> 01:00:35,010
The first divination will give an answer. If you ask again and again, it is an offense, and no answer will be given.

1401
01:00:35,010 --> 01:00:37,028
Favorable to be steadfast.

1402
01:00:37,028 --> 01:00:39,032
From seeking knowledge to imparting it.

1403
01:00:39,032 --> 01:00:42,096
The Meng Hexagram encompasses the full range of responsibilities and obligations for both parties in the educational process.

1404
01:00:42,096 --> 01:00:45,054
It also clearly outlines all the stages and conditions.

1405
01:00:45,054 --> 01:00:48,024
So, what can we learn from this?

1406
01:00:48,067 --> 01:00:51,033
The Xu Hexagram is the fifth of the 64 hexagrams in the I Ching.

1407
01:00:51,033 --> 01:00:53,071
Following the creation of Qian, and the bearing of Kun.

1408
01:00:53,071 --> 01:00:54,073
The Beginning: Zhun.

1409
01:00:54,073 --> 01:00:56,014
Following the Meng Hexagram, which represents the awakening of wisdom,

1410
01:00:56,014 --> 01:00:58,070
Now, it's time to explore the matters of our needs and desires.

1411
01:00:58,070 --> 01:01:02,061
This is precisely the line from the 'Sequence of Hexagrams': 'Meng, that which is unenlightened, is the infancy of all things.'

1412
01:01:02,061 --> 01:01:05,069
Things in their infancy cannot be left ungrown; therefore, the hexagram of Xu follows.

1413
01:01:05,069 --> 01:01:07,056
The character 'Xu' signifies the way of sustenance.

1414
01:01:07,056 --> 01:01:12,065
The Great Image commentary also summarizes this, saying: 'Clouds above heaven: the image of Waiting. The superior person nourishes himself with food and drink and awaits the time of action.'

1415
01:01:12,065 --> 01:01:14,059
The focus here is on "food and drink" and "feasting and entertainment."

1416
01:01:14,059 --> 01:01:17,057
These matters of sustaining life and distributing benefits

1417
01:01:17,057 --> 01:01:20,042
Now, the 'feasting and music' here doesn't mean just getting wasted and partying, you know.

1418
01:01:20,042 --> 01:01:22,078
It serves as a vehicle for uniting the team and distributing benefits.

1419
01:01:22,078 --> 01:01:24,075
We'll dive deeper into this when we get to the Ninth Five.

1420
01:01:24,075 --> 01:01:27,001
The Xū Hexagram is composed of Kan (Water) above and Qián (Heaven) below, which is why it is also known as 'Water over Heaven.'

1421
01:01:27,001 --> 01:01:29,083
That's why it's also called 'Water over Heaven,' with the lower trigram being Heaven.

1422
01:01:29,083 --> 01:01:32,065
This means that just as Heaven's course is ever vigorous, a gentleman should constantly strive for self-improvement.

1423
01:01:32,065 --> 01:01:36,031
Everything you need must be earned through your own hard work.

1424
01:01:36,031 --> 01:01:37,037
The upper trigram is Water.

1425
01:01:37,037 --> 01:01:40,039
This means your path ahead is once again fraught with danger.

1426
01:01:40,039 --> 01:01:42,065
Actually, have you guys ever noticed something?

1427
01:01:42,065 --> 01:01:45,021
The Kan trigram really shows up a lot, doesn't it?!

1428
01:01:45,021 --> 01:01:46,056
Starting with the Tun Hexagram,

1429
01:01:46,056 --> 01:01:50,022
In fact, the Kan trigram appears in every single hexagram of this initial stage of all things.

1430
01:01:50,022 --> 01:01:52,014
After the 'parent' hexagrams of Qian and Kun,

1431
01:01:52,014 --> 01:01:57,005
The hexagrams of Zhun, Meng, Xu, Song, Shi, and Bi all contain the Kan trigram within them.

1432
01:01:57,005 --> 01:02:00,001
So, what can we take away from all this?

1433
01:02:00,001 --> 01:02:02,089
The beginning of all things is fraught with peril.

1434
01:02:02,089 --> 01:02:04,093
Especially for this hexagram, the Tuan Zhuan, or the Commentary on the Decision, even directly explains it.

1435
01:02:04,093 --> 01:02:11,083
Xu means to wait. It signifies that danger lies ahead. However, if one is firm and strong, one will not be trapped. This is the principle of how one avoids being cornered.

1436
01:02:11,083 --> 01:02:13,033
The original meaning of the character "xū" is beard.

1437
01:02:13,033 --> 01:02:16,099
In the pre-Qin classics, it was also often used interchangeably with this character, '頫'.

1438
01:02:16,099 --> 01:02:18,054
This means 'to wait'.

1439
01:02:18,054 --> 01:02:19,072
For instance, in the 'Classic of Poetry,' there's a line that says, 'Others cross the river, but I will not. I will wait for my friend.'

1440
01:02:19,072 --> 01:02:20,056
pronounced as "áng"

1441
01:02:20,056 --> 01:02:22,066


1442
01:02:22,066 --> 01:02:24,042
Heaven will grant five years of grace to their descendants.

1443
01:02:24,042 --> 01:02:27,030
In the Zuo Zhuan, it says, "The day is waning, and our lord is waiting."

1444
01:02:27,030 --> 01:02:29,036
In all these instances, the character 'xū' carries the meaning of 'to wait'.

1445
01:02:29,036 --> 01:02:30,076
What the Commentary on the Tuan says is this:

1446
01:02:30,076 --> 01:02:32,096
All your needs require you to wait.

1447
01:02:32,096 --> 01:02:34,026
And this requires patience.

1448
01:02:34,026 --> 01:02:39,036
You need to think it through and carefully discern whether it's something you truly need.

1449
01:02:39,036 --> 01:02:41,090
Because right behind desire lies danger!

1450
01:02:41,090 --> 01:02:44,004
Of course, this isn't to say we should just lie flat and give up, you know.

1451
01:02:44,004 --> 01:02:46,064
It's not about actively suppressing our desires,

1452
01:02:46,064 --> 01:02:49,090
You see, our Chinese ancestors never taught us to be passive.

1453
01:02:49,090 --> 01:02:51,050
Even when facing the counsel to 'lie low like a hidden dragon,' or the warning that 'one step on frost means solid ice is near,'

1454
01:02:51,050 --> 01:02:53,046
or even 'treading on frost, the solid ice will come'

1455
01:02:53,046 --> 01:02:57,024
all of these are reminders for us to act with a low profile and in a proactive way.

1456
01:02:57,024 --> 01:03:00,090
This waiting is a proactive process of reflection and introspection, a necessary step to understand your true needs.

1457
01:03:00,090 --> 01:03:03,068
and to grasp the fundamental principles that govern how things develop.

1458
01:03:03,068 --> 01:03:07,008
If you want the fruits of autumn, you must sow in the spring and toil through the summer!

1459
01:03:07,008 --> 01:03:08,082
A noble person loves wealth, but acquires it through righteous means.

1460
01:03:08,082 --> 01:03:11,054
Reasonable desires are in accordance with the principles of nature and human nature.

1461
01:03:11,054 --> 01:03:13,016
So, the lower trigram is Qian.

1462
01:03:13,016 --> 01:03:15,020
This serves as a reminder that we must always strive.

1463
01:03:15,020 --> 01:03:17,065
But what is all this striving for?

1464
01:03:17,065 --> 01:03:19,069
Is it about the goals and meaning of life,

1465
01:03:19,069 --> 01:03:22,099
Or is it just to fall into a never-ending trap of desire?

1466
01:03:22,099 --> 01:03:26,022
And so, "The character for 'Need' (需) also signifies 'waiting' (須), as danger lies ahead."

1467
01:03:26,022 --> 01:03:28,012
Our ancestors remind us to be mindful of our own needs and desires.

1468
01:03:28,012 --> 01:03:32,010
We need to engage in prudent thinking.

1469
01:03:32,010 --> 01:03:34,091
We must endure the test of time and the trial of waiting.

1470
01:03:34,091 --> 01:03:36,097
It's true that we strive our entire lives,

1471
01:03:36,097 --> 01:03:40,034
But we must always be clear about what we're striving for.

1472
01:03:40,034 --> 01:03:45,016
This way, as you move forward, you won't be dragged into danger by the great net of desire.

1473
01:03:45,016 --> 01:03:48,078
This means 'to be firm and strong, yet not陷 in its righteousness, so it will not be困穷.'

1474
01:03:50,002 --> 01:03:51,006
Let's look at the Hexagram Statement: 'Faithfulness brings success, and it is beneficial to be steadfast and upright.'

1475
01:03:51,006 --> 01:03:53,080
With sincerity, it will be smooth and successful. Perseverance brings good fortune.

1476
01:03:53,080 --> 01:03:54,069
It is beneficial to cross the great river.

1477
01:03:54,069 --> 01:03:56,041
First of all, there's another point to note.

1478
01:03:56,041 --> 01:03:58,067
Here, we have 'Xiang,' 'Zhen,' and 'Li,' but 'Yuan' is missing.

1479
01:03:58,067 --> 01:04:01,026
But what does it mean that there's no 'Yuan'?

1480
01:04:01,026 --> 01:04:05,090
Your desires and needs are not something the universe is obligated to fulfill.

1481
01:04:05,090 --> 01:04:07,054
Whether it's a human or a beast, a plant or a fish,

1482
01:04:07,054 --> 01:04:09,018
be it plants and trees, or fish and insects.

1483
01:04:09,018 --> 01:04:12,042
How many young lives perish just moments after they are born?

1484
01:04:12,042 --> 01:04:15,016
The universe does, in fact, grant you a chance to begin.

1485
01:04:15,016 --> 01:04:18,003
But it's very likely just that: a beginning.

1486
01:04:18,003 --> 01:04:20,005
Heaven does indeed have a virtue of cherishing life.

1487
01:04:20,005 --> 01:04:24,053
But Heaven also never intervenes. The universe is not benevolent; it treats all things as straw dogs.

1488
01:04:24,053 --> 01:04:28,008
Therefore, we should cherish every single meal, remembering how hard it was to come by.

1489
01:04:28,008 --> 01:04:30,026
And every single thread reminds us of the toil and hardship involved.

1490
01:04:30,026 --> 01:04:33,082
We must cherish our blessings and our resources.

1491
01:04:33,082 --> 01:04:36,006
When we are grateful and cherish what we have,

1492
01:04:36,006 --> 01:04:38,098
And when we hold this sense of reverence, we are in the right state of being.

1493
01:04:38,098 --> 01:04:41,064
Only with a mind as open as a valley can one embrace all rivers.

1494
01:04:41,064 --> 01:04:44,036
With sincerity, there is great success, even the crossing of a great river.

1495
01:04:44,036 --> 01:04:46,024
The original meaning of this character, 'fú,' is 'to hatch an egg,' and from there, it was extended to mean 'to be trustworthy and faithful.'

1496
01:04:46,024 --> 01:04:48,054
Later, its meaning was extended to signify trustworthiness and faithfulness.

1497
01:04:48,054 --> 01:04:51,023
As the saying goes, 'Fu' means to hatch an egg, and by extension, to be trustworthy.

1498
01:04:51,023 --> 01:04:53,005
Just as a bird hatches its eggs precisely on schedule, it never fails to keep its promise.

1499
01:04:53,005 --> 01:04:54,059
Having good fortune.

1500
01:04:54,059 --> 01:04:57,089
To be "sincere and trustworthy" means to have a steady and faithful heart, free from frivolity and impetuousness.

1501
01:04:57,089 --> 01:05:01,011
It means being able to fulfill your duties diligently and persistently.

1502
01:05:01,011 --> 01:05:03,070
This is the prerequisite for waiting, as taught in the Xū hexagram.

1503
01:05:03,070 --> 01:05:08,036
When we hold fast to our beliefs, strive to stay on the right path, and patiently await the opportune moment,

1504
01:05:08,036 --> 01:05:10,040
our energy will continue to build and grow stronger.

1505
01:05:10,040 --> 01:05:12,082
our true needs will become clear in our hearts.

1506
01:05:12,082 --> 01:05:16,079
And the path to achieve it will also become clearer through this process of waiting and working hard.

1507
01:05:16,079 --> 01:05:19,056
Let's look back at the Monkey King's journey to seek immortality.

1508
01:05:19,056 --> 01:05:23,052
He starts off just messing around, acting like a king and a tyrant for three to five hundred years.

1509
01:05:23,052 --> 01:05:26,021
He watched wave after wave of monkeys die without feeling a thing.

1510
01:05:26,021 --> 01:05:28,065
Until one day, it suddenly hit him, and he was terrified.

1511
01:05:28,065 --> 01:05:32,037
Just then, a nearby NPC, the Long-armed Ape, reminds you that you should seek the secret of immortality.

1512
01:05:32,037 --> 01:05:34,050
Then, he voyaged far across two vast oceans.

1513
01:05:34,050 --> 01:05:38,016
After wandering the mortal world for eight or nine years, I've seen it all and found it wasn't worth it.

1514
01:05:38,016 --> 01:05:39,088
I've seen through all the ways of the mortal world.

1515
01:05:39,088 --> 01:05:41,086
When will the endless race for fame and fortune ever cease?

1516
01:05:41,086 --> 01:05:43,040
Waking early and sleeping late, with no freedom in sight!

1517
01:05:43,040 --> 01:05:46,016
Riding a donkey, one longs for a steed; a prime minister, for a king's crown.

1518
01:05:46,016 --> 01:05:47,078
Worried only about food and clothes, toiling away, why fear the Grim Reaper's call?

1519
01:05:47,078 --> 01:05:52,034
Striving for wealth and honor for their children and grandchildren, not a single one is willing to turn back!

1520
01:05:52,034 --> 01:05:55,028
After gaining ample experience and reflecting deeply,

1521
01:05:55,028 --> 01:05:57,028
The Monkey King had fortified his conviction.

1522
01:05:57,028 --> 01:05:58,044
I don't care what anyone says! I want to live forever!

1523
01:06:00,023 --> 01:06:03,073
Once your conviction is firm, it leads to the 'brilliant success' that comes from patient, steady effort.

1524
01:06:03,073 --> 01:06:05,096
This "sincerity" is the direction and the foundation.

1525
01:06:05,096 --> 01:06:09,046
Through hard work, you will reach a state of clarity and success, where everything flows smoothly and your efforts bear fruit.

1526
01:06:09,046 --> 01:06:11,070
This phrase, 'Guang Heng,' also serves as a reminder for us.

1527
01:06:11,070 --> 01:06:15,030
A true need is one that aligns with the core principles of light and progress.

1528
01:06:15,030 --> 01:06:18,028
Of course, just wanting 'Brightness and Success' and 'Having Faith' is not enough.

1529
01:06:18,028 --> 01:06:21,016
But if you're dead set on, say, murder and arson, that's a whole different story!

1530
01:06:21,016 --> 01:06:21,080
just 'smooth progress'

1531
01:06:21,080 --> 01:06:24,008
You also need the protection of core values.

1532
01:06:24,008 --> 01:06:25,062
This is what's meant by the 'steadfastness brings good fortune' that follows.

1533
01:06:25,062 --> 01:06:28,002
This is the red line for our needs and our waiting.

1534
01:06:28,002 --> 01:06:31,034
Only a wait and a pursuit that adhere to the right path will bring good fortune!

1535
01:06:31,034 --> 01:06:34,084
Those actions born of extravagance, reckless impulses, forcing growth, or a shortsighted pursuit of quick success...

1536
01:06:34,084 --> 01:06:36,086
will ultimately fall into the pit of danger.

1537
01:06:36,086 --> 01:06:38,094
The commentary in the Tuan Zhuan explains it as follows:

1538
01:06:38,094 --> 01:06:41,036
“With sincerity, it brings great success and is favorable. It is in the position of Heaven, to be correct and central.”

1539
01:06:41,036 --> 01:06:44,046
This means upholding the correct middle way, even when you've reached the highest position.

1540
01:06:44,046 --> 01:06:47,034
one must still follow the path of righteousness and not act recklessly.

1541
01:06:47,034 --> 01:06:50,012
So, once we have achieved 'sincerity, brightness, smoothness, correctness, and good fortune',

1542
01:06:50,012 --> 01:06:55,014
then you will be able to 'ford great rivers.' The phrase 'to ford great rivers' means to cross over perilous waters.

1543
01:06:55,014 --> 01:06:56,090
This is a common term in the I Ching.

1544
01:06:56,090 --> 01:06:59,012
It means to overcome great dangers and difficulties.

1545
01:06:59,012 --> 01:07:01,082
to accomplish great missions and achieve magnificent feats.

1546
01:07:01,082 --> 01:07:05,050
Desire itself is not a sin; what matters is whether it aligns with the right path.

1547
01:07:05,050 --> 01:07:07,006
But waiting is not an end in itself.

1548
01:07:07,006 --> 01:07:08,098
but a strategic response that respects the natural order of things.

1549
01:07:08,098 --> 01:07:11,050
The ultimate potential of the Xu Hexagram can be incredibly high.

1550
01:07:11,050 --> 01:07:13,096
It's about crossing great rivers to achieve great things!

1551
01:07:13,096 --> 01:07:19,021
It's that line from the Commentary on the Tuan, "Beneficial to cross great rivers, for there is merit in going forward!" If becoming a high official is purely for the sake of power and pleasure,

1552
01:07:19,021 --> 01:07:21,039
If it's purely for the sake of personal gain and pleasure,

1553
01:07:21,039 --> 01:07:22,068
Then that's not the right path. And notice, I said 'solely'.

1554
01:07:22,068 --> 01:07:24,070
Ah...

1555
01:07:24,070 --> 01:07:27,093
What is considered improper is to prioritize wielding power and enjoying its privileges above all else.

1556
01:07:27,093 --> 01:07:30,049
First of all, you should absolutely take advantage of the legitimate benefits and entitlements granted to you as a leader by the state.

1557
01:07:30,049 --> 01:07:36,097
If the desire and ambition to hold a high office are driven by the pursuit of one's political ideals,

1558
01:07:36,097 --> 01:07:39,041
and to do more tangible things for the country and the people.

1559
01:07:39,041 --> 01:07:40,091
That is a great and solemn vow.

1560
01:07:40,091 --> 01:07:42,057
Then it is time to cross the great river!

1561
01:07:42,057 --> 01:07:47,057
Then, we should dedicate our abilities to the great rejuvenation of the Chinese nation!

1562
01:07:47,094 --> 01:07:51,016
The first nine, the line statement reads: 'Waiting in the suburbs. Perseverance brings advantage. No blame.'

1563
01:07:51,016 --> 01:07:55,016
As the 'Tuan Zhuan' mentioned earlier, the character 'Xu' (需) means 'to wait'.

1564
01:07:55,016 --> 01:07:58,020
The so-called 'suburbs' refer to the area within the city walls, which is the state.

1565
01:07:58,020 --> 01:07:59,000
The area 100 li from the capital is the suburbs.

1566
01:07:59,000 --> 01:08:00,026
and fifty kilometers beyond the suburbs lies the wilderness.

1567
01:08:00,026 --> 01:08:02,052
Another interpretation is: 'Within the royal domain, a hundred li make up the suburbs, two hundred li make up a district, and three hundred li make up the wilderness.'

1568
01:08:02,052 --> 01:08:03,034
Two hundred li make a 'zhou'.

1569
01:08:03,034 --> 01:08:05,017
Waiting in the Suburbs.

1570
01:08:05,017 --> 01:08:08,045
Literally, it means to wait in the suburbs, far from the capital.

1571
01:08:08,045 --> 01:08:12,069
The deeper meaning is to wait in a place far from the lure of profit and desire.

1572
01:08:12,069 --> 01:08:16,056
The Commentary on the Images adds, "Waiting in the outskirts means not venturing into danger."

1573
01:08:16,056 --> 01:08:18,005
This is telling us that at this moment,

1574
01:08:18,005 --> 01:08:22,097
One should proactively seek safety in the buffer zone of the郊外,远离 danger.

1575
01:08:22,097 --> 01:08:25,020
and not to rashly advance into dangerous territory.

1576
01:08:25,020 --> 01:08:27,006
And notice, it's about actively avoiding risk.

1577
01:08:27,006 --> 01:08:31,067
This means not rashly heading towards the center of profit while taking on unnecessary risks.

1578
01:08:31,067 --> 01:08:35,059
The first nine is a yang line in a yang position. Although it is in the correct position, it is not centered.

1579
01:08:35,059 --> 01:08:39,031
Right from the start, you must always play it safe and let the dust settle.

1580
01:08:39,031 --> 01:08:42,079
Even the first nine at the bottom of the Qian hexagram is a 'hidden dragon, do not act'.

1581
01:08:42,079 --> 01:08:44,028
And it's also a yang line at the very bottom.

1582
01:08:44,028 --> 01:08:47,056
This line is also the one that is furthest from the danger of the upper trigram, Kan.

1583
01:08:47,056 --> 01:08:49,057
This is the safest stage of the entire hexagram.

1584
01:08:49,057 --> 01:08:50,063
So, why is it safe?

1585
01:08:50,063 --> 01:08:52,037
Because we're far from the center of the action.

1586
01:08:52,037 --> 01:08:54,047
We haven't gotten caught up in the fray.

1587
01:08:54,047 --> 01:08:58,025
And this so-called 'waiting in the suburbs' isn't just about physical space, either.

1588
01:08:58,025 --> 01:09:00,099
Instead, it means we can step outside the great web of desire.

1589
01:09:00,099 --> 01:09:02,037
and look at it from a sufficiently objective

1590
01:09:02,037 --> 01:09:05,086
and look at our needs objectively from a detached perspective.

1591
01:09:05,086 --> 01:09:07,075
Is it a genuine necessity?

1592
01:09:07,075 --> 01:09:09,069
Even if it's a genuine, essential need,

1593
01:09:09,069 --> 01:09:12,055
we also need to carefully consider our own vulnerability at this stage.

1594
01:09:12,055 --> 01:09:15,079
Is it really necessary to sign up for the rat race?

1595
01:09:15,079 --> 01:09:19,036
It's like, we all know that having a place to call our own is a basic necessity.

1596
01:09:19,036 --> 01:09:20,046
This is a basic need.

1597
01:09:20,046 --> 01:09:24,002
But when we've just entered the workforce, just started our first job,

1598
01:09:24,002 --> 01:09:27,090
But is this a need that has to be met right away?

1599
01:09:27,090 --> 01:09:32,064
Is it really worth taking on a loan for this 'essential need', and from then on, not daring to take any risks in life?

1600
01:09:32,064 --> 01:09:35,042
Once you've bought this house, you won't dare to switch jobs easily.

1601
01:09:35,042 --> 01:09:37,028
What if your company doesn't grow?

1602
01:09:37,028 --> 01:09:40,000
What if there aren't any good jobs near your little place?

1603
01:09:40,000 --> 01:09:41,052
You're completely tied down.

1604
01:09:41,052 --> 01:09:44,045
So, wouldn't renting a place be a better idea for now?

1605
01:09:44,045 --> 01:09:46,069
So, let's delay satisfying this essential need.

1606
01:09:46,069 --> 01:09:49,017


1607
01:09:49,017 --> 01:09:51,016
Once we've turned that first pot of gold into something that generates a continuous stream of income for us,

1608
01:09:51,016 --> 01:09:56,032
Wouldn't it be better to satisfy this essential need after we've acquired the productive assets that generate a steady income?

1609
01:09:56,032 --> 01:09:59,024
we should examine this matter with the attitude of 'needing at the outskirts'.

1610
01:09:59,024 --> 01:10:01,039
Then we can make a clear judgment.

1611
01:10:01,039 --> 01:10:03,041
If we start thinking about the rise and fall of housing prices, about investing and speculating,

1612
01:10:03,041 --> 01:10:06,087
Once you start mixing in things like wedding dowries and all that,

1613
01:10:06,087 --> 01:10:09,089
Then it's no longer a matter of 'needing in the suburbs.' We'll just get overwhelmed and confused.

1614
01:10:09,089 --> 01:10:12,044
Like we said, we have the power to act.

1615
01:10:12,044 --> 01:10:17,044
This is like the First Nine of the Qian hexagram, which represents 'Heaven's ceaseless motion.' Proactively avoiding risks is also a powerful form of action.

1616
01:10:17,044 --> 01:10:19,064
Because to克制欲望 and 克制焦虑 means we've conquered ourselves.

1617
01:10:19,064 --> 01:10:22,077
This means we've conquered ourselves.

1618
01:10:22,077 --> 01:10:25,028
To conquer an enemy is hard, but to conquer yourself is even harder.

1619
01:10:25,028 --> 01:10:27,033
Throughout history, there have been very few undefeated generals.

1620
01:10:27,033 --> 01:10:31,056
Because the reason they always win is that they 'first make themselves invincible, and then wait for the enemy to be vulnerable.'

1621
01:10:31,056 --> 01:10:34,020
We need to hardwire this attitude into our operating system.

1622
01:10:34,020 --> 01:10:36,070
This is also what the following line means: 'Perseverance brings no blame.'

1623
01:10:36,070 --> 01:10:39,072
When we hold fast to our righteous path with perseverance,

1624
01:10:39,072 --> 01:10:40,096
we can avoid disaster.

1625
01:10:40,096 --> 01:10:44,043
Notice, it's 'no blame,' 'no disaster,' not 'great fortune.'

1626
01:10:44,043 --> 01:10:45,021
What does that mean?

1627
01:10:45,021 --> 01:10:48,003
Desires and needs, no matter how essential they may seem,

1628
01:10:48,003 --> 01:10:50,013
When it comes down to it, it's all about vanity and self-interest.

1629
01:10:50,013 --> 01:10:52,027
It's what everyone is fighting over.

1630
01:10:52,027 --> 01:10:55,023
While they are the very source of life, they are also the root of all calamity.

1631
01:10:55,023 --> 01:10:58,031
We must guard our hearts at all times.

1632
01:10:58,031 --> 01:11:01,025
The second nine: In the sand, there is some talk, but in the end, it is auspicious.

1633
01:11:01,025 --> 01:11:02,044
The ultimate sand.

1634
01:11:02,044 --> 01:11:04,006
The character 'sha' (沙) refers to a shallow shoal or bank by the water.

1635
01:11:04,006 --> 01:11:06,002
The ground here is loose and prone to sinking.

1636
01:11:06,002 --> 01:11:07,026
But you won't sink in too deep.

1637
01:11:07,026 --> 01:11:08,004
But it's a fleeting danger.

1638
01:11:08,004 --> 01:11:12,076
This means we're getting closer to the peril of the Kan trigram than the '郊' (suburbs) of the initial nine.

1639
01:11:12,076 --> 01:11:14,094
But you're not in danger yet.

1640
01:11:14,094 --> 01:11:18,040
At most, it's like the saying, 'If you play with fire, you're bound to get burned.'

1641
01:11:18,040 --> 01:11:20,057
When we no longer want to just watch from a distance,

1642
01:11:20,057 --> 01:11:22,038
Or, to put it another way, they've already found their direction.

1643
01:11:22,038 --> 01:11:24,046
and their strength is also greater than that of the initial Nine.

1644
01:11:24,046 --> 01:11:26,066
So, we start to approach our goal, testing the waters.

1645
01:11:26,066 --> 01:11:29,052
But at this point, they are still clear-headed and self-aware.

1646
01:11:29,052 --> 01:11:32,022
It's not yet time to dive headfirst into the deep end.

1647
01:11:32,022 --> 01:11:34,052
Instead, you should test the waters at the edge of the danger zone.

1648
01:11:36,076 --> 01:11:39,048
This is about crossing the river by feeling the stones step-by-step. The following line, 'minor criticism, but ultimate good fortune,' means...

1649
01:11:39,048 --> 01:11:42,066
Because when you get close to the gains, you also get close to the danger.

1650
01:11:42,066 --> 01:11:45,024
This will inevitably draw criticism, gossip, blame, and condemnation.

1651
01:11:45,024 --> 01:11:46,082
But you don't need to worry too much about it.

1652
01:11:46,082 --> 01:11:48,090
In the end, we will achieve a favorable outcome.

1653
01:11:48,090 --> 01:11:51,034
Now, you might be wondering why that is.

1654
01:11:51,034 --> 01:11:53,078
The Commentary on the Images provides further explanation.

1655
01:11:53,078 --> 01:11:56,093
Waiting on the sandy ford means being in the middle.

1656
01:11:56,093 --> 01:11:58,065
Although there may be some initial criticism, it will ultimately lead to good fortune.

1657
01:11:58,065 --> 01:12:00,082
The character '衍' (yǎn) is composed of '行' (xíng), meaning 'to walk' or 'to go,' on the outside, and '水' (shuǐ), meaning 'water,' on the inside.

1658
01:12:00,082 --> 01:12:04,034
This signifies that the river channel is unobstructed, allowing the water to flow freely.

1659
01:12:04,034 --> 01:12:07,051
The Shuowen Jiezi states, "To 'Yan' is for all waters to converge upon the sea."

1660
01:12:07,051 --> 01:12:12,068
This idea of all rivers flowing into the sea was then extended to mean 'to extend, to spread, and to be abundant'.

1661
01:12:12,068 --> 01:12:15,057
This 'centrality' means that the second line, a yang line, is in a yin position.

1662
01:12:15,057 --> 01:12:16,062
Although it is not in its proper position, it is centered.

1663
01:12:16,062 --> 01:12:18,036
But the second line, it's in the central position.

1664
01:12:18,036 --> 01:12:22,009
Generally speaking, for any line, whether Yin or Yang, being in the central position means things won't turn out too badly.

1665
01:12:22,009 --> 01:12:26,053
The commentary in the Xiang Zhuan describes this state as being like waiting on a shallow sandbank, right on the edge of danger.

1666
01:12:26,053 --> 01:12:29,059
This means there's plenty of room and a wide margin for error.

1667
01:12:29,059 --> 01:12:31,042
so it won't lead to any major dangers.

1668
01:12:31,042 --> 01:12:33,057
If you take a small step forward and feel like something's not right, you can immediately pull back.

1669
01:12:33,057 --> 01:12:35,012
and pull back right away.

1670
01:12:35,012 --> 01:12:37,042
Since we've started moving towards the center of the action,

1671
01:12:37,042 --> 01:12:40,080
Then you're doomed to step into a battlefield of slander and a sea of conflict.

1672
01:12:40,080 --> 01:12:42,092
This 'minor criticism' is simply unavoidable.

1673
01:12:42,092 --> 01:12:45,082
And don't think it gets any easier. The further you go, the more it's going to hurt.

1674
01:12:45,082 --> 01:12:48,034
He who is praised by all is also slandered by all.

1675
01:12:48,034 --> 01:12:51,082
Being the subject of some gossip is an inevitable price for anyone who gains an advantage.

1676
01:12:51,082 --> 01:12:53,062
This assurance of 'ultimate good fortune' must be because...

1677
01:12:53,062 --> 01:12:57,078
Given your position and mindset at this moment, you're truly in a safe spot.

1678
01:12:57,078 --> 01:12:59,042
Because you are 'advancing from a central position'.

1679
01:12:59,042 --> 01:13:03,016
You have a buffer, both in terms of physical space and your state of mind.

1680
01:13:03,016 --> 01:13:05,078
The sand, the shallows by the water, act as a buffer zone.

1681
01:13:05,078 --> 01:13:09,024
So even if a huge wave suddenly crashes in, it won't be strong enough to sweep you away.

1682
01:13:09,024 --> 01:13:11,010
It's not like the next line, "Waiting in the mud."

1683
01:13:11,010 --> 01:13:14,010
But once you're stuck in the mud, it's not so easy to pull yourself out.

1684
01:13:14,010 --> 01:13:16,078
The point is, you can always pull back without fear.

1685
01:13:16,078 --> 01:13:20,079
This safety buffer also helps us maintain a balanced and centered mindset, free from extremism.

1686
01:13:20,079 --> 01:13:24,019
Not be provoked by petty remarks, nor argue with rumors.

1687
01:13:24,019 --> 01:13:26,066
Resolve conflicts with a tolerant and open mind.

1688
01:13:26,066 --> 01:13:29,054
Petty gossip is never a real obstacle.

1689
01:13:29,054 --> 01:13:31,064
As long as you don't let it mess with your head,

1690
01:13:31,064 --> 01:13:33,078
as long as you stick to your own pace and feel your way forward cautiously.

1691
01:13:35,007 --> 01:13:38,067
petty talk will never escalate into a major disaster.

1692
01:13:38,067 --> 01:13:39,069
Just take it as a bit of fun.

1693
01:13:39,069 --> 01:13:43,018
Of course, having come this far, we still need to be mentally prepared.

1694
01:13:43,018 --> 01:13:44,056
From now on, there will always be people talking.

1695
01:13:44,056 --> 01:13:49,051
It's a relentless assault, one wave crashing in before you can even catch your breath from the last.

1696
01:13:49,051 --> 01:13:50,079
Just don't let it get to you.

1697
01:13:50,079 --> 01:13:53,005
If you get too hung up on what other people say,

1698
01:13:53,005 --> 01:13:55,027
You'd better just turn around and head back to the 'suburbs'.

1699
01:13:55,027 --> 01:13:56,099
You're still not quite ready yet.

1700
01:13:56,099 --> 01:13:59,012
You need to go back and temper your mind a bit more.

1701
01:13:59,040 --> 01:14:03,040
The line text for the third nine says, "Waiting in the mud brings robbers near." This phrase, "waiting in the mud"...

1702
01:14:03,040 --> 01:14:05,060
Now, you've reached the muddy banks by the water.

1703
01:14:05,060 --> 01:14:07,084
One more step and you're in the river.

1704
01:14:07,084 --> 01:14:11,057
At this point, any big wave could come and sweep you right into the river.

1705
01:14:11,057 --> 01:14:13,090
Or even, you could just slip and fall right into the river.

1706
01:14:13,090 --> 01:14:17,068
So, you might wonder, why is the trigram 'Kan', which is associated with the water element in the Five Elements, defined as 'danger'?

1707
01:14:17,068 --> 01:14:19,020
Now, when you guys go to the river to hang out today,

1708
01:14:19,020 --> 01:14:20,070
Even if you're standing really close to the river,

1709
01:14:20,070 --> 01:14:22,006
we usually don't think much of it.

1710
01:14:22,006 --> 01:14:24,094
That's because the rivers we see in parks or around us today have usually been renovated.

1711
01:14:24,094 --> 01:14:26,046
They've usually been renovated.

1712
01:14:26,046 --> 01:14:29,060
The embankments slope gently into the river, providing a gradual transition.

1713
01:14:29,060 --> 01:14:30,064
But in ancient times,

1714
01:14:30,064 --> 01:14:34,065
Many rivers hide traps that can suddenly cause you to fall.

1715
01:14:34,065 --> 01:14:36,059
Perhaps you're just a single step away from the shore,

1716
01:14:36,059 --> 01:14:38,028
But if you take that one step forward, you'll find out.

1717
01:14:38,028 --> 01:14:41,086
The riverbed suddenly drops off vertically, as if it's been sliced by a knife.

1718
01:14:41,086 --> 01:14:45,036
In an instant, the water goes from knee-deep to two, three, or even more than ten meters deep!

1719
01:14:45,036 --> 01:14:52,048
From the initial Nine to the third Nine, we see a gradual progression from the 'suburbs,' a distant risk, to the 'sand,' a closer one, and finally to the 'mud,' where the danger is imminent.

1720
01:14:52,048 --> 01:14:55,062
“Waiting in the mud” means we have now reached a point of considerable danger.

1721
01:14:55,062 --> 01:14:58,093
This is a critical point of safety and danger, where your footing is unstable and you can easily fall into a predicament with no easy escape.

1722
01:14:58,093 --> 01:15:00,003
But despite the danger,

1723
01:15:00,003 --> 01:15:02,087
that doesn't mean we shouldn't move forward.

1724
01:15:02,087 --> 01:15:05,077
The lower trigram of the Xū Hexagram is the Qian Hexagram, symbolizing the vigorous movement of Heaven.

1725
01:15:05,077 --> 01:15:09,001
It's about being proactive while you wait.

1726
01:15:09,001 --> 01:15:11,016
Remember what the Tuan Zhuan says?

1727
01:15:11,016 --> 01:15:13,040
The character 'xū' in 'xū guà' means 'to need' or 'to require', and it signifies that danger lies ahead.

1728
01:15:13,040 --> 01:15:16,026
If one is firm and strong, yet does not fall into the pit, then one's path will not be one of hardship and poverty.

1729
01:15:16,026 --> 01:15:18,086
It's not telling us to just wait endlessly.

1730
01:15:18,086 --> 01:15:20,062
Once we've carefully discerned the situation,

1731
01:15:20,062 --> 01:15:22,044
Once you've identified the right opportunity and direction,

1732
01:15:22,044 --> 01:15:25,086
We have to keep moving forward. We can't let the fear of choking stop us from eating.

1733
01:15:25,086 --> 01:15:28,000
You can't let the fear of a cricket's chirp stop you from planting your crops.

1734
01:15:28,000 --> 01:15:30,036
But any action you take will inevitably involve some risk.

1735
01:15:30,036 --> 01:15:33,064
But as long as we have the right methods and resources to handle them, we'll be fine.

1736
01:15:33,064 --> 01:15:36,034
We'll head for the section of the river that's the least risky.

1737
01:15:36,034 --> 01:15:40,017
If we want to cross the Yellow River, we can just take the Pujin Ferry. That's a perfectly good option.

1738
01:15:40,017 --> 01:15:43,059
We don't have to insist on crossing at Longmen Ferry, the one from the legend of the carp leaping over the dragon gate.

1739
01:15:43,059 --> 01:15:45,095
and try to brute-force our way through the thundering, massive Yellow River.

1740
01:15:45,095 --> 01:15:48,089
Our ultimate goal is to ford the great river, to achieve something significant.

1741
01:15:48,089 --> 01:15:51,051
It's about taking calculated risks to achieve your goal.

1742
01:15:51,051 --> 01:15:53,048
All we need to do is get to the Guanzhong region.

1743
01:15:53,048 --> 01:15:55,072
Ultimately, we're here to do something big!

1744
01:15:55,072 --> 01:15:59,092
Crossing the river is the goal, but our real purpose is to be the first to enter the Guanzhong region and claim the throne.

1745
01:15:59,092 --> 01:16:01,012
Just getting across the river is all that matters.

1746
01:16:01,012 --> 01:16:05,004
Don't you dare go running off to Longmen Ferry to risk your neck for a chance at life!

1747
01:16:05,004 --> 01:16:07,040
When we are just one step away from the gate of profit,

1748
01:16:07,040 --> 01:16:12,004
This means that all sorts of misfortunes, like robbers, legal troubles, and natural disasters, are about to befall us.

1749
01:16:12,004 --> 01:16:13,063
In other words, 'bringing the robbers to your door.'

1750
01:16:13,063 --> 01:16:14,079
So, when all sorts of external calamities come knocking,

1751
01:16:14,079 --> 01:16:15,039
And once they arrive,

1752
01:16:15,039 --> 01:16:16,053
So, what should we do?

1753
01:16:16,053 --> 01:16:18,005
This is what the 'Xiang Zhuan' says:

1754
01:16:18,005 --> 01:16:24,033
To be stuck in the mud means disaster is coming from the outside. If you bring trouble upon yourself, you must be cautious and respectful to avoid defeat.

1755
01:16:24,033 --> 01:16:29,086
This 'reverence' means to be in awe. It's about having a deep reverence for the laws of nature, for boundaries, and for the risks of disaster.

1756
01:16:29,086 --> 01:16:31,022
Do not act recklessly just because you are powerful.

1757
01:16:31,022 --> 01:16:32,059
Don't leave things to chance.

1758
01:16:32,059 --> 01:16:33,071
And 'Shen' means being cautious.

1759
01:16:33,071 --> 01:16:36,044
It means making steady, solid progress without rushing forward, taking every step with caution.

1760
01:16:36,044 --> 01:16:38,090
Cultivate reverence to govern your mind, and practice prudence to govern your actions.

1761
01:16:38,090 --> 01:16:40,042
By upholding this attitude,

1762
01:16:40,042 --> 01:16:43,021
This is how you can remain invincible amidst all kinds of dangers.

1763
01:16:43,021 --> 01:16:46,087
After Liu Bang fought his way into the Guanzhong region, he got a big head and lost his cool.

1764
01:16:46,087 --> 01:16:48,077
He really started thinking he was the king of Guanzhong.

1765
01:16:48,077 --> 01:16:51,052
Then he blocked the Hangu Pass, nearly getting himself killed in the process.

1766
01:16:51,052 --> 01:16:53,040
His state at that moment was exactly 'Waiting in the Mud'.

1767
01:16:53,040 --> 01:16:54,054
He's already in too deep.

1768
01:16:54,054 --> 01:16:56,068
What was truly remarkable was his ability to slam on the brakes and retreat to Bashang.

1769
01:16:56,068 --> 01:16:59,006
He retreated to Bashang with a posture of reverence and caution.

1770
01:16:59,006 --> 01:17:00,064
He pulled off a series of incredibly difficult maneuvers.

1771
01:17:00,064 --> 01:17:03,023
Xiang Bo and Xiang Yu's two rounds of crisis management

1772
01:17:03,023 --> 01:17:05,059
Before we can charge towards our ultimate goal, we all go through a phase of being 'bogged down in the mud'.

1773
01:17:05,059 --> 01:17:07,020
There's always a phase of trudging through the mud.

1774
01:17:07,020 --> 01:17:09,026
During this stage, we need to keep a low profile.

1775
01:17:09,026 --> 01:17:10,048
and keep a low profile.

1776
01:17:10,048 --> 01:17:13,048
Create the impression that you've just happened upon the riverbank by chance.

1777
01:17:13,048 --> 01:17:17,012
This way, you can avoid being overwhelmed by blows from all sides before you're ready.

1778
01:17:17,012 --> 01:17:19,006
Getting taken out before you even step into the ring.

1779
01:17:19,006 --> 01:17:22,067
As for the officials and bandits lying in wait, looking for trouble,

1780
01:17:22,067 --> 01:17:25,085
Respond with a respectful and cautious attitude, neither humble nor arrogant.

1781
01:17:25,085 --> 01:17:29,047
After all, there's no real proof that we've actually entered the fray.

1782
01:17:29,047 --> 01:17:32,016
As long as there's no hard evidence, you can always talk your way out of it.

1783
01:17:32,016 --> 01:17:34,012
I, Liu Bang, might have courted death for a moment there.

1784
01:17:34,012 --> 01:17:35,072
But I pulled back.

1785
01:17:35,072 --> 01:17:38,084
I'm just here, exercising caution and self-control, waiting for my dear Secretary Xiang.

1786
01:17:38,084 --> 01:17:40,048
So you can't make a move on me.

1787
01:17:40,048 --> 01:17:42,018
Whether you're strategizing against enemies on the battlefield or scheming for a position in the political arena,

1788
01:17:43,064 --> 01:17:46,042
or in the preparatory phase of charging ahead to make a profit in the business world.

1789
01:17:46,042 --> 01:17:48,030
The principle is the same across the board.

1790
01:17:48,030 --> 01:17:49,096
Six in the Fourth Place.

1791
01:17:49,096 --> 01:17:51,097
The line statement says: 'Waiting in the blood, one emerges from the pit.'

1792
01:17:51,097 --> 01:17:52,079
In the last line, it was before we had even stepped into the deep waters of the river of profit.

1793
01:17:52,079 --> 01:17:55,081
This is before we've even stepped into the deep waters of the great river of profit.

1794
01:17:55,081 --> 01:17:57,013
And just as they got their feet wet, they had already 'attracted the bandits'.

1795
01:17:57,013 --> 01:17:58,067
and you've already invited the bandits to come and get you.

1796
01:17:58,067 --> 01:18:01,083
Xiang Yu had already mocked him, saying, "Oh, so the King of Guanzhong has arrived."

1797
01:18:01,083 --> 01:18:02,008
Hey.

1798
01:18:02,008 --> 01:18:05,030
Now, we have officially entered the core peril of the upper trigram, Kan, which represents danger.

1799
01:18:05,030 --> 01:18:07,024
So, it's time to get out the knives.

1800
01:18:07,024 --> 01:18:09,054
This line, 'needing to emerge from a pit of blood,'

1801
01:18:09,054 --> 01:18:12,038
This describes the intensifying conflicts of interest and escalating contradictions at this stage.

1802
01:18:12,038 --> 01:18:14,062
The situation has escalated to a perilous point, one where blood will be shed.

1803
01:18:14,062 --> 01:18:16,074
Unlike the first three lines where the danger was external,

1804
01:18:16,074 --> 01:18:18,038
Instead, the danger is now upon us.

1805
01:18:18,038 --> 01:18:21,056
At this point, no one can save us. We need to 'emerge from the pit'.

1806
01:18:21,056 --> 01:18:24,016
We have to find our own way out of the danger.

1807
01:18:24,016 --> 01:18:25,070
So, how do we get out?

1808
01:18:25,070 --> 01:18:27,056
This is how the Commentary on the Images explains it.

1809
01:18:27,056 --> 01:18:29,080
One must wait amidst the blood, and listen by following the current.

1810
01:18:29,080 --> 01:18:33,028
Here, "顺应" (shùn yìng) means to go with the flow, rather than going against the current or being rigid.

1811
01:18:33,028 --> 01:18:37,031
This line, the fourth six, is a yin line in a yin position, which emphasizes the importance of going with the flow.

1812
01:18:37,031 --> 01:18:39,049
At this point, we've entered the deep end.

1813
01:18:39,049 --> 01:18:42,053
If we charge head-on against the perilous current

1814
01:18:42,053 --> 01:18:44,050
Either we'll quickly exhaust all our strength,

1815
01:18:44,050 --> 01:18:47,000
or, without even touching them, our boat capsizes and we're done for.

1816
01:18:47,000 --> 01:18:51,085
Any attempt to be reckless or confrontational will only cause us to lose our strength even faster.

1817
01:18:51,085 --> 01:18:53,021
and sink us deeper and deeper.

1818
01:18:53,021 --> 01:18:54,071
We need to conserve our energy.

1819
01:18:54,071 --> 01:18:57,091
Only by moving with the current can you avoid being swallowed by the treacherous waves.

1820
01:18:57,091 --> 01:19:00,028
We need to be clear about the advantage we're trying to gain.

1821
01:19:00,028 --> 01:19:03,056
If you want to cross this river, you'll find yourself surrounded by a massive crowd of competitors.

1822
01:19:03,056 --> 01:19:08,030
Countless heroes and outstanding figures have plunged into these perilous waters to do battle.

1823
01:19:08,030 --> 01:19:11,043
At this very moment, no matter how powerful we as individuals might be,

1824
01:19:11,043 --> 01:19:13,071
is never enough against the tide of history.

1825
01:19:13,071 --> 01:19:15,039
I mean, Xiang Yu was an absolute beast in a fight.

1826
01:19:15,039 --> 01:19:18,007
He was the one who, by his own strength, changed the course of the late Qin dynasty.

1827
01:19:18,007 --> 01:19:20,040
But in the end, he was defeated by Liu Bang, Han Xin, Ying Bu, and Chen Ping.

1828
01:19:20,040 --> 01:19:24,042
And this gang of former underlings? They were all drowned out in the great river of the late Qin dynasty.

1829
01:19:24,042 --> 01:19:27,044
Even though he was victorious in every battle, he was ultimately defeated by his own string of successes.

1830
01:19:27,044 --> 01:19:30,010
The use of the character 'tīng' (听) in the phrase 'shùn yǐ tīng' (顺以听) is particularly brilliant.

1831
01:19:30,010 --> 01:19:31,046
First, let's look at the hexagram's imagery.

1832
01:19:31,046 --> 01:19:32,088
According to the 'Shuogua Zhuan' or 'Discussion of the Trigrams' from the 'I Ching',

1833
01:19:32,088 --> 01:19:35,090
Qian represents the head, Kun the abdomen, Zhen the foot, and Xun the thigh.

1834
01:19:35,090 --> 01:19:38,076
Kan corresponds to the ear, Li to the eye, Gen to the hand, and Dui to the mouth.

1835
01:19:38,076 --> 01:19:40,090
So, it says here that the Kan trigram represents the ear.

1836
01:19:40,090 --> 01:19:43,008
So, the character for 'listening' is a perfect match for the trigram's symbolism from the very beginning.

1837
01:19:43,008 --> 01:19:46,036
Being in the peril of Kan is like being plunged into a land of darkness.

1838
01:19:46,036 --> 01:19:47,094
Your eyes can't see the whole picture,

1839
01:19:47,094 --> 01:19:49,004
and can't tell which way to go.

1840
01:19:49,004 --> 01:19:52,086
That's why it's crucial to calm down and listen carefully.

1841
01:19:52,086 --> 01:19:57,045
The essence of "listening" is that the more dangerous the environment, the more you need to remain calm.

1842
01:19:57,045 --> 01:20:00,001
Secondly, "listening" isn't about passive conformity or just going with the flow.

1843
01:20:00,001 --> 01:20:01,019
but rather, it's about discerning right from wrong.

1844
01:20:01,019 --> 01:20:02,037
It means to perceive the subtle and profound.

1845
01:20:02,037 --> 01:20:05,024


1846
01:20:05,024 --> 01:20:08,042
The first is appearance, the second is speech, the third is observation, the fourth is listening, and the fifth is thought.

1847
01:20:08,042 --> 01:20:09,030
Demeanor should be reverent, speech should be compliant, and vision should be clear.

1848
01:20:09,030 --> 01:20:11,012
Speech should be compliant, and vision should be clear.

1849
01:20:11,012 --> 01:20:12,091
Listening leads to discernment, and thinking leads to wisdom.

1850
01:20:12,091 --> 01:20:15,097
Respectfulness leads to solemnity, compliance leads to order, and clarity leads to wisdom.

1851
01:20:15,097 --> 01:20:18,008
Cleverness leads to strategy, and wisdom leads to sagehood.

1852
01:20:18,008 --> 01:20:21,098
The character '听' (tīng), which means 'to listen' or 'to hear', implies being intelligent, discerning, and perceptive to the finest detail.

1853
01:20:21,098 --> 01:20:23,000
For instance, the term 'judging a case'.

1854
01:20:23,000 --> 01:20:25,099
This is the principle of 'adjudicating the lawsuits of the people with the Five Punishments, and supplementing the punishments with intelligence and reports.'

1855
01:20:25,099 --> 01:20:27,087


1856
01:20:27,087 --> 01:20:28,089
For instance, "attending to governance."

1857
01:20:28,089 --> 01:20:33,046
This means that when the king holds court to govern, the ministers are to support and listen to his judgments. The same principle applies when the king receives reports from the four directions.

1858
01:20:33,046 --> 01:20:35,024
What's emphasized is a state of complete clarity.

1859
01:20:35,024 --> 01:20:37,042
Take, for example, that famous saying from Confucius.

1860
01:20:37,042 --> 01:20:39,012
At fifteen, I set my heart on learning.

1861
01:20:39,012 --> 01:20:39,092
At thirty, I stood firm. At forty, I had no more doubts.

1862
01:20:39,092 --> 01:20:40,082
At forty, I had no more doubts.

1863
01:20:40,082 --> 01:20:41,090
At fifty, I knew the mandate of Heaven.

1864
01:20:41,090 --> 01:20:45,035
At sixty, my ears were attuned. At seventy, I could follow my heart's desire without transgressing the boundaries.

1865
01:20:45,035 --> 01:20:47,087
Now, this 'being receptive to all sounds' isn't just about getting old.

1866
01:20:47,087 --> 01:20:48,079
and become a cheerful old man who can take anything in stride.

1867
01:20:48,079 --> 01:20:49,080
So, the old man is just having a good time, huh?

1868
01:20:49,080 --> 01:20:51,084
Instead, it builds upon the idea of "knowing the will of Heaven at fifty."

1869
01:20:51,084 --> 01:20:54,064
and serves as the key to understanding "At seventy, I can follow my heart's desire without transgressing the boundaries."

1870
01:20:54,064 --> 01:20:57,088
It means, 'When your ears are attuned, you hear words and understand their subtle meaning.'

1871
01:20:57,088 --> 01:21:00,000
It's that after hearing just one sentence from someone,

1872
01:21:00,000 --> 01:21:03,002
You get what they really mean without even having to think twice.

1873
01:21:03,002 --> 01:21:04,066
I get what he's trying to say.

1874
01:21:04,066 --> 01:21:07,098
The other person might not even realize they've already shown their hand.

1875
01:21:07,098 --> 01:21:10,077
And the 60-year-old master has already seen through it all.

1876
01:21:10,077 --> 01:21:14,072
This state of 'ear-obedience' is precisely what is meant here by 'obeying to listen'.

1877
01:21:14,072 --> 01:21:18,004
So, the use of the word 'listen' here is just brilliant.

1878
01:21:18,004 --> 01:21:20,094
For instance, 'to follow with compliance,' 'to avoid with compliance,' 'to receive with compliance.'

1879
01:21:20,094 --> 01:21:22,014
or "Shun to achieve"

1880
01:21:22,014 --> 01:21:24,078
it just doesn't have that flavor of wisdom.

1881
01:21:24,078 --> 01:21:26,057
To be 'needing in blood' is to listen with compliance.

1882
01:21:26,057 --> 01:21:28,052
Whether it's 'yielding' or 'listening'

1883
01:21:28,052 --> 01:21:31,039
Both of these, in fact, emphasize the idea of waiting, which is the essence of 'Xu'.

1884
01:21:31,039 --> 01:21:32,089
In the torrent of danger, your first priority is to preserve your own strength.

1885
01:21:32,089 --> 01:21:34,075
The first priority is to preserve your own strength.

1886
01:21:34,075 --> 01:21:36,015
Follow the prevailing trend with a calm mind.

1887
01:21:36,015 --> 01:21:41,008
and use a sharp mind to analyze the situation and find a way to safety.

1888
01:21:41,008 --> 01:21:46,043
After Han Xin argued that this was the only window of opportunity to conquer the empire, and that if they faltered now, they would lose their momentum forever,

1889
01:21:46,043 --> 01:21:49,027
Liu Bang was able to ignore the advice of Zhang Liang, whose suggestions had always been foolproof, and instead rapidly advanced to pacify the Three Qins.

1890
01:21:49,027 --> 01:21:49,047
sword

1891
01:21:49,047 --> 01:21:51,013
and swiftly reclaimed the Three Qins.

1892
01:21:51,013 --> 01:21:55,039
After the disastrous defeat at Pengcheng, when Zhang Liang revealed who the three heroes for conquering Chu were,

1893
01:21:55,039 --> 01:21:58,080
Liu Bang then swiftly redeployed Han Xin to the north to open up a second front.

1894
01:21:58,080 --> 01:22:01,090
He went to Huainan to persuade Ying Bu, and to Liang to secure Peng Yue's allegiance.

1895
01:22:01,090 --> 01:22:06,036
When Han Xin, after conquering Qi, demanded to be made the acting King of Qi, and Liu Bang was, in theory, powerless to refuse,

1896
01:22:06,036 --> 01:22:08,041
He was magnanimous enough to make him a true king.

1897
01:22:08,041 --> 01:22:10,051
When he broke the treaty at the Hong Canal and pursued the Western Chu forces,

1898
01:22:10,051 --> 01:22:14,010
When faced with the threats of Peng Yue and Han Xin, who were holding out for a price before committing their troops,

1899
01:22:14,010 --> 01:22:16,054
He was able to swallow his pride and grant them territories.

1900
01:22:16,054 --> 01:22:18,040
When the final defeat of Chu was at hand,

1901
01:22:18,040 --> 01:22:24,048
Liu Bang was able to swallow his pride, hand over command, and let the God of War have his ultimate showdown with the Hegemon-King.

1902
01:22:24,048 --> 01:22:27,065
The more danger you're in, the more you need to keep a cool head.

1903
01:22:27,065 --> 01:22:29,067
Go with the flow and spot the opportunities.

1904
01:22:29,067 --> 01:22:31,009
Don't just foolishly and blindly charge ahead!

1905
01:22:31,009 --> 01:22:32,084
Instead of just charging in like a fool.

1906
01:22:32,084 --> 01:22:34,078
You must constantly break down the components,

1907
01:22:34,078 --> 01:22:37,034
and continuously unite the widest range of forces.

1908
01:22:37,034 --> 01:22:39,052
and constantly use your superior forces to avoid the strong and attack the weak.

1909
01:22:39,052 --> 01:22:42,031
To wait amidst bloodshed means to follow the situation and listen to its dictates.

1910
01:22:42,031 --> 01:22:46,009
This is the principle and wisdom that our ancestors have long since summarized for us.

1911
01:22:46,009 --> 01:22:48,037
From the hidden perils of a distant swamp, to the treacherous sands in plain sight.

1912
01:22:48,037 --> 01:22:49,037
then to the manifest mud,

1913
01:22:49,037 --> 01:22:50,059
and finally, to the blood that seeps in.

1914
01:22:50,059 --> 01:22:52,009
If you do take the risk and succeed,

1915
01:22:52,009 --> 01:22:53,001
It is advantageous to cross the great river.

1916
01:22:53,001 --> 01:22:54,047
Alright, next up we have the Ninth Five.

1917
01:22:54,047 --> 01:22:55,091
“Waiting upon wine and food, it is favorable to be steadfast and upright.”

1918
01:22:55,091 --> 01:22:58,019
First, let's talk about what 'wine and food' actually means here.

1919
01:22:58,019 --> 01:23:03,088
This line isn't saying that after you've profited from a risky situation, you can just kick back, relax, and party all the way to the bank.

1920
01:23:03,088 --> 01:23:07,056
In ancient societies, "food and wine" were the central elements of sacrificial rites and hospitality.

1921
01:23:07,056 --> 01:23:09,088
It's not just about 'Things in their infancy must be nurtured; therefore, it is followed by the Hexagram of Xu.'

1922
01:23:09,088 --> 01:23:12,056
nor is it just the way of eating for sustenance and survival, as mentioned in the 'Xu' hexagram.

1923
01:23:12,056 --> 01:23:15,012
but also represents the rites of sacrificial and the feasting of sages.

1924
01:23:15,012 --> 01:23:16,066
and a governance that benefits all people.

1925
01:23:16,066 --> 01:23:18,082
It's not merely a symbol of indulgence.

1926
01:23:18,082 --> 01:23:23,014
So, to understand a pre-Qin classic like the I Ching, you have to compare it with other famous works from the same period.

1927
01:23:23,014 --> 01:23:25,022
For instance, the "Record of Music" in the Book of Rites states the following.

1928
01:23:25,022 --> 01:23:26,042
I'm not going to read this part out loud.

1929
01:23:26,042 --> 01:23:27,034
So, let's break down what that means.

1930
01:23:27,034 --> 01:23:31,002
The purpose of brewing wine is not to create calamity.

1931
01:23:31,002 --> 01:23:34,026
But it's also true that alcohol is something that amplifies the evil in human nature.

1932
01:23:34,026 --> 01:23:36,052
That's why the ancient kings established specific rituals for drinking.

1933
01:23:36,052 --> 01:23:38,070
Even for the most basic form of this ritual, the 'One-Offering Ceremony',

1934
01:23:38,070 --> 01:23:41,050
This means when the host offers a toast to the guest, this single offering is called 'One Offering'.

1935
01:23:41,050 --> 01:23:44,034
There were also quite complex rituals to be observed between the host and the guest.

1936
01:23:44,034 --> 01:23:46,061
Here, 'a hundred bows' is a figure of speech to describe its complexity.

1937
01:23:46,061 --> 01:23:49,045
So you could drink this wine all day and still not get drunk.

1938
01:23:49,045 --> 01:23:50,033
All that hustle and bustle? It's all been metabolized and pissed away.

1939
01:23:50,033 --> 01:23:51,081
It's all just metabolized and gone.

1940
01:23:51,081 --> 01:23:54,028
All of this is to prevent the disasters that can come from drinking.

1941
01:23:54,028 --> 01:23:56,088
So, the purpose of food and wine is to bring people together.

1942
01:23:56,088 --> 01:23:59,064
a legitimate means to bond and share joy.

1943
01:23:59,064 --> 01:24:02,034
The 'Rites of Zhou, Chapter of the Grand Minister of Sacrifices' records: 'Use the rites of food and drink to draw near to the kinsmen and brothers.'

1944
01:24:02,034 --> 01:24:06,028
and to use the rites of feasting to welcome guests from all corners of the world.

1945
01:24:06,028 --> 01:24:08,080
explicitly designated feasting and drinking as a means to unite the clan,

1946
01:24:08,080 --> 01:24:10,049
and the key ritual for winning over guests.

1947
01:24:10,049 --> 01:24:13,041


1948
01:24:13,041 --> 01:24:18,061
This means that wine was only to be used for sacrificial rituals! Heaven, in its divine will, created wine for the people,

1949
01:24:18,061 --> 01:24:21,098
Its purpose was for everyone to use during grand sacrificial ceremonies!

1950
01:24:21,098 --> 01:24:24,034
Heaven sent down its punishment, the people fell into chaos, and morality was lost.

1951
01:24:24,034 --> 01:24:25,084
And it was all because of the reckless behavior caused by excessive drinking.

1952
01:24:25,084 --> 01:24:29,062
King Wen warned his descendants not to drink without reason, and especially not to overindulge in alcohol.

1953
01:24:29,062 --> 01:24:33,034
He even established a rule for the vassal states: they were only permitted to drink during sacrificial ceremonies.

1954
01:24:33,034 --> 01:24:35,088
Even during sacrifices, one must not be greedy with the cup and get drunk.

1955
01:24:35,088 --> 01:24:36,096
Such behavior is a breach of decorum and a failing of virtue.

1956
01:24:36,096 --> 01:24:39,072
So, what profound meaning do "wine and food" represent, after all?

1957
01:24:39,072 --> 01:24:41,087
First, it represents gratitude to Heaven.

1958
01:24:41,087 --> 01:24:46,077
After successfully crossing the great river and profiting from the shore, one must maintain a sense of reverence and be grateful for the blessings received.

1959
01:24:46,077 --> 01:24:48,065
Secondly, it represents the maintenance of order.

1960
01:24:48,065 --> 01:24:50,024
It's the core method for uniting forces.

1961
01:24:50,024 --> 01:24:51,004
At the same time, it also means that you must share the benefits with your own team.

1962
01:24:51,004 --> 01:24:53,088
This is the oath Liu Bang made when he was about to confer titles and ranks.

1963
01:24:53,088 --> 01:24:56,046
This is the oath Liu Bang made when he was about to grant titles and fiefdoms.

1964
01:24:56,046 --> 01:25:00,038
This would make the Yellow River as narrow as a belt and Mount Tai as smooth as a whetstone, so that the state may be preserved forever, and this love may extend to the descendants.

1965
01:25:00,038 --> 01:25:04,030
Secondly, it represents the caution of not indulging in desires and always being as prudent as walking on thin ice.

1966
01:25:04,030 --> 01:25:07,096
This is the same "zhēn" from the line statement, "Waiting on wine and food, it is auspicious to be steadfast."

1967
01:25:07,096 --> 01:25:11,098
as well as the "uprightness" in the Xiang Zhuan, which says, "Good fortune in feasting and drinking comes from uprightness."

1968
01:25:11,098 --> 01:25:13,022
All of this is telling us...

1969
01:25:13,022 --> 01:25:14,026
This is from the line: 'Clouds rise to the heavens. This is the image of Waiting. In accordance with this, the superior man eats and drinks, and is of good cheer.'

1970
01:25:14,026 --> 01:25:18,099
This is a balance you must always get right!

1971
01:25:18,099 --> 01:25:21,030
So, what does this mean for us?

1972
01:25:21,030 --> 01:25:22,040
Generally speaking,

1973
01:25:22,040 --> 01:25:24,080
After surviving the storm, fighting tooth and nail, and finally making it big,

1974
01:25:24,080 --> 01:25:27,010
There are three major pitfalls that await.

1975
01:25:27,010 --> 01:25:28,098
First, they get a big head and forget who they are.

1976
01:25:28,098 --> 01:25:31,030
They feel their abilities are so immense they're practically bursting at the seams.

1977
01:25:31,030 --> 01:25:32,078
You start to lose your sense of reverence.

1978
01:25:32,078 --> 01:25:34,036
They start thinking they can do anything.

1979
01:25:34,036 --> 01:25:36,045
And what follows this arrogance is a great disaster.

1980
01:25:36,045 --> 01:25:38,035
Second, greedily monopolizing all the credit.

1981
01:25:38,035 --> 01:25:39,085
They cling tightly to their profits, refusing to share with the brothers who have weathered the storm with them.

1982
01:25:39,085 --> 01:25:41,017
unwilling to share with those who

1983
01:25:41,017 --> 01:25:42,043
the brothers who've been through thick and thin with you

1984
01:25:42,043 --> 01:25:43,084
And what follows is being deserted by everyone.

1985
01:25:43,084 --> 01:25:45,082
So, how exactly did Xiang Yu meet his end?

1986
01:25:45,082 --> 01:25:48,066
So why did guys like Han Xin and Chen Ping all jump ship?

1987
01:25:48,066 --> 01:25:50,034
So why, despite being such a great warrior, did he end up with fewer and fewer people on his side?

1988
01:25:50,034 --> 01:25:51,096
So, what was the reason?

1989
01:25:51,096 --> 01:25:53,036
Because he doesn't share the rewards!

1990
01:25:53,036 --> 01:25:55,098
He'd rather wear the corners off his official seal than give out a single reward!

1991
01:25:55,098 --> 01:25:56,076
Everything you wouldn't reward, Old Liu went and rewarded for you.

1992
01:25:56,076 --> 01:25:58,030
He let Old Liu take care of all the rewards.

1993
01:25:58,030 --> 01:26:01,018
Third, indulging in pleasure without restraint.

1994
01:26:01,018 --> 01:26:03,026
This attracts a crowd of disreputable friends, as well as wolves and tigers.

1995
01:26:03,026 --> 01:26:05,043
squandering both their health and their wealth.

1996
01:26:05,043 --> 01:26:07,067
Our ancestors summed this up in just six words: 'Waiting over wine and food, perseverance brings good fortune.'

1997
01:26:07,067 --> 01:26:12,041
This clearly tells us the right mindset to have once we've made it to shore.

1998
01:26:12,041 --> 01:26:14,015
First, by offering sacrifices to Heaven, Earth, and our ancestors, we can quiet our minds.

1999
01:26:14,015 --> 01:26:16,041
Paying respects to our ancestors helps us quiet our minds.

2000
01:26:16,041 --> 01:26:17,065
and return to a state of calm.

2001
01:26:17,065 --> 01:26:22,014
Second, use sacrificial rites and feasts to unite the team and strengthen cohesion.

2002
01:26:22,014 --> 01:26:25,042
This makes your team feel that following you is a path to a better future, where everyone gets their share of the rewards.

2003
01:26:25,042 --> 01:26:27,080
And together, you will march from one victory to the next!

2004
01:26:27,080 --> 01:26:32,025
Third, by observing the absolute restrictions and warnings regarding alcohol set by the ancient sages and worthies.

2005
01:26:32,025 --> 01:26:34,069
and remind yourself not to get lost in the pursuit of pleasure.

2006
01:26:34,069 --> 01:26:36,056
Although the ninth five line is in the correct position and central, which is a great auspiciousness for the ruler's hexagram,

2007
01:26:36,056 --> 01:26:37,093
and is considered a great and auspicious hexagram.

2008
01:26:37,093 --> 01:26:40,073
But at the end of the day, this is still the middle line of the upper trigram, Kan, which represents danger.

2009
01:26:40,073 --> 01:26:44,016
After all, you're in a dangerous situation, so you must be vigilant at all times!

2010
01:26:44,016 --> 01:26:48,076
My friends, after we've weathered the storm and made it to shore, having left countless others behind,

2011
01:26:48,076 --> 01:26:51,076
and look back on the mountains of corpses and seas of blood left in the wake of that peril.

2012
01:26:51,076 --> 01:26:54,030
We must remember the playbook our ancestors gave us for navigating this stage.

2013
01:26:54,030 --> 01:26:56,028
So, what are the key strategies for this phase?

2014
01:26:56,028 --> 01:26:59,086
So whatever you do, don't get cocky, don't get reckless, don't be stingy, and don't give in to your every whim.

2015
01:26:59,086 --> 01:27:02,036
First off, I've just got to give a huge shout-out to our brilliant ancestors.

2016
01:27:02,036 --> 01:27:03,028
Such profound wisdom.

2017
01:27:03,028 --> 01:27:09,048
For those of you who've been through the wringer, you know exactly how much weight that last part really carries!

2018
01:27:10,009 --> 01:27:11,041
The Sixth, at the Top

2019
01:27:11,041 --> 01:27:14,093
The line text reads: 'Entering the cave, three uninvited guests arrive. If you treat them with respect, it will be auspicious in the end.'

2020
01:27:14,093 --> 01:27:18,035
If, after successfully crossing the great river, you fail to follow the path of centrality and correctness of the Ninth Five,

2021
01:27:18,035 --> 01:27:20,063
You get carried away, go wild, become stingy, and court disaster.

2022
01:27:20,063 --> 01:27:21,047
Well, that's a shame.

2023
01:27:21,047 --> 01:27:24,033
And with that, you arrive at the top sixth line of the Xu hexagram.

2024
01:27:24,033 --> 01:27:26,004
This is the ultimate position of peril, the very peak of the dangerous upper trigram, Kan.

2025
01:27:26,004 --> 01:27:27,086
Kan represents a pit, a cave, and perilous difficulties.

2026
01:27:27,086 --> 01:27:28,062
Entering the pit of hardship.

2027
01:27:28,062 --> 01:27:30,062
“Entering the pit” means you have fallen into a perilous and desperate situation.

2028
01:27:30,062 --> 01:27:33,056
At this point, you're at a dead end, trapped and with no one to help.

2029
01:27:33,056 --> 01:27:36,002
And don't ask why. You've got no one to blame but yourself.

2030
01:27:36,002 --> 01:27:37,057
Your arrogance and extravagance will make everyone jealous and resent you.

2031
01:27:37,057 --> 01:27:39,020
and now everyone resents you for it.

2032
01:27:39,020 --> 01:27:41,084
You don't share the profits, so your key people leave you.

2033
01:27:41,084 --> 01:27:43,032
Everyone is just waiting for you to fail, watching you as a joke!

2034
01:27:43,032 --> 01:27:45,020
Everyone's just waiting for you to fail, watching you like it's a joke.

2035
01:27:45,020 --> 01:27:46,084
Not only will no one come to help you anymore,

2036
01:27:46,084 --> 01:27:48,050
And at this point, 'three uninvited guests arrive.'

2037
01:27:48,050 --> 01:27:51,033
Here, the character 'su' (速) means to invite or to summon.

2038
01:27:51,033 --> 01:27:54,057
On the surface, an 'uninvited guest' is simply a visitor who shows up without being asked.

2039
01:27:54,057 --> 01:27:59,042
But in reality, it carries a more negative connotation, referring to unwelcome intruders with ill intentions.

2040
01:27:59,042 --> 01:28:01,032
The term 'three people' here doesn't literally mean three individuals.

2041
01:28:01,032 --> 01:28:02,056
Here, the number 'three' represents a multitude.

2042
01:28:02,056 --> 01:28:03,045
In other words,

2043
01:28:03,045 --> 01:28:06,087
When you reach the top sixth line of the Xu hexagram, you have entered the very heart of the Kan, the abyss of danger.

2044
01:28:06,087 --> 01:28:09,090
a whole host of uninvited guests will come crashing into your life.

2045
01:28:09,090 --> 01:28:11,068
To put it in Buddhist terms,

2046
01:28:11,068 --> 01:28:14,085
This means wealth is jointly owned by five types of entities, as stated in the Mahāprajñāpāramitā Śāstra.

2047
01:28:14,085 --> 01:28:15,099
We toil for wealth, yet it is shared by five others.

2048
01:28:15,099 --> 01:28:17,009
shared by our own family.

2049
01:28:17,009 --> 01:28:20,018
be it by the king, by thieves, by fire, by flood, or by your own unvirtuous children.

2050
01:28:20,018 --> 01:28:21,057
Even what you bury will be lost.

2051
01:28:21,057 --> 01:28:25,072
In other words, legal disasters, theft, floods, fires, and prodigal children.

2052
01:28:25,072 --> 01:28:28,057
If you disrespect the heavens, disasters of water and fire will befall you.

2053
01:28:28,057 --> 01:28:31,086
If you live extravagantly or are miserly, calamities from officials and thieves will come to take your wealth.

2054
01:28:31,086 --> 01:28:35,000
If you don't believe in karma, then you will be ruined by your own unworthy descendants, leading to the bankruptcy of your family.

2055
01:28:35,000 --> 01:28:37,010
So, what should you do in this situation?

2056
01:28:37,010 --> 01:28:38,048
Our ancestors have already told us.

2057
01:28:38,048 --> 01:28:39,086
If you maintain this reverence, you will ultimately find good fortune.

2058
01:28:39,086 --> 01:28:43,024
If the arrival of these uninvited guests can serve as a wake-up call for us,

2059
01:28:43,024 --> 01:28:45,024
and make us wake up and repent,

2060
01:28:45,024 --> 01:28:48,064
and once again adopt an attitude of reverence, respect, and prudence in how we conduct ourselves.

2061
01:28:48,064 --> 01:28:51,046
No matter what kind of uninvited guest comes to snatch and plunder,

2062
01:28:51,046 --> 01:28:54,057
If we can realize that this disaster is one of our own making,

2063
01:28:54,057 --> 01:28:57,074
Then, these uninvited guests are actually the benefactors in our lives.

2064
01:28:57,074 --> 01:29:00,016
It's what allows us to break these bad habits.

2065
01:29:00,016 --> 01:29:02,040
and make it possible for us to make a comeback in the future.

2066
01:29:02,040 --> 01:29:05,010
No matter how severe this uninvited guest might be,

2067
01:29:05,010 --> 01:29:07,090
as long as you regain your sense of reverence and caution.

2068
01:29:07,090 --> 01:29:10,042
it usually won't be a fatal blow.

2069
01:29:10,042 --> 01:29:11,050
Even in the absolute worst-case scenario,

2070
01:29:11,050 --> 01:29:15,022
meaning they could strip you of all your resources and status,

2071
01:29:15,022 --> 01:29:17,066
But the experiences and the lessons you've gained along the way...

2072
01:29:17,066 --> 01:29:19,022
and the invaluable lessons you've learned—no one can ever take those away from you!

2073
01:29:19,022 --> 01:29:20,012
and no one can ever take that away from you.

2074
01:29:20,012 --> 01:29:21,076
We still have a chance to start over!

2075
01:29:21,076 --> 01:29:23,034
But have you guys ever noticed something?

2076
01:29:23,034 --> 01:29:25,074
If the Kan trigram appears in the lower trigram,

2077
01:29:25,074 --> 01:29:29,060
This means that the first, second, and third lines—Initial Six, Nine Two, and Six Three—are all out of their proper positions.

2078
01:29:29,060 --> 01:29:31,075
But if it appears in the upper trigram,

2079
01:29:31,075 --> 01:29:33,075
Even if it represents danger,

2080
01:29:33,075 --> 01:29:38,067
However, the Six in the Fourth, the Nine in the Fifth, and the Six at the Top are all in their proper positions, and all hold the potential for a turning point.

2081
01:29:38,067 --> 01:29:39,076
So, what does that mean?

2082
01:29:39,076 --> 01:29:44,016
Now, when it comes to these hardships, encountering them right at the very beginning is extremely perilous!

2083
01:29:44,016 --> 01:29:46,096
Every step is a struggle, a life-or-death battle!

2084
01:29:46,096 --> 01:29:49,004
Many people run into trouble right when they're just starting out.

2085
01:29:49,004 --> 01:29:50,098
Or you get physically wiped out, and see you in the next life.

2086
01:29:50,098 --> 01:29:53,022
Or, they just mentally check out, bow their heads, and resign themselves to a life of fear and mediocrity.

2087
01:29:53,022 --> 01:29:56,093
But if you've already got some foundation...

2088
01:29:56,093 --> 01:29:57,081
and a certain amount of experience,

2089
01:29:57,081 --> 01:29:59,031
and then you encounter them after you've built up enough of a foundation,

2090
01:29:59,031 --> 01:30:02,034
It's an unavoidable part of starting any venture.

2091
01:30:02,034 --> 01:30:05,020
Every trial that doesn't kill me only makes me stronger!

2092
01:30:05,020 --> 01:30:08,064
Even if you're knocked back to square one, even if you've lost everything you had,

2093
01:30:08,064 --> 01:30:10,060
But you can still start all over again!

2094
01:30:10,060 --> 01:30:13,036
The Hexagram of Xu is about the acquisition and distribution of resources.

2095
01:30:13,036 --> 01:30:15,018
So, after explaining the first six lines of the hexagram,

2096
01:30:15,018 --> 01:30:19,077
So, has this sparked any new thoughts for you all about the process of gaining benefits and the principles of distribution?

2097
01:30:19,077 --> 01:30:21,069
The Hexagram of Xu is unique in that it doesn't possess the 'Yuan' quality.

2098
01:30:21,069 --> 01:30:23,071
Because resources are always finite.

2099
01:30:23,071 --> 01:30:25,021
If you succeed in gaining a profit, it means someone else has failed to get it.

2100
01:30:25,021 --> 01:30:27,028
which means someone else has failed to get their share.

2101
01:30:27,028 --> 01:30:29,038
And this, in turn, means that conflicts are bound to arise.

2102
01:30:29,038 --> 01:30:30,074
and even lead to conflict.

2103
01:30:34,026 --> 01:30:36,064
This then leads to resorting to legal means and public authority to resolve the conflict. In other words, as it is said, 'The Way of Nourishment.'

2104
01:30:36,064 --> 01:30:40,010
Where there are disputes over food and drink, there will inevitably be litigation. Therefore, the hexagram of 'Dispute' follows.

2105
01:30:40,054 --> 01:30:43,054
The hexagram of 'Xu', which deals with the principles of sustenance, has a trigram of Water above and Heaven below.

2106
01:30:43,054 --> 01:30:47,004
Except for the Second Yang line, which is out of place, all the other five lines are in their proper positions.

2107
01:30:47,004 --> 01:30:49,032
And the only line that's not in its proper place, the Ninth Two, is still central.

2108
01:30:49,032 --> 01:30:52,092
This shows that the heavens are extremely supportive of us finding our place, sustaining our lives, and building our legacies.

2109
01:30:52,092 --> 01:30:54,046
It is a matter of utmost support.

2110
01:30:54,046 --> 01:30:56,040
As long as you remember that the core principle is to wait,

2111
01:30:56,040 --> 01:30:58,094
As long as a noble person keeps their talents hidden and acts at the opportune moment,

2112
01:30:58,094 --> 01:31:01,042
Acquire and allocate resources in a reasonable manner.

2113
01:31:01,042 --> 01:31:02,074
This is the fundamental law of the universe!

2114
01:31:02,074 --> 01:31:05,094
But now, the hexagram of litigation is completely the opposite.

2115
01:31:05,094 --> 01:31:07,040
Qian above, Kan below.

2116
01:31:07,040 --> 01:31:10,094
The first six, the second nine, the third six, the fourth nine, the fifth nine, and the top nine.

2117
01:31:10,094 --> 01:31:13,071
Except for the ninth five, all the other lines are out of place!

2118
01:31:13,071 --> 01:31:15,015
And right here, we can see why.

2119
01:31:15,015 --> 01:31:18,004
This whole idea of litigation is fundamentally inauspicious from the very root.

2120
01:31:18,004 --> 01:31:20,072
This is something that every single one of us should do our utmost to avoid.

2121
01:31:20,072 --> 01:31:22,050
So, looking at the hexagram of 'Conflict' as a whole,

2122
01:31:22,050 --> 01:31:25,038
Nor is it about teaching us how to win a lawsuit.

2123
01:31:25,038 --> 01:31:27,094
Instead, it serves as a reminder for us to be cautious about litigation and to stop it whenever possible.

2124
01:31:27,094 --> 01:31:29,022
讼, which means to litigate.

2125
01:31:29,022 --> 01:31:31,096
Don't resort to litigation unless it's absolutely the last option!

2126
01:31:31,096 --> 01:31:33,048
Now, let's look at the Hexagram Statement.

2127
01:31:33,048 --> 01:31:36,094
It says, "Sincerity is blocked, be alert." Now, as we mentioned in the commentary on the previous hexagram,

2128
01:31:36,094 --> 01:31:38,078
The character '孚' (fú) signifies faithfulness and trustworthiness.

2129
01:31:38,078 --> 01:31:40,082
Here, the character 'zhì' (窒) means to be blocked or obstructed.

2130
01:31:40,082 --> 01:31:42,084
and "惕" (tì) means to be vigilant and prudent.

2131
01:31:42,084 --> 01:31:45,070
So, the phrase 'you fu zhi ti' means...

2132
01:31:45,070 --> 01:31:47,096
Even if you are in the right and acting in good faith at this moment,

2133
01:31:47,096 --> 01:31:50,009
and you have every right and all the proof to back you up,

2134
01:31:50,009 --> 01:31:52,067
Even if your legitimate rights and interests have been violated,

2135
01:31:52,067 --> 01:31:54,037
Even if we are completely in the right,

2136
01:31:54,037 --> 01:31:58,059
and the person you're up against is a complete bastard who maliciously twists the facts to bully an honest person.

2137
01:31:58,059 --> 01:32:03,027
But even then, we must still think twice before taking that final step of going to court.

2138
01:32:03,027 --> 01:32:06,020
and whether you can bring your own powerful backers to the table.

2139
01:32:06,020 --> 01:32:09,062
Resolve it privately beforehand through communication, negotiation, or even deterrence.

2140
01:32:09,062 --> 01:32:12,082
You must always maintain a sense of reverence for the judiciary and public authority.

2141
01:32:12,082 --> 01:32:14,030
If you can avoid going to court,

2142
01:32:14,030 --> 01:32:17,030
If you can settle things privately, you should always do so beforehand.

2143
01:32:17,030 --> 01:32:21,057
And why is that? Because in ancient times, you'd be dealing with a whole pack of corrupt officials who were like wolves and jackals.

2144
01:32:21,057 --> 01:32:25,050
There's an old saying: 'An official's ruling has ten possible paths, nine of which are hidden from the public.' What does that mean?

2145
01:32:25,050 --> 01:32:26,034
In ancient times, the verdict for the very same lawsuit...

2146
01:32:26,034 --> 01:32:30,048
The punishment could be light or severe, the verdict could be a win or a loss.

2147
01:32:30,048 --> 01:32:31,090
There were no fixed standards.

2148
01:32:31,090 --> 01:32:35,009
The intricacies of these matters were completely unknown to the vast majority of common people.

2149
01:32:35,009 --> 01:32:38,051
In a case like this, as long as there's the slightest room for maneuver,

2150
01:32:38,051 --> 01:32:41,094
And the presiding officials? Well, the things they can do next are just endless.

2151
01:32:41,094 --> 01:32:43,026
Take the 'Studebaker Boy' from the TV series 'Lurk' for example.

2152
01:32:43,026 --> 01:32:46,048
So, how did he go about handling those gold bars for the station chief?

2153
01:32:46,048 --> 01:32:48,080
That's called showing leniency to a meritorious subject!

2154
01:32:48,080 --> 01:32:52,004
You see, this Regiment Commander Xu, he made great contributions during the war of resistance.

2155
01:32:52,004 --> 01:32:55,044
He's a war hero, after all. You can't just wipe them all out!

2156
01:32:55,044 --> 01:32:56,072
So, how did our dear 'Jade Throne Golden Buddha' get his hands on Liu Yu's most prized treasure?

2157
01:32:56,072 --> 01:32:58,036
how did he manage to get Liu Yu's most treasured possession,

2158
01:32:58,036 --> 01:33:00,046
And get it into the hands of his wife?

2159
01:33:00,046 --> 01:33:03,030
Because Yu Zecheng has leverage over the major corrupt official's sister.

2160
01:33:03,030 --> 01:33:06,012
The discretion to determine whether they count as an accomplice.

2161
01:33:06,012 --> 01:33:08,064
If Ji Weimin wanted to keep his sister safe,

2162
01:33:08,064 --> 01:33:13,025
he would never dare to mention that his loot once included a jade throne and a golden Buddha.

2163
01:33:13,025 --> 01:33:17,053
So why did the station chief have the nerve to shamelessly shake down the major traitor, Mu Liancheng?

2164
01:33:17,053 --> 01:33:21,009
Because he's the one who holds the power to decide whether this old geezer is a traitor or not.

2165
01:33:21,009 --> 01:33:24,059
If I declare you a traitor, all your property will be confiscated.

2166
01:33:24,059 --> 01:33:26,009
But if I say you're not...

2167
01:33:26,009 --> 01:33:28,081
So, how do you think we should split up your family fortune?

2168
01:33:28,081 --> 01:33:29,067
In ancient times,

2169
01:33:32,037 --> 01:33:33,064
Once the authorities find any pretext to drag you into it,

2170
01:33:33,064 --> 01:33:35,086
They'll skin you alive if they get the chance!

2171
01:33:35,086 --> 01:33:37,074
So, how did Song Jiang get so rich?

2172
01:33:37,074 --> 01:33:40,076
That's because all his life, he's had a passion for befriending heroes of the martial world.

2173
01:33:40,076 --> 01:33:44,008
But if anyone came to seek his help, regardless of their status or background, he would take them in without exception.

2174
01:33:44,008 --> 01:33:45,074
He would have them stay at his manor, providing them with food and lodging.

2175
01:33:45,074 --> 01:33:47,074
He would spend his days in their company, never tiring of their presence.

2176
01:33:47,074 --> 01:33:49,020
And if anyone wanted to leave and start their own journey, he would do everything in his power to fund them.

2177
01:33:49,020 --> 01:33:51,054
He was truly a spendthrift, treating gold as if it were dirt.

2178
01:33:51,054 --> 01:33:54,099
Because Song Jiang was serving as a clerk in Yuncheng County.

2179
01:33:54,099 --> 01:33:57,085
He was a master of both writing and administration, highly skilled in the ways of the bureaucracy.

2180
01:33:57,085 --> 01:34:01,011


2181
01:34:01,011 --> 01:34:04,042
The phrase 'master of the knife and brush' refers to the ancient practice of carving characters onto bamboo slips to record events.

2182
01:34:04,042 --> 01:34:06,018
and used a knife to scrape off any mistakes.

2183
01:34:06,018 --> 01:34:09,017


2184
01:34:09,017 --> 01:34:10,028


2185
01:34:10,028 --> 01:34:11,025
son

2186
01:34:11,025 --> 01:34:13,090
Basically, whenever the term 'knife and brush' appears,

2187
01:34:13,090 --> 01:34:15,052
Nine times out of ten, it's used with a negative connotation.

2188
01:34:15,052 --> 01:34:18,036
In ancient times, these two characters were especially favored in the biographies of cruel officials.

2189
01:34:18,036 --> 01:34:22,073
So, why was Song Jiang so obsessed with befriending heroes from the martial world?

2190
01:34:22,073 --> 01:34:28,089
Because he needed to use these social outlaws to build a reputation that commanded respect in both the legal and criminal worlds, creating his own kind of 'Studebaker influence'.

2191
01:34:28,089 --> 01:34:30,038
and the influence of a Studebaker.

2192
01:34:30,038 --> 01:34:33,098
Within the system, he was the Clerk of Yuncheng, a master of officialdom.

2193
01:34:33,098 --> 01:34:37,023
Outside the system, he was Song Jiang, the man with connections in the entire underworld of Shandong and Hebei.

2194
01:34:37,023 --> 01:34:41,042
This influence, spanning both the legitimate and the underworld, can be summed up in one simple phrase in the market.

2195
01:34:41,042 --> 01:34:46,030
The price I, Song Jiang, set is one that's accepted by both the Yuncheng County Court and the heroes of the martial world.

2196
01:34:46,030 --> 01:34:48,078
For the cases I handle, just pay up, by the book.

2197
01:34:48,078 --> 01:34:50,056
I make my fortune by keeping things peaceful and pleasant.

2198
01:34:50,056 --> 01:34:53,040
If you want to save that money, if you want to break the rules...

2199
01:34:53,040 --> 01:34:56,076
And Brother Gongming, of course, wouldn't say a word either, just chuckling it off.

2200
01:34:56,076 --> 01:34:58,008
He frowns,

2201
01:34:58,008 --> 01:35:02,006
Then, the captain of Yuncheng and the heroes of the Jianghu would naturally help that person disappear.

2202
01:35:02,006 --> 01:35:04,036
Because you were cutting off Brother Song Jiang's source of income.

2203
01:35:04,036 --> 01:35:06,004
You're basically cutting off the bailiffs' bonuses.

2204
01:35:06,004 --> 01:35:07,064
You're basically taking away the heroes' insurance.

2205
01:35:07,064 --> 01:35:08,054
For example,

2206
01:35:08,054 --> 01:35:12,036
So, when a case involving a hero or a wealthy family landed in Song Jiang's hands...

2207
01:35:12,036 --> 01:35:14,032
So, what's Clerk Song's move?

2208
01:35:14,032 --> 01:35:16,024
He would alter the testimony and falsify the case files.

2209
01:35:16,024 --> 01:35:18,020
Change 'murder' to 'manslaughter'...

2210
01:35:18,020 --> 01:35:19,062
Change 'robbery' to 'theft' with just a little tweak.

2211
01:35:19,062 --> 01:35:21,092
And that completely changes the nature of the crime.

2212
01:35:21,092 --> 01:35:24,070
Or even just delete or lose key evidence outright.

2213
01:35:24,070 --> 01:35:28,085
Even for those high-profile, seemingly unsolvable cases, he's got his ways.

2214
01:35:28,085 --> 01:35:31,053
If there's really no way to tamper with the evidence, I'll just tip them off, right?

2215
01:35:31,053 --> 01:35:33,049
So, how did Chao Gai and his crew manage to get away?

2216
01:35:33,049 --> 01:35:36,040
With Song Jiang, a serious crime could be reduced to a minor one.

2217
01:35:36,040 --> 01:35:39,034
A prime suspect can be downgraded to an accomplice, and a minor offense can be dismissed as no offense at all.

2218
01:35:39,034 --> 01:35:41,002
So, that brings us to the question:

2219
01:35:41,002 --> 01:35:45,022
So, were all these "heroes of the rivers and lakes" that Song Jiang helped really good people?

2220
01:35:45,022 --> 01:35:46,090
In the novel "Water Margin," the term "jianghu" broadly refers to the world outside of the official system.

2221
01:35:46,090 --> 01:35:50,020
And that's why the word "heroes" needs to be in quotation marks.

2222
01:35:50,020 --> 01:35:51,086
essentially referring to the destabilizing elements in society.

2223
01:35:51,086 --> 01:35:53,034
Just how famous was Song Jiang?

2224
01:35:53,034 --> 01:35:56,089
that means just as many truly good people were being treated unjustly.

2225
01:35:56,089 --> 01:36:00,037
And Song Jiang wasn't some isolated case back in ancient times.

2226
01:36:00,037 --> 01:36:02,060
Once a matter escalates to the point of a lawsuit,

2227
01:36:02,060 --> 01:36:08,004
In essence, it's just the plaintiff and the defendant constantly funneling money into the government's coffers.

2228
01:36:08,004 --> 01:36:12,018
Even if the rich and powerful commit murder and arson with irrefutable proof,

2229
01:36:12,018 --> 01:36:15,012
the authorities can still drag things out with all sorts of excuses.

2230
01:36:15,012 --> 01:36:17,062
For instance, they might deliberately transfer the case to another yamen.

2231
01:36:17,062 --> 01:36:19,057
to increase the litigation costs for the victim.

2232
01:36:19,057 --> 01:36:23,006
For instance, they might arrange for court staff to be on a business trip, bringing the case to a standstill.

2233
01:36:23,006 --> 01:36:25,038
They drag the victim's family down until they are utterly bankrupt.

2234
01:36:25,038 --> 01:36:26,048
forcing you to settle out of court.

2235
01:36:26,048 --> 01:36:28,042
They could even fabricate a whole new case.

2236
01:36:28,042 --> 01:36:32,004
For instance, they might send a bunch of local thugs to the victim's place to stir up trouble.

2237
01:36:32,004 --> 01:36:34,042
and frame the victim for stealing their stuff.

2238
01:36:34,042 --> 01:36:35,098
and a whole gang of thugs can all testify. It's the classic Lai Junchen playbook, right?

2239
01:36:35,098 --> 01:36:37,078
That's the same old playbook as Lai Junchen.

2240
01:36:37,078 --> 01:36:40,002
And then, they'd just lock the victim up.

2241
01:36:40,002 --> 01:36:42,024
Then they'd just wait until the victim was tormented to death in prison.

2242
01:36:42,024 --> 01:36:46,027
And this became the primary condition for officials in ancient cases who just wanted to get things done quickly.

2243
01:36:46,027 --> 01:36:47,085
And with the victim gone...

2244
01:36:47,085 --> 01:36:49,062
And then, they'd just pass a sentence, casually.

2245
01:36:49,062 --> 01:36:50,052
In ancient times,

2246
01:36:50,052 --> 01:36:53,072
If you're quite wealthy, but don't have any backing from the authorities,

2247
01:36:53,072 --> 01:36:55,054
Those jackals with powerful backers

2248
01:36:55,054 --> 01:36:57,086
They might even fabricate lawsuits against you, just like we mentioned.

2249
01:36:57,086 --> 01:37:00,064
They'll drag you into their schemes and bleed you dry.

2250
01:37:00,064 --> 01:37:03,005
So, why was it that in ancient times, excelling in studies was the path to becoming a government official?

2251
01:37:03,005 --> 01:37:05,087
So, why did having male heirs mean everything in ancient times?

2252
01:37:05,087 --> 01:37:08,081
Having more men in the family meant higher productivity.

2253
01:37:08,081 --> 01:37:12,035
This means that even before the family falls to its final, fatal line,

2254
01:37:12,035 --> 01:37:14,086
And there's always that last desperate path, where you fight to the death and take everyone down with you.

2255
01:37:14,086 --> 01:37:19,068
This means that before corrupt officials or bandits decide to wipe you out, they have to weigh the costs.

2256
01:37:19,068 --> 01:37:22,036
So, do you see now why it says 'sincerity brings apprehension'?

2257
01:37:22,036 --> 01:37:23,035
Let's continue to the next part.

2258
01:37:23,035 --> 01:37:27,013
It says, "Moderate success, but an ominous end. It is favorable to meet a great man, but unfavorable to cross the great river."

2259
01:37:27,013 --> 01:37:29,028
This sets the core tone for the Lawsuit Hexagram.

2260
01:37:29,028 --> 01:37:31,082
It tells us the boundaries between fortune and misfortune when it comes to litigation.

2261
01:37:31,082 --> 01:37:35,076
Now, the "middle" in "middle good fortune" doesn't mean that the middle of the dispute is auspicious.

2262
01:37:35,076 --> 01:37:37,066
This 'middle' means knowing when to stop,

2263
01:37:37,066 --> 01:37:39,010
It means not being extreme or stubborn.

2264
01:37:39,010 --> 01:37:43,000
This is exactly what the Commentary on the Tuan explains in the line: 'Favorable in the center, because the firm has arrived at the center.'

2265
01:37:43,000 --> 01:37:44,016
The firm comes and attains the center.

2266
01:37:44,016 --> 01:37:47,077
This means that litigation should only be a last resort.

2267
01:37:47,077 --> 01:37:49,067
or even just a deterrent weapon.

2268
01:37:49,067 --> 01:37:52,084
If the other party is willing to back down and start talking properly,

2269
01:37:52,084 --> 01:37:55,092
and are willing to talk, even if you still end up losing out a little,

2270
01:37:55,092 --> 01:37:57,090
as long as it's not a devastating blow,

2271
01:37:57,090 --> 01:38:01,074
as long as they're scared enough afterwards to stop hurting us,

2272
01:38:01,074 --> 01:38:03,057
So, it's best to quit while you're ahead.

2273
01:38:03,057 --> 01:38:06,050
Never, ever press your advantage relentlessly or be unforgiving when you're in the right!

2274
01:38:06,050 --> 01:38:11,027
Back in the day, you had to remember one thing: compared to corrupt officials, common thieves were nothing!

2275
01:38:11,027 --> 01:38:13,063
Getting into lawsuits is just asking for trouble, a recipe for disaster.

2276
01:38:13,063 --> 01:38:14,067
It's a bottomless pit.

2277
01:38:14,067 --> 01:38:15,097
As long as you can cut your losses in time, that's a huge win!

2278
01:38:15,097 --> 01:38:17,021
That would be the best possible outcome.

2279
01:38:17,021 --> 01:38:18,086
If this whole thing drags on endlessly,

2280
01:38:18,086 --> 01:38:21,078
Even if you have every right on your side, fighting to the bitter end will inevitably lead to disaster.

2281
01:38:21,078 --> 01:38:23,020
the outcome will inevitably be disastrous.

2282
01:38:23,020 --> 01:38:28,012
First of all, the authorities will do everything in their power to squeeze every last drop of property from both the plaintiff and the defendant.

2283
01:38:28,012 --> 01:38:29,070
Even if you ultimately win the lawsuit,

2284
01:38:29,070 --> 01:38:32,044
But you will have already lost the very foundation to make a comeback.

2285
01:38:32,044 --> 01:38:33,056
But what's even more critical is this:

2286
01:38:33,056 --> 01:38:35,030
After a life-or-death struggle,

2287
01:38:35,030 --> 01:38:37,087
So, what do you do when your opponent is out for blood?

2288
01:38:37,087 --> 01:38:40,073
Now, this isn't to say that you should just blindly avoid conflict through this channel.

2289
01:38:40,073 --> 01:38:43,089
If the other side sees you showing any weakness, they'll just push even harder.

2290
01:38:43,089 --> 01:38:47,007
Instead, it means this channel is best used purely as a deterrent.

2291
01:38:47,007 --> 01:38:50,081
We must be prepared for the worst-case scenario, even if it means fighting a lawsuit until we're bankrupt.

2292
01:38:50,081 --> 01:38:52,044
and my determination to see this through to the very end.

2293
01:38:52,044 --> 01:38:58,065
But we know this is a way to get both sides to weigh the costs, take a step back, and settle the matter peacefully.

2294
01:38:58,065 --> 01:39:04,096
The last line of the Judgment for the Lawsuit Hexagram, 'It is beneficial to see the great man, but not to cross the great river,' also serves to elaborate on what to do.

2295
01:39:04,096 --> 01:39:08,076
When it comes to a dispute, it doesn't necessarily have to end up in court.

2296
01:39:08,076 --> 01:39:12,030
Even if both sides have already lost their cool and are ready for a fight to the death,

2297
01:39:12,030 --> 01:39:14,040
you can still try a different approach.

2298
01:39:14,040 --> 01:39:18,000
Find a fair and reputable authority figure to act as a mediator and make the ruling.

2299
01:39:18,000 --> 01:39:20,018
This is precisely the line from the Commentary on the Tuan.

2300
01:39:20,018 --> 01:39:22,014
It is beneficial to meet a great man, for this upholds what is central and correct.

2301
01:39:22,014 --> 01:39:25,024
Now, on the surface, this term 'uprightness and impartiality' seems to be about credibility.

2302
01:39:25,024 --> 01:39:26,052
But in reality, the deeper meaning behind it is more about...

2303
01:39:26,052 --> 01:39:31,062
Find a powerful figure who is respected, or even commands authority, by both sides.

2304
01:39:31,062 --> 01:39:35,074
Otherwise, neither side would acknowledge that this prominent figure is 'upright and impartial'.

2305
01:39:35,074 --> 01:39:38,030
When two sides are at a stalemate, it's a classic clash of titans.

2306
01:39:38,030 --> 01:39:41,038
Once a third party is brought in, it creates some room to maneuver.

2307
01:39:41,038 --> 01:39:43,086
Perhaps both sides had wanted to reconcile all along.

2308
01:39:43,086 --> 01:39:46,002
But they're just too proud to back down.

2309
01:39:46,002 --> 01:39:49,098
In this situation, the third party's role is to provide a way for both sides to save face.

2310
01:39:49,098 --> 01:39:51,094
As long as someone can step in and make that transition,

2311
01:39:51,094 --> 01:39:54,049
In the end, it's even possible for both sides to turn enemies into friends.

2312
01:39:54,049 --> 01:39:56,051
Even if we're the ones taking the hit,

2313
01:39:56,051 --> 01:39:59,083
As long as you can eventually get to the stage where 'no discord, no concord' becomes a reality,

2314
01:39:59,083 --> 01:40:01,049
In fact, this is a good thing, a sign of fortune.

2315
01:40:01,049 --> 01:40:04,096
Just think of the costs you've incurred as money spent to ward off disaster.

2316
01:40:04,096 --> 01:40:06,094
Whatever you do, don't get bogged down in endless arguments.

2317
01:40:06,094 --> 01:40:08,060
If, when it comes to disputes, you were to act as in the previous hexagram,

2318
01:40:08,060 --> 01:40:11,059
to take the risk and 'cross the great river'

2319
01:40:11,059 --> 01:40:13,018
insisting on taking that risk,

2320
01:40:13,018 --> 01:40:17,056
So, whether it means fighting a lawsuit to the bitter end, or resorting to desperate measures and even violence,

2321
01:40:17,056 --> 01:40:19,088
your ultimate fate will certainly be a bad one.

2322
01:40:19,088 --> 01:40:23,057
So, what we've discussed so far is that even when you're in the right, you should still avoid disputes.

2323
01:40:23,057 --> 01:40:25,084
let alone when you're the one in the wrong.

2324
01:40:25,084 --> 01:40:28,064
If you've done something wrong and are now being held accountable,

2325
01:40:28,064 --> 01:40:29,080
If you're wrong, admit you're wrong.

2326
01:40:29,080 --> 01:40:32,056
Pay what you owe in compensation, and ask for forgiveness where it's due.

2327
01:40:32,056 --> 01:40:34,028
If their asking price is too high, just say, 'In that case, let's just take it to the authorities.'

2328
01:40:34,028 --> 01:40:35,092
Then just say, 'Alright, let's take it to the authorities.'

2329
01:40:35,092 --> 01:40:39,084
Use the cost of going to court to scare them, making them weigh the pros and cons.

2330
01:40:39,084 --> 01:40:41,061
It is better to make friends than enemies.

2331
01:40:41,061 --> 01:40:44,017
We absolutely must avoid taking a lawsuit all the way to the bitter end.

2332
01:40:44,017 --> 01:40:45,097
And it's just as the saying goes: in ancient times, it didn't matter if you were the plaintiff or the defendant.

2333
01:40:45,097 --> 01:40:51,078
Regardless of who wins or loses, there are no real winners. The only winner is the government.

2334
01:40:51,078 --> 01:40:53,073
Looking at the entire hexagram of 'Conflict' and its major lines,

2335
01:40:53,073 --> 01:40:57,079
The only line that is both in its correct position and centered is the ninth five, which symbolizes the government.

2336
01:40:57,079 --> 01:41:00,062
You really have to savor the profound meaning behind this!

2337
01:41:00,062 --> 01:41:03,044
The Commentary on the Decision says, "In the end, it is inauspicious. A lawsuit cannot be won."

2338
01:41:03,044 --> 01:41:05,042
We must always remember, this doesn't mean that a dispute can't ultimately be won or succeed.

2339
01:41:05,042 --> 01:41:07,062
It's not that you can never succeed in a dispute,

2340
01:41:07,062 --> 01:41:08,008
or that you can't win.

2341
01:41:08,008 --> 01:41:10,045
Instead, it's about the act of arguing itself.

2342
01:41:10,045 --> 01:41:12,076
There is no such thing as true success to begin with!

2343
01:41:12,076 --> 01:41:14,038
Don't think you're untouchable just because you have connections in the government.

2344
01:41:14,038 --> 01:41:17,092
Just because you're powerful, you think you can wield the judicial system like a butcher's knife and just hack away at people as you please.

2345
01:41:17,092 --> 01:41:19,066
First, your reputation will be ruined.

2346
01:41:19,066 --> 01:41:22,091
Second, the people you victimize aren't necessarily pushovers.

2347
01:41:22,091 --> 01:41:25,092
Once you make an enemy, they will hunt you to the ends of the earth.

2348
01:41:25,092 --> 01:41:28,080
Even the most humble person, as long as they keep their eyes open at all times,

2349
01:41:28,080 --> 01:41:31,075
Sooner or later, they'll seize the chance to get their revenge on the most powerful people!

2350
01:41:31,075 --> 01:41:34,021
During the Su Jun Rebellion, Huan Yi defended Jingcheng for a year.

2351
01:41:34,021 --> 01:41:35,082
He was ultimately killed by the rebel general, Han Huang.

2352
01:41:35,082 --> 01:41:37,014
Han Huang was defeated and killed.

2353
01:41:37,014 --> 01:41:38,038
However, Jiang Bo, the magistrate of Jingcheng at the time, was also involved in Huan Yi's murder.

2354
01:41:38,038 --> 01:41:40,044
At the time, the magistrate of the capital, Jiang Bo, was also involved.

2355
01:41:40,044 --> 01:41:43,086
And so, the fifteen-year-old Huan Wen, with a heart full of grief and a burning desire for revenge, vowed to avenge his father.

2356
01:41:43,086 --> 01:41:45,076
However, Jiang Bo was an official of the imperial court.

2357
01:41:45,076 --> 01:41:46,086
But Huan Wen held back.

2358
01:41:46,086 --> 01:41:47,086
Three years later, Jiang Bo died.

2359
01:41:47,086 --> 01:41:48,078
Jiang Bo died.

2360
01:41:48,078 --> 01:41:49,086
At the funeral, Huan Wen killed Jiang Bo's three sons.

2361
01:41:49,086 --> 01:41:51,082
Huan Wen killed Jiang Bo's three sons.

2362
01:41:51,082 --> 01:41:53,092
Huan Wen held the imperial court in awe.

2363
01:41:53,092 --> 01:41:58,069
This act of avenging his kinsmen with such composure later became a model of virtue for the young men of the Eastern Jin Dynasty.

2364
01:41:58,069 --> 01:42:00,045
When the lawsuit finally reaches its end,

2365
01:42:00,045 --> 01:42:04,030
The feud between the two sides had, in fact, escalated far beyond the original incident.

2366
01:42:04,030 --> 01:42:09,070
And this escalating hatred will plunge both families into an endless, inescapable hell!

2367
01:42:09,070 --> 01:42:12,094
Regardless of who wins or loses, both sides will be financially drained.

2368
01:42:12,094 --> 01:42:17,006
And on top of that, they would have to bear the endless future costs of guarding against revenge!

2369
01:42:17,006 --> 01:42:20,056
In ancient times, one had to maintain a constant sense of awe and reverence towards lawsuits.

2370
01:42:20,056 --> 01:42:25,000
You should even see it as a terrifying beast! The government isn't there to give you justice or clear your name.

2371
01:42:25,000 --> 01:42:27,032
He's a living King of Hell who devours people without spitting out the bones!

2372
01:42:27,032 --> 01:42:29,030
Litigation should only be used as a deterrent.

2373
01:42:29,030 --> 01:42:32,080
The best way forward is to know when to stop, as it's better to resolve a feud than to escalate it.

2374
01:42:32,080 --> 01:42:35,059
If you pursue litigation to the bitter end, everything will turn out badly!

2375
01:42:35,059 --> 01:42:40,055
This line from the Xiang Zhuan, "Heaven and water move in different directions, giving rise to the image of contention. The superior person, in his undertakings, plans the beginning."

2376
01:42:40,055 --> 01:42:42,073
This once again serves as a warning about the core principle of this hexagram.

2377
01:42:42,073 --> 01:42:44,069
Heaven moves westward, while water flows eastward.

2378
01:42:44,069 --> 01:42:46,061
This hexagram is inherently about moving in opposite directions.

2379
01:42:46,061 --> 01:42:48,005
When it comes to this matter of contention,

2380
01:42:48,005 --> 01:42:49,028
A noble person must "plan for the beginning when starting a task."

2381
01:42:49,028 --> 01:42:53,020
In other words, you have to plan for the beginning right from the very start.

2382
01:42:53,020 --> 01:42:55,072
Define the rules and clarify the boundaries in advance.

2383
01:42:55,072 --> 01:43:00,016
So, from the very root of the matter, you must do everything possible to avoid reaching the point of litigation.

2384
01:43:00,016 --> 01:43:04,028
as a guiding principle for how we conduct ourselves in life.

2385
01:43:04,028 --> 01:43:06,064
Now, let's look at the line statements. The lower trigram of the 'Dispute' hexagram is 'Kǎn', which represents danger.

2386
01:43:06,064 --> 01:43:08,038
This means that right from the start, it's fraught with danger.

2387
01:43:08,038 --> 01:43:10,078
The first six, a yin line, is in a yang position, which is an improper placement.

2388
01:43:10,078 --> 01:43:12,012
This position, which should be occupied by a strong, masculine force, is instead taken by a soft, feminine one from the very beginning.

2389
01:43:12,012 --> 01:43:13,082
but instead, it's handled with a soft and yielding approach from the very beginning.

2390
01:43:13,082 --> 01:43:16,050
The very beginning of the Song Hexagram serves as a reminder that its core principle is to be prudent and avoid litigation.

2391
01:43:16,050 --> 01:43:18,054
This is the core tenet of the Song hexagram.

2392
01:43:18,054 --> 01:43:19,054
Do not prolong the matter; though there is some talk, it will ultimately be auspicious.

2393
01:43:19,054 --> 01:43:21,094
In the phrase '不永所事', '永' means 'long-lasting' or 'permanent'.

2394
01:43:21,094 --> 01:43:23,092
Here, "yong" means to be long-lasting or to continue for a long time.

2395
01:43:23,092 --> 01:43:25,020
This line from the hexagram means...

2396
01:43:25,020 --> 01:43:27,088
Do not get bogged down in a dispute that has just arisen.

2397
01:43:27,088 --> 01:43:29,032
Don't blow small things out of proportion.

2398
01:43:29,032 --> 01:43:30,076
Do not be the first to initiate a lawsuit.

2399
01:43:30,076 --> 01:43:33,080
Even if you're in the right, it's best to cut your losses and stop the conflict as soon as possible.

2400
01:43:33,080 --> 01:43:36,008
The commentary in the Xiang Zhuan states: 'Do not persist in the matter of litigation, for it cannot be prolonged.'

2401
01:43:36,008 --> 01:43:37,096
Disputes should not be prolonged.

2402
01:43:37,096 --> 01:43:40,078
This kind of dispute absolutely cannot be allowed to drag on.

2403
01:43:40,078 --> 01:43:42,012
We've already covered the reasons for this.

2404
01:43:42,012 --> 01:43:43,090
Once your case is on the government's record,

2405
01:43:43,090 --> 01:43:46,086
and closing the case is no longer up to you.

2406
01:43:46,086 --> 01:43:49,064
From the county magistrate, his advisors, and the clerks, to the bailiffs and runners...

2407
01:43:49,064 --> 01:43:51,042
If you fail to grease the palm of even one of them,

2408
01:43:53,096 --> 01:43:57,088
They have what you might call a 'legal right to harm' you. Even if it's just summoning you back and forth to 'discuss the case'.

2409
01:43:57,088 --> 01:43:59,006
Can you take the heat?

2410
01:43:59,006 --> 01:44:01,046
And that's not even mentioning if the other side is throwing a lot of money at the problem.

2411
01:44:01,046 --> 01:44:04,013
They can even fabricate evidence to completely destroy you!

2412
01:44:04,013 --> 01:44:05,074
“Minor complaints, but ultimate good fortune.”

2413
01:44:05,074 --> 01:44:08,092
Even if it means swallowing their pride just to keep the peace,

2414
01:44:08,092 --> 01:44:10,076
You'll be mocked by the onlookers.

2415
01:44:10,076 --> 01:44:14,046
But we jumped out of the black hole of controversy from the very beginning.

2416
01:44:14,046 --> 01:44:18,088
This prevents the endless drain and potential disaster that come with an escalating conflict.

2417
01:44:18,088 --> 01:44:22,080
This allows us to focus our resources, energy, and time on expanding the pie.

2418
01:44:22,080 --> 01:44:27,000
A noble person asks about disaster, not fortune. For a noble person, the absence of disaster is fortune itself.

2419
01:44:27,000 --> 01:44:29,072
The Xiang Zhuan says, "Although there are minor disagreements, it is through these that clarity is achieved."

2420
01:44:29,072 --> 01:44:31,012
The text says 'to clarify', not 'to win the argument'.

2421
01:44:31,012 --> 01:44:32,041
not to win the argument.

2422
01:44:32,041 --> 01:44:34,019
When a conflict arises between two parties,

2423
01:44:34,019 --> 01:44:36,021
Let's sit down and lay all the cards on the table.

2424
01:44:36,021 --> 01:44:38,065
Clarify the facts and explain the reasoning.

2425
01:44:38,065 --> 01:44:41,009
I took a loss, but I know you didn't do it on purpose.

2426
01:44:41,009 --> 01:44:41,089
I'll do you the favor, let's just avoid this in the future.

2427
01:44:41,089 --> 01:44:45,020
If you've taken a loss, I'll give you fair compensation.

2428
01:44:45,020 --> 01:44:48,018
Forget about winning or losing, it's all about the interests. That's it.

2429
01:44:48,018 --> 01:44:50,063
But when it's about winning or losing, people get emotional.

2430
01:44:50,063 --> 01:44:52,045
Who's right or wrong doesn't matter.

2431
01:44:52,045 --> 01:44:54,071
But when you boil it down to the actual benefits and do the math,

2432
01:44:54,071 --> 01:44:56,035
and all that anger just melts away.

2433
01:44:56,035 --> 01:44:59,040
If you gotta pay, you pay. If you gotta haggle, you haggle. It's all about the money, right?

2434
01:44:59,040 --> 01:45:00,088
Besides, it's not like we're pushovers who just let people walk all over us.

2435
01:45:00,088 --> 01:45:02,002
or just let you walk all over us.

2436
01:45:02,002 --> 01:45:04,089
We're not afraid to face the law or even a knife fight, and we'll take full responsibility for our actions.

2437
01:45:04,089 --> 01:45:08,097
But what's the point of us both ending up losers? There's no point.

2438
01:45:08,097 --> 01:45:10,028
Let's just talk it out.

2439
01:45:10,028 --> 01:45:13,052
We'll be seeing a lot of each other down the road, so we've got to keep things friendly to make money, right?

2440
01:45:13,052 --> 01:45:18,001
The vast majority of disasters and internal conflicts stem from the endless escalation of trivial matters.

2441
01:45:18,001 --> 01:45:21,099
When any conflict arises, your first instinct should always be to prevent it from escalating.

2442
01:45:21,099 --> 01:45:25,037
Always remember: seek profit, not a fight. Address the issue, not the person.

2443
01:45:25,037 --> 01:45:28,047
Once the truth is discerned, stop there, and you will ultimately achieve good fortune.

2444
01:45:28,047 --> 01:45:29,079
Now, for the second line, let's look at its statement.

2445
01:45:29,079 --> 01:45:30,091
If you cannot win the dispute, retreat and flee.

2446
01:45:30,091 --> 01:45:32,089
The three hundred households in his town will be free from blame.

2447
01:45:32,089 --> 01:45:35,006
The character '克' (kè) here means 'to be capable of' or 'to be competent for'.

2448
01:45:35,006 --> 01:45:36,036
It does not imply retreat.

2449
01:45:36,036 --> 01:45:38,002
The original meaning of the character "shěng" is a film or opacity growing over the eye.

2450
01:45:38,002 --> 01:45:39,046
and by extension, it came to mean disaster.

2451
01:45:39,046 --> 01:45:40,067
The meaning of this line is...

2452
01:45:40,067 --> 01:45:42,023
If you can't hold back from that first step,

2453
01:45:42,023 --> 01:45:43,075
the lawsuit is inevitable.

2454
01:45:43,075 --> 01:45:49,032
But if you have a hunch that you're simply no match for them in terms of resources and status in this conflict,

2455
01:45:49,032 --> 01:45:50,088
Continuing will lead to certain defeat.

2456
01:45:50,088 --> 01:45:52,098
Then you must stop the confrontation immediately.

2457
01:45:52,098 --> 01:45:56,068
Just bite the bullet, sheathe your锋芒, and retreat to a place where you pose no threat.

2458
01:45:56,068 --> 01:46:00,030
The character '窜' (cuàn) in this line from the Xiang Zhuan, 'Unable to win the lawsuit, he flees and escapes,' is particularly well-chosen.

2459
01:46:00,030 --> 01:46:01,062
It's a perfect description.

2460
01:46:01,062 --> 01:46:05,057
It means making a swift and decisive retreat, as fast as possible.

2461
01:46:05,057 --> 01:46:09,062
The phrase 'a fief of two hundred households' refers to the smallest landed estate granted to a junior minister in the pre-Qin period.

2462
01:46:09,062 --> 01:46:11,054
It was the smallest fiefdom size, posing the least threat.

2463
01:46:11,054 --> 01:46:13,044
This shows an attitude of conceding defeat.

2464
01:46:13,044 --> 01:46:15,052
as long as you can pull back in time to cut your losses,

2465
01:46:15,052 --> 01:46:17,095
we can still protect our last remaining asset.

2466
01:46:17,095 --> 01:46:19,087
And this stronghold you've retreated to will no longer pose a threat to your adversary.

2467
01:46:19,087 --> 01:46:22,010
and won't pose a threat to your opponent in the dispute.

2468
01:46:22,010 --> 01:46:24,056
This is also a way to show, through your actions, that you've completely surrendered.

2469
01:46:24,056 --> 01:46:27,062
This way, you can avoid disaster, settle the score, and preserve your vital resources.

2470
01:46:27,062 --> 01:46:29,074
When many people run into conflicts and disputes,

2471
01:46:29,074 --> 01:46:31,044
Even when they know they can't win,

2472
01:46:31,044 --> 01:46:33,046
but are dragged down and ultimately destroyed by their own pride.

2473
01:46:33,046 --> 01:46:36,002
All because they can't swallow their pride, they insist on fighting to the bitter end.

2474
01:46:36,002 --> 01:46:38,054
Ultimately, they exhaust all their time, energy, and resources.

2475
01:46:38,054 --> 01:46:41,014
dragging their families down with them, and even losing their lives in the process.

2476
01:46:41,014 --> 01:46:43,016
When we were discussing 'The Mirror of Rise and Fall'...

2477
01:46:43,016 --> 01:46:46,057
We've talked about how big corporations use lawsuits to bleed out and crush small businesses.

2478
01:46:46,057 --> 01:46:48,050
When we were discussing the second line of the Qian hexagram, 'A dragon appearing in the field is favorable to see the great man',

2479
01:46:48,050 --> 01:46:51,010
and we said something similar when discussing the line 'A dragon appearing in the field is favorable to meet the great man'.

2480
01:46:51,010 --> 01:46:53,060
If you're being squeezed out by a 'great man',

2481
01:46:53,060 --> 01:46:55,096
then you need to find another 'great man' to rescue you.

2482
01:46:55,096 --> 01:46:57,024
So, in this situation, let's say you're a small company...

2483
01:46:57,024 --> 01:47:01,078
What if you get targeted by a big corporation before you're even ready?

2484
01:47:01,078 --> 01:47:03,090
He's just going to bleed you dry and drag you to your death.

2485
01:47:03,090 --> 01:47:06,057
So, swallow your pride and negotiate an acquisition with them immediately.

2486
01:47:06,057 --> 01:47:08,094
If he refuses, it means he's out to destroy you.

2487
01:47:08,094 --> 01:47:11,020
Then go talk to their competitor about an acquisition.

2488
01:47:11,020 --> 01:47:14,022
Save as many resources as you possibly can.

2489
01:47:14,022 --> 01:47:16,094
At this point, the core objective is to minimize losses as much as possible.

2490
01:47:16,094 --> 01:47:19,016
As long as our price is lower than the market price,

2491
01:47:19,016 --> 01:47:22,070
Whether it's the company that's trying to harm us, or its competitors,

2492
01:47:22,070 --> 01:47:25,024
will be interested in acquiring us.

2493
01:47:25,024 --> 01:47:27,016
And so, we were able to 'return and save our three hundred households from harm'.

2494
01:47:27,016 --> 01:47:27,070
three hundred households

2495
01:47:27,070 --> 01:47:30,070
We've managed to pull ourselves out of the vortex of confrontation.

2496
01:47:30,070 --> 01:47:32,036
Maybe we did sell it for a pittance.

2497
01:47:32,036 --> 01:47:34,048
Perhaps the future prospects were snuffed out.

2498
01:47:34,048 --> 01:47:36,080
But at least we've saved our skin.

2499
01:47:36,080 --> 01:47:38,009
There will be other opportunities in the future.

2500
01:47:38,009 --> 01:47:40,013
After the "Dragon in the Field" fails to "see the great man,"

2501
01:47:40,013 --> 01:47:42,065
It's not like you're the Leaping Dragon, destined to be crushed to pieces.

2502
01:47:42,065 --> 01:47:45,037
Just go back to being a 'Hidden Dragon' and start all over again!

2503
01:47:45,037 --> 01:47:48,063
Never assume that just because you're in the right, you have to pursue justice.

2504
01:47:48,063 --> 01:47:53,020
In ancient times, if you were an adult and still believed in things like justice and truth,

2505
01:47:53,020 --> 01:47:55,017
That just means you've never really grown up.

2506
01:47:55,017 --> 01:47:57,059
This line from the Xiang Zhuan is the most sobering of all.

2507
01:47:57,059 --> 01:47:59,083
When the lower disputes with the higher, disaster is imminent.

2508
01:47:59,083 --> 01:48:01,057
At best, it's just a token gesture of praise.

2509
01:48:01,057 --> 01:48:04,050
When it comes to conflict, it's not really about who's right or wrong.

2510
01:48:04,050 --> 01:48:07,022
Instead, it's simply a matter of weighing the strengths and weaknesses of the opposing sides.

2511
01:48:07,022 --> 01:48:10,012
Being in the lower trigram means you're the weaker party.

2512
01:48:10,012 --> 01:48:12,012
If you, being in a lower position, decide to contend with those above you,

2513
01:48:12,012 --> 01:48:13,049
challenging the strong as the weak.

2514
01:48:13,049 --> 01:48:17,003
When there's a complete imbalance in status, power, and resources,

2515
01:48:17,003 --> 01:48:18,069
and still insist on taking them to court.

2516
01:48:18,069 --> 01:48:21,015
In that case, you have no one to blame but yourself for the trouble that follows.

2517
01:48:21,015 --> 01:48:22,057
The vast majority of disasters,

2518
01:48:22,057 --> 01:48:24,088
Or they're brought on by your own stubbornness and competitiveness.

2519
01:48:24,088 --> 01:48:27,030
or they stem from our own naivety and delusions, from not knowing when to advance or retreat.

2520
01:48:27,030 --> 01:48:30,024
or brought on by not understanding the unwritten rules of the real world. Take our creative ideas, for instance.

2521
01:48:30,024 --> 01:48:33,082
The path we've just pioneered might get stolen by a big corporation.

2522
01:48:33,082 --> 01:48:36,021
We feel wronged, and we want to fight to the bitter end, but that's just not necessary.

2523
01:48:36,021 --> 01:48:37,065
There's just no need for that.

2524
01:48:37,065 --> 01:48:41,011
This has been a reality since ancient times: the strong prey on the weak.

2525
01:48:41,011 --> 01:48:42,069
We have to face reality.

2526
01:48:42,069 --> 01:48:44,095
You're just an Apple, crushed by Microsoft.

2527
01:48:44,095 --> 01:48:46,027
Once you rise to the top, you too will become the very dragon you once sought to slay.

2528
01:48:46,027 --> 01:48:48,059
Big

2529
01:48:48,059 --> 01:48:50,022
Because human nature never changes.

2530
01:48:50,022 --> 01:48:52,028
What we need to do is recognize these principles and get things done.

2531
01:48:52,028 --> 01:48:57,091
Knowing when to cut your losses and admit defeat is all part of getting things done.

2532
01:48:57,091 --> 01:49:02,037
Now, for the third six. Let's look at the line statement: 'Feasting on the old virtue, firmness in danger, and finally, good fortune.'

2533
01:49:02,037 --> 01:49:05,044
This means to adhere to established rules and cherish the legacy of your predecessors.

2534
01:49:05,044 --> 01:49:08,080
On one hand, this phrase 'enjoying the old virtue' means you should stick to your own duties.

2535
01:49:08,080 --> 01:49:10,096
Do not covet benefits or positions that are not rightfully yours.

2536
01:49:10,096 --> 01:49:12,006
and not stir up trouble.

2537
01:49:12,006 --> 01:49:13,032
and avoid picking fights.

2538
01:49:13,032 --> 01:49:14,044
On the other hand, it means that

2539
01:49:14,044 --> 01:49:16,026
Even when you find yourself in the middle of a dispute,

2540
01:49:16,026 --> 01:49:17,056
Alternatively, you can keep a low profile while seeking out the wisdom and virtues of the older generation.

2541
01:49:17,056 --> 01:49:21,022
while also seeking the virtues of the older generation to mediate and communicate.

2542
01:49:21,022 --> 01:49:24,088
The core idea is just one thing: to calm things down and make peace. As long as you can stop and cut your losses,

2543
01:49:24,088 --> 01:49:26,056
then the crisis will inevitably be resolved.

2544
01:49:26,056 --> 01:49:28,048
And the commentary from the 'Xiang Zhuan,' which says, 'Following the established virtues brings good fortune,' is also a very insightful addition.

2545
01:49:28,048 --> 01:49:30,079
The addition, 'following the superior,' is also quite insightful.

2546
01:49:30,079 --> 01:49:33,023
As the lower trigram, as the subordinate,

2547
01:49:33,023 --> 01:49:35,025
Stay true to your own duties and established virtues.

2548
01:49:35,025 --> 01:49:36,007
Do not engage in pointless disputes.

2549
01:49:36,007 --> 01:49:37,001
Don't go looking for trouble.

2550
01:49:37,001 --> 01:49:40,014
These are the rules that those in power expect you to follow.

2551
01:49:40,014 --> 01:49:43,030
The higher-ups don't want their subordinates constantly causing trouble for them.

2552
01:49:43,030 --> 01:49:44,068
You need to handle the mess yourself.

2553
01:49:44,068 --> 01:49:47,076
What the higher-ups expect from you is that you keep your own house in order.

2554
01:49:47,076 --> 01:49:49,010
and hand over the profits.

2555
01:49:49,010 --> 01:49:51,034
What's emphasized is a state of peace and stability.

2556
01:49:51,034 --> 01:49:53,042
But if your superiors see you as a troublemaker,

2557
01:49:53,042 --> 01:49:54,092
your journey will come to an end.

2558
01:49:54,092 --> 01:49:56,088
When the powers that be see you as someone who only brings profit, not trouble,

2559
01:49:56,088 --> 01:49:58,008
and you're only bringing in the profits,

2560
01:49:58,008 --> 01:50:00,004
Only then will you become more stable and prosperous.

2561
01:50:00,004 --> 01:50:02,057
And purely from a developmental perspective,

2562
01:50:02,057 --> 01:50:03,090
The reason we stand out is also because...

2563
01:50:03,090 --> 01:50:07,025
the strengthening of our own capabilities and our ability to solve problems.

2564
01:50:07,025 --> 01:50:08,093
In an environment rife with controversy,

2565
01:50:08,093 --> 01:50:11,078
The safest path is always to stick to the right way and stay true to your own course.

2566
01:50:11,078 --> 01:50:14,084
and leave your competitors far behind through steady, daily progress.

2567
01:50:14,084 --> 01:50:17,086
While the apes on the banks wail without cease, the light boat has already passed ten thousand mountains.

2568
01:50:17,086 --> 01:50:22,036
Development and progress have never been about picking fights or trying to be the strongest.

2569
01:50:22,036 --> 01:50:23,072
or how many lawsuits you win,

2570
01:50:23,072 --> 01:50:25,004
or winning countless arguments.

2571
01:50:25,004 --> 01:50:27,042
Instead, it's about doing your own job well from the very beginning.

2572
01:50:27,042 --> 01:50:29,028
and to avoid getting mired in disputes.

2573
01:50:29,028 --> 01:50:30,052
The latter part of this line, 'or to serve the king, but without success'...

2574
01:50:30,052 --> 01:50:34,065
It also points out the sources of many of our unexpected misfortunes.

2575
01:50:34,065 --> 01:50:37,041
We've actually covered this line before, back when we were discussing the third six of the Kun hexagram.

2576
01:50:37,041 --> 01:50:40,011
Now, this 'no success' doesn't mean you're incapable of achieving anything.

2577
01:50:40,011 --> 01:50:42,066
Instead, it means not claiming credit for your achievements and not being greedy for success.

2578
01:50:42,066 --> 01:50:44,070
If we are the ones who get things done,

2579
01:50:44,070 --> 01:50:46,080
and then attribute the credit to your superiors.

2580
01:50:46,080 --> 01:50:48,028
so as not to overshadow your superior with your achievements.

2581
01:50:48,028 --> 01:50:51,001
The third six is a yin line in a yang position, which is an improper placement.

2582
01:50:51,001 --> 01:50:52,067
You are at the very heart of the peril.

2583
01:50:52,067 --> 01:50:59,007
So, the emphasis of the third six is on 'attributing the achievements of the lower to the higher.'

2584
01:50:59,007 --> 01:51:00,031
If you don't understand that 'carrying out the superior's work' is the next best thing,

2585
01:51:00,031 --> 01:51:01,075
Evil is bestowed by the superior.

2586
01:51:01,075 --> 01:51:03,043
Assessment comes first, action second.

2587
01:51:03,043 --> 01:51:05,002
Authority is a gift bestowed by others, and this act of bestowing it is of the utmost importance.

2588
01:51:05,002 --> 01:51:07,086
If you don't get the fact that the only way for you to advance is to help your superiors get ahead,

2589
01:51:07,086 --> 01:51:08,070
you can truly advance.

2590
01:51:08,070 --> 01:51:09,024
this principle

2591
01:51:09,024 --> 01:51:12,070
Then you, the little go-getter who takes all the credit, are just asking for trouble.

2592
01:51:12,070 --> 01:51:15,066
You'll bring a lot of unwarranted disasters upon yourself.

2593
01:51:15,066 --> 01:51:21,081
If you don't yield the credit, the higher-ups have plenty of ways to turn a 'good comrade' like you into a 'bad one'.

2594
01:51:21,081 --> 01:51:23,095
And just like that, they'll block your path to advancement.

2595
01:51:23,095 --> 01:51:26,089
How did Deng Ai, a hero who conquered a kingdom, get thrown into a prisoner's cart by Zhong Hui in a single day?

2596
01:51:26,089 --> 01:51:28,077
thrown into a prison cart in a single move.

2597
01:51:28,077 --> 01:51:32,009
How did Shi Wansui, the Turks' worst nightmare, end up being framed by Yang Su and executed in the imperial court?

2598
01:51:32,009 --> 01:51:36,074
When you are in a subordinate position, you must always be aware of your place.

2599
01:51:36,074 --> 01:51:38,092
Always remember the rules of this world.

2600
01:51:38,092 --> 01:51:43,044
Even in the Qian Gua, the second nine line says, 'A dragon appears in the field. It is beneficial to see the great man.'

2601
01:51:43,044 --> 01:51:44,066
You need someone to give you a leg up.

2602
01:51:44,066 --> 01:51:48,008
Even at the Ninth Two line, you must be vigilant from morning till night, or you'll fail to catch the eye of those above you.

2603
01:51:48,008 --> 01:51:52,028
And whatever you do, don't ever think this world is a fair system where your efforts are guaranteed to pay off.

2604
01:51:52,028 --> 01:51:55,007
Instead, it's a world where the advantaged destroy the disadvantaged.

2605
01:51:55,007 --> 01:51:58,079
Every underdog who rises to the top does so by clinging to the powerful and leveraging their strength.

2606
01:51:58,079 --> 01:52:00,003
Liu Bang, before he started, had the backing of the Xiang family.

2607
01:52:00,003 --> 01:52:02,040
Before Liu Bang started his rise, he was backed by the Xiang family.

2608
01:52:02,040 --> 01:52:04,044
When Liu Xiu entered Hebei, he relied on the Twenty-Eight Generals of Yuntai.

2609
01:52:04,044 --> 01:52:05,032
the 28 Generals.

2610
01:52:05,032 --> 01:52:09,044
Cao Cao, who fought his way out of the chaos at the end of the Han Dynasty, initially relied on the banner of Yuan Shao and the authority of the Han court.

2611
01:52:09,044 --> 01:52:11,096
Build high walls, stockpile grain, and delay proclaiming yourself king.

2612
01:52:11,096 --> 01:52:14,068
Even when you are in a position of power, you should still stay away from disputes.

2613
01:52:14,068 --> 01:52:16,040
We'll get to that in a moment.

2614
01:52:16,040 --> 01:52:19,090
And if you're in a lower position, it's even more crucial to stay away from legal disputes!

2615
01:52:19,090 --> 01:52:22,018
The fourth nine, the line statement: 'Not winning the lawsuit, return to the original mandate, change, and be steadfast in what is right. Good fortune.'

2616
01:52:22,018 --> 01:52:25,044
Now, the situation for the fourth line is just like the second.

2617
01:52:25,044 --> 01:52:26,034
Here, the phrase "unable to win the lawsuit" appears.

2618
01:52:26,034 --> 01:52:28,024
But a different position means a different meaning.

2619
01:52:28,024 --> 01:52:30,064
In the case of the second nine, it's in the lower trigram, so it represents a subordinate challenging a superior, an inferior confronting a superior.

2620
01:52:30,064 --> 01:52:33,081
When the subordinate challenges the superior, the weaker party has no inherent chance of winning.

2621
01:52:33,081 --> 01:52:36,093
The fourth line, the Nine-Four, is in the upper trigram, but it is a solid line in a soft position.

2622
01:52:36,093 --> 01:52:38,001
This is not its rightful place.

2623
01:52:38,001 --> 01:52:41,055
The fourth line, being close to the ruler's position like a high minister, should be humble and obedient to the one above.

2624
01:52:41,055 --> 01:52:43,066
However, it's placed at the beginning of the Qian trigram.

2625
01:52:43,066 --> 01:52:46,014


2626
01:52:46,014 --> 01:52:49,010
This 'failure to win the lawsuit' implies that the strong are bullying the weak.

2627
01:52:49,010 --> 01:52:51,008
This means that after gaining power, resources, and a judicial advantage,

2628
01:52:51,008 --> 01:52:52,004
and judicial advantage,

2629
01:52:52,004 --> 01:52:54,092
They start to actively provoke conflicts and prey on the weak.

2630
01:52:54,092 --> 01:52:57,014
But because this goes against the natural order and is not the righteous path,

2631
01:52:57,014 --> 01:52:58,064
Even if they gain the upper hand for a time,

2632
01:52:58,064 --> 01:53:00,042
But in the end, it will backfire on them.

2633
01:53:03,020 --> 01:53:06,094
When a subordinate official provokes the wrath of the masses, those in power will often execute them to appease the people's anger.

2634
01:53:06,094 --> 01:53:12,001
Getting rid of those who bully the weak and abuse their power is actually the lowest-cost solution for society.

2635
01:53:12,001 --> 01:53:13,087
and the most effective pressure release valve.

2636
01:53:13,087 --> 01:53:16,019
And this is exactly what the Ninth Five loves to do.

2637
01:53:16,019 --> 01:53:17,081
In our 'Mirror of Rise and Fall' series, we've talked about the tactic of 'using Heaven's name to blame others and hide one's own selfish motives.'

2638
01:53:17,081 --> 01:53:19,015
Using the heavens to judge others and conceal one's own selfish motives.

2639
01:53:19,015 --> 01:53:19,054
selfish

2640
01:53:19,054 --> 01:53:20,042
under the guise of the "Will of Heaven," the "Mandate of Heaven," or "national law,"

2641
01:53:20,042 --> 01:53:23,012
and attack their targets in the name of a supreme authority.

2642
01:53:23,012 --> 01:53:25,018
exploiting the guise of public justice to conceal their own selfish desires.

2643
01:53:25,018 --> 01:53:26,056
and under the guise of 'acting on Heaven's behalf,' forcibly label their opponents as reactionaries.

2644
01:53:28,047 --> 01:53:30,033
and "Gaining trust by speaking in the people's name."

2645
01:53:30,033 --> 01:53:33,019
in the name of the people, the wishes of the common folk, or the voice of the masses.

2646
01:53:33,019 --> 01:53:35,057
and package his own agenda as 'acting in accordance with the will of the people'.

2647
01:53:35,057 --> 01:53:38,056
using the voice of the masses to cover up one's autocratic intentions.

2648
01:53:38,056 --> 01:53:41,039
and make their own schemes appear to be the choice of the masses.

2649
01:53:41,039 --> 01:53:43,095
Never, ever take public opinion lightly.

2650
01:53:43,095 --> 01:53:46,014
And when they want to take you down, it's the sharpest knife they have!

2651
01:53:46,014 --> 01:53:48,098
Go with the flow, or you'll be branded a rebel.

2652
01:53:48,098 --> 01:53:49,070
And once that label is slapped on you, it's no small matter.

2653
01:53:49,070 --> 01:53:50,086
And that's no small matter.

2654
01:53:50,086 --> 01:53:52,040
Whatever you do, don't become a traitor to the people.

2655
01:53:52,040 --> 01:53:54,095
To return to one's destiny, even if it changes, and to remain steadfast and upright brings good fortune.

2656
01:53:54,095 --> 01:53:56,019
Here, "复" (fù) means to return, and "渝" (yú) means to change.

2657
01:53:56,019 --> 01:53:57,041
I interpret it as the meaning of change.

2658
01:54:00,017 --> 01:54:01,098
If those in power who prey on the weak can realize their mistakes,

2659
01:54:01,098 --> 01:54:05,000
and are able to turn back from their mistakes and return to the righteous path of the natural order,

2660
01:54:05,000 --> 01:54:07,070
in the end, they can still hold fast to the right path and achieve a favorable outcome.

2661
01:54:07,070 --> 01:54:08,093
and receive good fortune nine times.

2662
01:54:08,093 --> 01:54:11,077
The reason why the fourth nine line should not bully the weak is that...

2663
01:54:11,077 --> 01:54:13,071
Because it presents three major hidden dangers for you.

2664
01:54:13,071 --> 01:54:16,056
First, the family you've bullied and brought to ruin.

2665
01:54:16,056 --> 01:54:19,010
You'll be forging a feud, a vendetta, that will last until one side is utterly destroyed.

2666
01:54:19,010 --> 01:54:21,074
And are you so sure you can wipe them out, root and stem?

2667
01:54:21,074 --> 01:54:25,072
It's not the theft you should fear, but the thief who's always watching. The cost of being on constant guard is just too high.

2668
01:54:25,072 --> 01:54:28,084
Besides, what if he happens to have a brother named Wu Song?

2669
01:54:28,084 --> 01:54:30,096
Second, if you go too far...

2670
01:54:30,096 --> 01:54:33,092
The Ninth Five, acting on Heaven's behalf, will punish and eliminate you to quell the public's outrage.

2671
01:54:33,092 --> 01:54:36,030
All the profits you've made from bullying the weak,

2672
01:54:36,030 --> 01:54:39,020
will all become the spoils for the Ninth Five to carry out Heaven's will.

2673
01:54:39,020 --> 01:54:40,018
In ancient times,

2674
01:54:40,018 --> 01:54:44,060
Confiscating property was a key method for replenishing the national treasury and the emperor's personal coffers.

2675
01:54:44,060 --> 01:54:47,014
Third, even though you're in a position of advantage,

2676
01:54:47,014 --> 01:54:49,050
But at the end of the day, you're not the one sitting on the throne.

2677
01:54:49,050 --> 01:54:51,076
You're not the one who has the final say in everything.

2678
01:54:51,076 --> 01:54:53,082
What if your opponent has connections that reach the heavens?

2679
01:54:53,082 --> 01:54:56,084
What if the person you've just messed with has someone powerful backing them up, someone you can't afford to cross?

2680
01:54:56,084 --> 01:54:58,028
What if it's just a huge coincidence?

2681
01:54:58,028 --> 01:55:00,034
Yang Naiwu had a classmate named Wu Yitong.

2682
01:55:00,034 --> 01:55:02,006
And Wu Yitong's boss was Hu Xueyan.

2683
01:55:02,006 --> 01:55:03,072
And as it turns out, Hu Xueyan also knew Weng Tonghe.

2684
01:55:03,072 --> 01:55:06,096
Could it be that someone was trying to use this incident to shake up the imperial court?

2685
01:55:06,096 --> 01:55:09,073
So, the point is, even if you're in a position of advantage,

2686
01:55:09,073 --> 01:55:11,079
nor should you bully the weak with your power.

2687
01:55:11,079 --> 01:55:15,076
And especially, you must never twist the law to harm the innocent!

2688
01:55:17,096 --> 01:55:20,096
When it comes to bullying those in a weaker position, they do indeed have an inherent advantage.

2689
01:55:22,092 --> 01:55:24,069
For the subordinate to challenge the superior is to invite disaster and flee in disgrace.

2690
01:55:24,069 --> 01:55:27,059
If you don't run fast enough, you're going to die a horrible death.

2691
01:55:27,059 --> 01:55:29,082
But for the one in power, as long as they are willing to turn back,

2692
01:55:29,082 --> 01:55:31,066
That's already giving the victim too much credit.

2693
01:55:31,066 --> 01:55:33,030
This is all about returning to the right path.

2694
01:55:33,030 --> 01:55:35,004
Change your heart, and disputes will dissolve. Return to the right path, and disaster will vanish.

2695
01:55:35,004 --> 01:55:36,059
Return to the right path, and disaster will dissipate.

2696
01:55:36,059 --> 01:55:38,071
To recognize and correct one's mistakes is a great virtue.

2697
01:55:38,071 --> 01:55:42,091
This is especially true when you're in a position of power and the victim is less fortunate.

2698
01:55:42,091 --> 01:55:44,099
Turn back, and you'll have a chance.

2699
01:55:44,099 --> 01:55:49,005
The real world already gives those in power so many advantages.

2700
01:55:49,005 --> 01:55:50,067
All you have to do is turn back.

2701
01:55:50,067 --> 01:55:51,071
Don't be a fool and refuse a good offer.

2702
01:55:51,071 --> 01:55:52,069
Ah.

2703
01:55:52,069 --> 01:55:54,017
The fifth nine.

2704
01:55:54,017 --> 01:55:59,059
The line statement says, 'In litigation, great fortune.' Now, when you see that, don't jump to the conclusion that going to court is a guaranteed win, okay?

2705
01:55:59,059 --> 01:56:01,070
that you'll win just by taking the case to court.

2706
01:56:01,070 --> 01:56:03,020
But that's not what this line means at all.

2707
01:56:03,020 --> 01:56:04,038
The fifth, nine, is the position of the ruler.

2708
01:56:04,038 --> 01:56:06,032
It is the position of hearing and adjudicating disputes.

2709
01:56:06,032 --> 01:56:07,014
Not the plaintiff or the defendant.

2710
01:56:07,014 --> 01:56:10,068
This corresponds to the core line from the hexagram's statement: 'It is beneficial to see a great man.'

2711
01:56:10,068 --> 01:56:13,024
This is also further explained by a line from the Tuan Zhuan.

2712
01:56:13,024 --> 01:56:18,092
The text says, 'It is advantageous to see the great man, for he upholds centrality and correctness.' This brings us to the Ninth Five, a yang line in a yang position, the ruler's position, and it is also centered.

2713
01:56:18,092 --> 01:56:20,050
And it's also the only line in the entire hexagram that's in its correct position. So, what does that tell us?

2714
01:56:20,050 --> 01:56:21,094
So, what does this tell us?

2715
01:56:21,094 --> 01:56:25,074
But when it comes to debate, it's the one thing that's all gain and no loss for a ruler.

2716
01:56:25,074 --> 01:56:26,074
Or to be more precise,

2717
01:56:26,074 --> 01:56:28,074
Now, this 'Nine in the Fifth' position isn't just referring to the monarch.

2718
01:56:28,074 --> 01:56:31,027
but rather, it refers to the person in power who holds the ultimate authority to make the final decision.

2719
01:56:31,027 --> 01:56:33,087
In the county, this Ninth Four line would be like Ximen Qing.

2720
01:56:33,087 --> 01:56:37,087
The 9-5 is the county magistrate, and all lawsuits ultimately land on his desk.

2721
01:56:37,087 --> 01:56:39,017


2722
01:56:39,017 --> 01:56:41,021
Because he's the one who makes the final call.

2723
01:56:41,021 --> 01:56:45,033
It's just like the lawsuit between Bai Jingqi from the TV series 'The Grand Mansion Gate' and the Sun family, who stole his medicine formula.

2724
01:56:45,033 --> 01:56:47,056
Bai Jingqi had to pay Jiang Wen.

2725
01:56:47,056 --> 01:56:48,085
The Sun family was dragged into this endless process and had to keep paying up.

2726
01:56:48,085 --> 01:56:50,053
And this endless process meant they had to keep paying up too.

2727
01:56:50,053 --> 01:56:54,087
The ones who hold the final say in any dispute are the ones who love it most when you take each other to court.

2728
01:56:54,087 --> 01:56:56,037
If there were no lawsuits, then what about his advisors and bookkeepers?

2729
01:56:56,037 --> 01:56:58,067
So how were the clerks from the six offices and the bailiffs from the three squads supposed to make a living?

2730
01:56:58,067 --> 01:57:02,067
The imperial court only pays the county magistrate's salary!

2731
01:57:02,067 --> 01:57:04,039
Take Song Jiang, for example. He was a clerk in the county jail.

2732
01:57:04,039 --> 01:57:05,095
And those guys? They didn't get a government salary.

2733
01:57:05,095 --> 01:57:08,071
So, what do you think? Was Song Jiang expecting a paycheck from the county magistrate, or was he making his own money?

2734
01:57:08,071 --> 01:57:09,091
So,

2735
01:57:09,091 --> 01:57:14,057
Of course, it's true that if the dispute reaches the Ninth Five line, the Ninth Five will always come out ahead and never suffer a loss.

2736
01:57:14,057 --> 01:57:17,080
But when it comes to making a profit, you still have to distinguish between short-term gains and long-term benefits.

2737
01:57:17,080 --> 01:57:19,054
Regarding the line statement's mention of "Dispute, supreme good fortune"...

2738
01:57:19,054 --> 01:57:20,006
However,

2739
01:57:20,006 --> 01:57:24,028
The Xiang Zhuan further explains that the great fortune in litigation comes from upholding centrality and correctness, which again emphasizes...

2740
01:57:24,028 --> 01:57:26,042
the person in power who holds the final authority to make a ruling.

2741
01:57:26,042 --> 01:57:28,014
requires a firm and decisive power.

2742
01:57:28,014 --> 01:57:30,044
and a heart of impartial fairness, without bias or favor.

2743
01:57:30,044 --> 01:57:32,046
The ruling must convince both parties, bringing the dispute to a final and peaceful end.

2744
01:57:32,046 --> 01:57:34,072
Ultimately, the dispute is brought to the Nine in the Fifth place.

2745
01:57:34,072 --> 01:57:38,038
The fifth nine line, positioned in the correct place of the Qian trigram, the Heaven, observes the subtle and treacherous rights and wrongs of the disputes below.

2746
01:57:38,038 --> 01:57:40,077
Its duty is to resolve all disputes under heaven.

2747
01:57:40,077 --> 01:57:45,021
This means that all disputes, when they reach this point, can receive a judgment that is acceptable to both parties.

2748
01:57:45,021 --> 01:57:49,005
Its purpose is to cease litigation and resolve conflicts at their very source.

2749
01:57:49,005 --> 01:57:52,005
Let all zero-sum games and internal conflicts end here.

2750
01:57:52,005 --> 01:57:53,046
Once the case is closed, the matter is settled.

2751
01:57:53,046 --> 01:57:56,094
rather than inciting even greater violence and bloodshed down the line.

2752
01:57:56,094 --> 01:58:00,064
The reason this line is described as 'Yuan Ji'—the highest level of auspiciousness...

2753
01:58:00,064 --> 01:58:01,042
This is to say,

2754
01:58:01,042 --> 01:58:04,098
The impartial judgment of the fifth nine, the sovereign position holding the power of final decision,

2755
01:58:04,098 --> 01:58:06,030
In this case,

2756
01:58:06,030 --> 01:58:09,097
and how vital it is for the peace and stability of the people under their jurisdiction!

2757
01:58:09,097 --> 01:58:12,081
A fair and impartial judgment can dispel the hostility in society.

2758
01:58:12,081 --> 01:58:15,071
It prevents the powerful from wantonly bullying the weak,

2759
01:58:15,071 --> 01:58:19,071


2760
01:58:19,071 --> 01:58:21,068
and reduce the overall social cost.

2761
01:58:21,068 --> 01:58:24,057
and to reverse the contentious and unruly atmosphere within the jurisdiction.

2762
01:58:24,057 --> 01:58:29,010
Only then can it be worthy of this fundamental and ultimate auspiciousness—'Great Fortune'!

2763
01:58:29,010 --> 01:58:32,096
And this impartial judgment is also the most crucial element when it comes to getting things done, starting a business, and leading a team.

2764
01:58:32,096 --> 01:58:35,014
Remember when we were discussing the "Power and Its Application" chapter of the "Art of Power"?

2765
01:58:35,014 --> 01:58:38,062
Do you remember how Li Shimin's authority stemmed from his wisdom, his trust from his sincerity, and his success from his harmony?

2766
01:58:38,062 --> 01:58:39,076
and that achievement comes from harmony?

2767
01:58:39,076 --> 01:58:41,030
But we won't go into all that again here.

2768
01:58:41,030 --> 01:58:43,042
If you've forgotten, just go back and check out our video on the Art of Power.

2769
01:58:43,042 --> 01:58:45,027
And here, I also need to point out a common misconception.

2770
01:58:45,027 --> 01:58:47,071
The term 'zhong zheng' doesn't refer to absolute fairness.

2771
01:58:47,071 --> 01:58:49,085
After all, absolute fairness has never existed.

2772
01:58:49,085 --> 01:58:52,077
To be precise, this "zhongzheng" actually means finding a compromise.

2773
01:58:52,077 --> 01:58:56,041
It's about allowing both sides of a dispute to reach an acceptable outcome.

2774
01:58:56,041 --> 01:58:58,086
The core objective is to resolve the conflict.

2775
01:58:58,086 --> 01:59:01,010
and bring the matter to a close.

2776
01:59:01,010 --> 01:59:05,094
This is just like what happened to Yuchi Gong, who was almost killed by that old guard of the Prince of Qin's mansion, Yin Kaishan, and Qu Jiaotong.

2777
01:59:05,094 --> 01:59:08,066
Now, from a standpoint of absolute fairness and justice,

2778
01:59:08,066 --> 01:59:12,018
Yin Kaishan and Qu Jiaotong absolutely should have been punished and held accountable.

2779
01:59:12,018 --> 01:59:13,092
But Li Shimin didn't punish them.

2780
01:59:13,092 --> 01:59:15,082
Because they were the most crucial members of his core team.

2781
01:59:15,082 --> 01:59:18,066
Li Shimin, however, chose to balance the scales from a different perspective.

2782
01:59:18,066 --> 01:59:21,024
On one hand, he rewarded Yuchi Gong generously to appease him.

2783
01:59:21,024 --> 01:59:23,084
On the other hand, he also made Yuchi Gong his personal bodyguard.

2784
01:59:23,084 --> 01:59:25,044
From then on, he no longer had to worry about being backstabbed.

2785
01:59:25,044 --> 01:59:28,000
At the same time, he also had Yuchi Gong earn military merits.

2786
01:59:28,000 --> 01:59:31,012
This also served to humiliate Li Yuanji, proving to the veteran generals why he was so determined to protect this fierce general.

2787
01:59:31,012 --> 01:59:34,009
This simple act of fairness was enough to cause the Prince of Qin's household to fall apart.

2788
01:59:34,009 --> 01:59:36,025
This caused the Prince of Qin's administration to fall apart.

2789
01:59:36,025 --> 01:59:39,047
This made the Prince of Qin seem like someone who favored the new over the old.

2790
01:59:39,047 --> 01:59:41,001
and ensure the loyalty of Yuchi Gong.

2791
01:59:41,001 --> 01:59:42,067
This left the old guards with no room for complaint, forcing them to work even harder in an increasingly cutthroat environment.

2792
01:59:42,067 --> 01:59:44,027
and work even harder in this increasingly competitive environment.

2793
01:59:44,027 --> 01:59:47,014
This is the true meaning of the ninth five's centrality and correctness.

2794
01:59:47,014 --> 01:59:51,008
Now, let's look at the topmost line, the Ninth Yang. It's a yang line in a yin position, which means it's out of place.

2795
01:59:51,008 --> 01:59:54,000
Failing to stop where one should is a sign of obstinacy and self-will.

2796
01:59:54,000 --> 01:59:56,036
Let's look at the hexagram statement: 'Perhaps he will be given a fragrant sash.'

2797
01:59:56,036 --> 02:00:01,013
The character '锡' is interchangeable with '赐', which means 'to bestow', and '鞶带' refers to a wide, leather belt.

2798
02:00:01,013 --> 02:00:02,067
It was part of the official attire for ancient officials.

2799
02:00:02,067 --> 02:00:06,042
This line of the hexagram means that those who win through endless disputes,

2800
02:00:06,042 --> 02:00:09,066
Even if you temporarily gain the status and rewards bestowed by the ruler,

2801
02:00:09,066 --> 02:00:11,086
will also be stripped away in a very short time.

2802
02:00:11,086 --> 02:00:15,050
So, to sum it up: endless litigation leads to ruin, and what's granted in the morning is taken away by evening.

2803
02:00:15,050 --> 02:00:16,070
The reason this happens is that

2804
02:00:16,070 --> 02:00:19,016
This is because your honor and favor are not earned through meritorious deeds,

2805
02:00:19,016 --> 02:00:20,057
earned through establishing your words and character.

2806
02:00:20,057 --> 02:00:24,004
Instead, it's the result of exhausting all arguments, escalating conflicts to the breaking point, and suffering through a brutal internal struggle.

2807
02:00:24,004 --> 02:00:25,042
and won through brutal internal strife.

2808
02:00:25,042 --> 02:00:28,006
Its very origin is tainted, and its virtue is unworthy of its position.

2809
02:00:28,006 --> 02:00:31,036
And on top of that, this endless litigation process will cause you to lose your very foundation.

2810
02:00:31,036 --> 02:00:32,068
and completely drained your own resources.

2811
02:00:32,068 --> 02:00:37,028
You're extremely vulnerable to a third party taking advantage of the situation, like the oriole waiting behind the mantis.

2812
02:00:37,028 --> 02:00:41,004
Every single step of this lawsuit is just a constant drain on your finances.

2813
02:00:41,004 --> 02:00:43,098
No matter how much you're in the right, once a lawsuit drags on for too long,

2814
02:00:43,098 --> 02:00:47,046
Whether it's your superiors, your friends and family, or your neighbors,

2815
02:00:47,046 --> 02:00:50,082
They'll all start to see you as someone who just stirs up trouble and is constantly surrounded by problems.

2816
02:00:50,082 --> 02:00:53,096
This, in fact, is a huge blow to your own reputation.

2817
02:00:53,096 --> 02:00:58,010
This is exactly what the 'Xiang Zhuan' says: 'To win a lawsuit and receive an official position is not worthy of respect!'

2818
02:00:58,010 --> 02:00:59,046
So, the case is over.

2819
02:00:59,046 --> 02:01:04,000
What if another competitor of yours decides to kick you while you're down and files another lawsuit against you?

2820
02:01:04,000 --> 02:01:06,036
Do you really have the financial resources and energy to handle another one?

2821
02:01:06,036 --> 02:01:08,036
Even if you're not afraid, thinking, 'We're in the right, so who are we scared of?'

2822
02:01:08,036 --> 02:01:09,028
But here's the thing...

2823
02:01:09,028 --> 02:01:12,000
But the arbiter might not have a very good impression of you.

2824
02:01:12,000 --> 02:01:13,086
And they'll think, 'Oh great, you're here to stir up trouble again!'

2825
02:01:13,086 --> 02:01:15,052
But that's not even the worst part.

2826
02:01:15,052 --> 02:01:17,060
But the most terrifying part is the long-term consequences that stem from a protracted lawsuit.

2827
02:01:17,060 --> 02:01:21,024
The losing side will harbor endless, long-term malice and seek revenge!

2828
02:01:21,024 --> 02:01:23,056
It could even lead to the annihilation of your entire family!

2829
02:01:23,056 --> 02:01:26,002
Let's take this a step further, to the victory in a bitter lawsuit.

2830
02:01:26,002 --> 02:01:28,048
This is also the ultimate fate of all factional strife.

2831
02:01:28,048 --> 02:01:32,020
All factional conflicts stem from initial disputes that were not properly resolved.

2832
02:01:32,020 --> 02:01:35,062
One side, with the emperor's backing, secured a temporary victory.

2833
02:01:35,062 --> 02:01:39,048
The emperor, however, failed to follow the path of the central and correct ninth five to settle and stop the dispute.

2834
02:01:39,048 --> 02:01:43,002
As a result, the losing side feels they've suffered a great injustice and taken a huge loss.

2835
02:01:43,002 --> 02:01:46,038
What follows is an increasingly messy and tangled cycle of mutual retaliation.

2836
02:01:46,038 --> 02:01:49,046
The entire Hexagram of Litigation, in essence, serves to remind us of one fundamental principle.

2837
02:01:49,046 --> 02:01:52,021
Success is built on strength and a solid foundation.

2838
02:01:52,021 --> 02:01:56,027
Engaging in disputes is an act that endlessly drains our strength and foundation.

2839
02:01:56,027 --> 02:01:59,005
Even if the strong prevail over the weak and win a protracted lawsuit,

2840
02:01:59,005 --> 02:02:02,057
But the resulting costs down the line are simply incalculable.

2841
02:02:02,057 --> 02:02:04,062
Therefore, it is essential to cease litigation and end disputes.

2842
02:02:04,062 --> 02:02:07,071
Traveling light is the path to good fortune.

2843
02:02:08,023 --> 02:02:10,021
The Hexagram of Xu represents the principle of sustenance.

2844
02:02:10,021 --> 02:02:12,081
Where there is the provision of food and drink, there is bound to be contention. Therefore, it is followed by the hexagram 'Conflict'.

2845
02:02:12,081 --> 02:02:14,025
And where there are disputes, there must be a great arbiter.

2846
02:02:14,025 --> 02:02:15,073
And conflict must be followed by the military.

2847
02:02:15,073 --> 02:02:18,013
The Xù Hexagram is about the competition for and distribution of resources.

2848
02:02:18,013 --> 02:02:19,081
Because resources are always finite,

2849
02:02:19,081 --> 02:02:22,037
If you get your hands on it, it means someone else didn't.

2850
02:02:22,037 --> 02:02:23,069
And this is what leads to conflict.

2851
02:02:23,069 --> 02:02:24,084
And this leads to the hexagram of Lawsuit.

2852
02:02:24,084 --> 02:02:27,004
So, with the Lawsuit Hexagram, if the litigation process is taken to its very end and still doesn't stop...

2853
02:02:27,004 --> 02:02:30,002
Ultimately, the conflict escalates.

2854
02:02:30,002 --> 02:02:32,074
And that's how more and more people get dragged into the conflict.

2855
02:02:32,074 --> 02:02:36,031
Both sides start calling for backup, and a full-scale battle begins.

2856
02:02:36,031 --> 02:02:39,055
Another nearly 40,000 words, just to marvel at the great wisdom of our ancestors.

2857
02:02:39,055 --> 02:02:43,024
In our next episode, we'll dive into the Hexagram of the Army, and explore the dynamics of group conflict!

